250 static int OS_SNPRINTF(OS_CHAR * str, size_t size, const OS_CHAR *format, ...)
251 {
252  va_list va;
253  va_start(va, format);
254  int ret = OS_VSNPRINTF(str, size, format, va);
255  va_end(va);
256  return ret;
257 }

287 static inline OS_BYTE toLittleEndianByteOrder(OS_BYTE val)
288 {
289  OS_ASSERT(sizeof(val) == sizeof(OS_BYTE)*1);
290  return val;

299 static inline OS_U16 toLittleEndianByteOrder(OS_U16 val)
300 {
301  OS_ASSERT(sizeof(val) == sizeof(OS_BYTE)*2);
302  if(IS_LITTLE_ENDIAN){
303  return val;
304  }
305  OS_U16 r;
306  ((OS_BYTE*)&r)[0] = ((OS_BYTE*)&val)[1];
307  ((OS_BYTE*)&r)[1] = ((OS_BYTE*)&val)[0];
308  return r;
309 }

314  if(IS_LITTLE_ENDIAN){
315  return val;
316  }

319  ((OS_BYTE*)&r)[1] = ((OS_BYTE*)&val)[0];
320  return r;

323 static inline OS_INT32 toLittleEndianByteOrder(OS_INT32 val)
324 {
325  OS_ASSERT(sizeof(val) == sizeof(OS_BYTE)*4);
326  if(IS_LITTLE_ENDIAN){
327  return val;
328  }
329  OS_INT32 r;
330  ((OS_BYTE*)&r)[0] = ((OS_BYTE*)&val)[3];
331  ((OS_BYTE*)&r)[1] = ((OS_BYTE*)&val)[2];
332  ((OS_BYTE*)&r)[2] = ((OS_BYTE*)&val)[1];
333  ((OS_BYTE*)&r)[3] = ((OS_BYTE*)&val)[0];
334  return r;
335 }

337 static inline OS_INT64 toLittleEndianByteOrder(OS_INT64 val)
338 {
339  OS_ASSERT(sizeof(val) == sizeof(OS_BYTE)*8);
340  if(IS_LITTLE_ENDIAN){
341  return val;
342  }
343  OS_INT64 r;
344  ((OS_BYTE*)&r)[0] = ((OS_BYTE*)&val)[7];
345  ((OS_BYTE*)&r)[1] = ((OS_BYTE*)&val)[6];
346  ((OS_BYTE*)&r)[2] = ((OS_BYTE*)&val)[5];
347  ((OS_BYTE*)&r)[3] = ((OS_BYTE*)&val)[4];
348  ((OS_BYTE*)&r)[4] = ((OS_BYTE*)&val)[3];
349  ((OS_BYTE*)&r)[5] = ((OS_BYTE*)&val)[2];
350  ((OS_BYTE*)&r)[6] = ((OS_BYTE*)&val)[1];
351  ((OS_BYTE*)&r)[7] = ((OS_BYTE*)&val)[0];
352  return r;
353 }

387 static inline long double toLittleEndianByteOrder(long double val)
388 {
389  // OS_ASSERT(sizeof(val) == sizeof(OS_BYTE)*8);
390  if(IS_LITTLE_ENDIAN){
391  return val;
392  }
393  long double r;
394  for(int i = 0; i < (int)sizeof(long double); i++){
395  ((OS_BYTE*)&r)[i] = ((OS_BYTE*)&val)[sizeof(long double)-1-i];
396  }
397  return r;
398 }

411 template <class T>
412 static bool parseSimpleRadix(const OS_CHAR *& p_str, T& p_val, int radix)
413 {
414  T val = 0, prev_val = 0;
415  const OS_CHAR * str = p_str;
416  const OS_CHAR * start = str;
417  for(int cur;; str++){
418  if(*str >= OS_TEXT('0') && *str <= OS_TEXT('9')){
419  cur = (int)(*str - OS_TEXT('0'));
420  }else if(*str >= OS_TEXT('a') && *str <= (OS_TEXT('z'))){
421  cur = 10 + (int)(*str - OS_TEXT('a'));
422  }else if(*str >= OS_TEXT('A') && *str <= OS_TEXT('Z')){
423  cur = 10 + (int)(*str - OS_TEXT('A'));
424  }else{
425  break;
426  }
427  if(cur >= radix){
428  /* p_str = start;
429  p_val = 0;
430  return false; */
431  break;
432  }
433  val = val * radix + (T)cur;
434  if(prev_val > val){
435  p_str = start;
436  p_val = 0;
437  return false;
438  }
439  prev_val = val;
440  }
441  p_val = val;
442  p_str = str;
443  return str > start;
444 }
445 
446 template <class T>
447 static bool parseSimpleHex(const OS_CHAR *& p_str, T& p_val)
448 {
449  T val = 0, prev_val = 0;
450  const OS_CHAR * str = p_str;
451  const OS_CHAR * start = str;
452  for(;; str++){
453  if(*str >= OS_TEXT('0') && *str <= OS_TEXT('9')){
454  val = (val << 4) + (T)(*str - OS_TEXT('0'));
455  }else if(*str >= OS_TEXT('a') && *str <= OS_TEXT('f')){
456  val = (val << 4) + 10 + (T)(*str - OS_TEXT('a'));
457  }else if(*str >= OS_TEXT('A') && *str <= OS_TEXT('F')){
458  val = (val << 4) + 10 + (T)(*str - OS_TEXT('A'));
459  }else{
460  break;
461  }
462  if(prev_val > val){
463  p_str = start;
464  p_val = 0;
465  return false;
466  }
467  prev_val = val;
468  }
469  p_val = val;
470  p_str = str;
471  return str > start;
472 }

474 template <class T>
475 static bool parseSimpleBin(const OS_CHAR *& p_str, T& p_val)
476 {
477  T val = 0, prev_val = 0;
478  const OS_CHAR * str = p_str;
479  const OS_CHAR * start = str;
480  for(; *str >= OS_TEXT('0') && *str <= OS_TEXT('1'); str++){
481  val = (val << 1) + (T)(*str - OS_TEXT('0'));
482  if(prev_val > val){
483  p_str = start;
484  p_val = 0;
485  return false;
486  }
487  prev_val = val;
488  }
489  p_val = val;
490  p_str = str;
491  return str > start;
492 }

494 template <class T>
495 static bool parseSimpleOctal(const OS_CHAR *& p_str, T& p_val)
496 {
497  T val = 0, prev_val = 0;
498  const OS_CHAR * str = p_str;
499  const OS_CHAR * start = str;
500  for(; *str >= OS_TEXT('0') && *str <= OS_TEXT('7'); str++)
501  {
502  val = (val << 3) + (T)(*str - OS_TEXT('0'));
503  if(prev_val > val){
504  p_str = start;
505  p_val = 0;
506  return false;
507  }
508  prev_val = val;
509  }
510  p_val = val;
511  p_str = str;
512  return str > start;
513 }

535 template <class T>
536 static bool parseSimpleFloat(const OS_CHAR *& p_str, T& p_val)
537 {
538  T val = 0;
539  const OS_CHAR * str = p_str;
540  const OS_CHAR * start = str;
541  for(; *str >= OS_TEXT('0') && *str <= OS_TEXT('9'); str++){
542  val = val * 10 + (*str - OS_TEXT('0'));
543  }
544  p_val = val;
545  p_str = str;
546  return str > start;
547 }
548 
549 static bool isValidCharAfterNumber(const OS_CHAR * str)
550 {
551  return !*str || OS_IS_SPACE(*str) || OS_STRCHR(OS_TEXT("!@#$%^&*()-+={}[]\\|;:'\",<.>/?`~"), *str);
552 }
553 
554 bool OS::Utils::parseFloat(const OS_CHAR *& str, OS_FLOAT& result, ENumberParseType parse_type, int int_radix)
555 {
556  const OS_CHAR * start_str = str;
557  int sign = 1;
558  if(*str == OS_TEXT('-')){
559  str++;
560  start_str++;
561  sign = -1;
562  }else if(*str == OS_TEXT('+')){
563  str++;
564  start_str++;
565  }
566 
567  OS_UINT uint_val;
568  if(parse_type == PARSE_INT){
569  bool is_valid = parseSimpleRadix(str, uint_val, int_radix);
570  if(!is_valid){
571  result = 0;
572  return false;
573  }
574  result = (OS_FLOAT)uint_val;
575  if((OS_UINT)result != uint_val){ // number overflow
576  result = 0;
577  return false;
578  }
579  if(sign < 0){
580  result = -result;
581  };
582  return true;
583  }else if(parse_type == PARSE_TOKEN && str[0] == OS_TEXT('0') && str[1] != OS_TEXT('.')){
584  bool is_valid, is_octal = false;
585  if(str[1] == OS_TEXT('x')){ // || str[1] == OS_TEXT('X')){ // parse hex
586  str += 2;
587  is_valid = parseSimpleHex(str, uint_val);
588  }else if(str[1] == OS_TEXT('b')){ // || str[1] == OS_TEXT('B')){ // parse bin
589  str += 2;
590  is_valid = parseSimpleBin(str, uint_val);
591  }else{ // parse octal
592  is_octal = true;
593  is_valid = parseSimpleOctal(str, uint_val);
594  }
595  if(!is_valid || (start_str+1 == str && !is_octal)){
596  result = 0;
597  return false;
598  }
599  result = (OS_FLOAT)uint_val;
600  if((OS_UINT)result != uint_val){ // number overflow
601  result = 0;
602  return false;
603  }
604  if(sign < 0){
605  result = -result;
606  };
607  return true;
608  }
609 
610  OS_FLOAT float_val;
611  if(!parseSimpleFloat(str, float_val)){
612  result = 0;
613  return false;
614  }
615 
616  if(*str == OS_TEXT('.')){ // parse float
617  if(str[1] == OS_TEXT('.')){
618  result = sign > 0 ? float_val : -float_val;
619  return true;
620  }
621  // parse 1.#INF ...
622  if(sign == 1 && start_str+1 == str && *start_str == OS_TEXT('1') && str[1] == OS_TEXT('#')){
623  const OS_CHAR * spec[] = {OS_TEXT("INF"), OS_TEXT("IND"), OS_TEXT("QNAN"), NULL};
624  int i = 0;
625  for(; spec[i]; i++){
626  int spec_len = (int)OS_STRLEN(spec[i]);
627  if(OS_MEMCMP(str+2, spec[i], spec_len) != 0)
628  continue;
629 
630  str += spec_len + 2;
631  if(isValidCharAfterNumber(str)){
632  OS_INT32 spec_val;
633  switch(i){
634  case 0:
635  spec_val = 0x7f800000; // INF
636  break;
637 
638  case 1:
639  spec_val = 0xffc00000; // IND
640  break;
641 
642  default:
643  OS_ASSERT(false);
644  // no break
645 
646  case 2:
647  spec_val = 0x7fc00000; // NAN
648  break;
649  }
650  result = (OS_FLOAT)fromLittleEndianByteOrder(*(float*)&spec_val);
651  return true;
652  }
653  }
654  result = 0;
655  return false;
656  }
657 
658  OS_FLOAT m = (OS_FLOAT)0.1;
659  for(str++; *str >= OS_TEXT('0') && *str <= OS_TEXT('9'); str++, m *= (OS_FLOAT)0.1){
660  float_val += (OS_FLOAT)(*str - OS_TEXT('0')) * m;
661  }
662  if(start_str == str){
663  result = 0;
664  return false;
665  }
666  if(*str == OS_TEXT('e') || *str == OS_TEXT('E')){
667  str++;
668  bool div = false; // + for default
669  if(*str == OS_TEXT('-')){
670  div = true;
671  str++;
672  }else if(*str == OS_TEXT('+')){
673  // div = false;
674  str++;
675  }
676  int pow;
677  if(!parseSimpleDec(str, pow)){
678  result = 0;
679  return false;
680  }
681  m = (OS_FLOAT)1.0;
682  for(int i = 0; i < pow; i++){
683  m *= (OS_FLOAT)10.0;
684  }
685  if(div){
686  float_val /= m;
687  }else{
688  float_val *= m;
689  }
690  }
691  if(*str == OS_TEXT('f') && isValidCharAfterNumber(str+1)){
692  str++;
693  }
694  result = sign > 0 ? float_val : -float_val;
695  return true;
696  }
697  if(start_str == str){
698  result = 0;
699  return false;
700  }
701  result = sign > 0 ? float_val : -float_val;
702  return true;
703 }
704

717 template <class T> struct FloatFormatStr
718 {
719  static const OS_CHAR * roundFmt(){ return OS_TEXT("%.f"); }
720  static const OS_CHAR * precisionFmt(){ return OS_TEXT("%.*f"); }
721  static const OS_CHAR * autoFmt(){ return OS_TEXT("%.*G"); }
722 };
723 
724 template <> struct FloatFormatStr<long double>
725 {
726  static const OS_CHAR * roundFmt(){ return OS_TEXT("%.Lf"); }
727  static const OS_CHAR * precisionFmt(){ return OS_TEXT("%.*Lf"); }
728  static const OS_CHAR * autoFmt(){ return OS_TEXT("%.*LG"); }
729 };

731 OS_CHAR * OS::Utils::numToStr(OS_CHAR * dst, OS_FLOAT a)
732 {
733  /* %G already handles removing trailing zeros from the fractional part */
734  OS_SNPRINTF(dst, sizeof(OS_CHAR)*127, FloatFormatStr<OS_NUMBER>::autoFmt(), a < 1e10 ? 15 : 30, a);
735  return dst;
736 }
737 
738 double OS::Utils::round(double a, int precision)
739 {
740  if(precision <= 0){
741  if(precision < 0){
742  double p = 10.0;
743  for(int i = -precision-1; i > 0; i--){
744  p *= 10.0;
745  }
746  return ::floor(a / p + 0.5) * p;
747  }
748  return ::floor(a + 0.5);
749  }
750  double p = 10.0;
751  for(int i = precision-1; i > 0; i--){
752  p *= 10.0;
753  }
754  return ::floor(a * p + 0.5) / p;
755 }
756 
757 OS_CHAR * OS::Utils::numToStr(OS_CHAR * dst, OS_FLOAT a, int precision)
758 {
759  if(precision <= 0) {
760  if(precision < 0) {
761  OS_FLOAT p = (OS_FLOAT)10.0;
762  for(int i = -precision-1; i > 0; i--){
763  p *= (OS_FLOAT)10.0;
764  }
765  a = (OS_FLOAT)::floor(a / p + (OS_FLOAT)0.5) * p;
766  }
767  OS_SNPRINTF(dst, sizeof(OS_CHAR)*127, FloatFormatStr<OS_NUMBER>::roundFmt(), a);
768  return dst;
769  }
770  int n = OS_SNPRINTF(dst, sizeof(OS_CHAR)*127, FloatFormatStr<OS_NUMBER>::precisionFmt(), precision, a);
771  OS_ASSERT(n >= 1 && (!OS_STRSTR(dst, OS_TEXT(".")) || dst[n-1] != '0')); (void)n;
772  return dst;
773 }

780 OS_FLOAT OS::Utils::strToFloat(const OS_CHAR* str)
781 {
782  OS_FLOAT fval;
783  if(parseFloat(str, fval, PARSE_FLOAT) && (!*str || (*str==OS_TEXT('f') && !str[1]))){
784  return fval;
785  }
786  return 0;
787 }
788 
789 #define OS_STR_HASH_START_VALUE 5381
790 #define OS_ADD_STR_HASH_VALUE hash = ((hash << 5) + hash) + *buf
791 // #define OS_ADD_STR_HASH_VALUE hash ^= (hash<<6) + (hash>>2) + *buf;
792 
793 #define OS_STR_HASH_LIMIT_SHIFT 5
794 
795 int OS::Utils::keyToHash(const void * p_buf, int size)
796 {
797  OS_ASSERT(size >= 0);
798  if(size < 0) size = 0;
799  int step = (size >> OS_STR_HASH_LIMIT_SHIFT) + 1;
800  const OS_BYTE * buf = (const OS_BYTE*)p_buf;
801  const OS_BYTE * end = buf + size;
802  int hash = OS_STR_HASH_START_VALUE;
803  for(; buf < end; buf += step){
804  OS_ADD_STR_HASH_VALUE;
805  }
806  return hash;
807 }
808 
809 int OS::Utils::keyToHash(const void * buf1, int size1, const void * buf2, int size2)
810 {
811  OS_ASSERT(size1 >= 0 && size2 >= 0);
812  if(size1 < 0) size1 = 0;
813  if(size2 < 0) size2 = 0;
814  if(size2 > 0){
815  int size = size1 + size2;
816  int step = (size >> OS_STR_HASH_LIMIT_SHIFT) + 1;
817  const OS_BYTE * buf = (const OS_BYTE*)buf1;
818  const OS_BYTE * end = buf + size1;
819  int hash = OS_STR_HASH_START_VALUE;
820  for(; buf < end; buf += step){
821  OS_ADD_STR_HASH_VALUE;
822  }
823  buf = (const OS_BYTE*)buf2 + (buf - end);
824  end = (const OS_BYTE*)buf2 + size2;
825  for(; buf < end; buf += step){
826  OS_ADD_STR_HASH_VALUE;
827  }
828  return hash;
829  }
830  return keyToHash(buf1, size1);
831 }
832 
833 int OS::Utils::cmp(const void * buf1, int len1, const void * buf2, int len2)
834 {
835  int len = len1 < len2 ? len1 : len2;
836  int cmp = OS_MEMCMP(buf1, buf2, len);
837  return cmp ? cmp : len1 - len2;
838 }

1076 OS::Core::String& OS::Core::String::operator=(const String& b)
1077 {
1078  if(string != b.string){
1079  OS_ASSERT(string->external_ref_count > 0);
1080  if(!--string->external_ref_count && !string->ref_count){
1081  allocator->core->saveFreeCandidateValue(string);
1082  }
1083  string = b.string;
1084  string->external_ref_count++;
1085 #ifdef OS_DEBUG
1086  this->str = string->toChar();
1087 #endif
1088  }
1089  return *this;
1090 }

1274 void OS::Core::Buffer::freeCacheStr()
1275 {
1276  if(cache_str){
1277  if(!--cache_str->external_ref_count && !cache_str->ref_count){
1278  allocator->core->saveFreeCandidateValue(cache_str);
1279  }
1280  cache_str = NULL;
1281  }
1282 }
1283 
1284 void OS::Core::Buffer::swap(Buffer& b)
1285 {
1286  OS * temp_allocator = allocator;
1287  GCStringValue * temp_cache_str = cache_str;
1288  OS_BYTE * temp_buf = buffer.buf;
1289  int temp_capacity = buffer.capacity;
1290  int temp_count = buffer.count;
1291  int temp_pos = pos;
1292 
1293  allocator = b.allocator;
1294  cache_str = b.cache_str;
1295  buffer.buf = b.buffer.buf;
1296  buffer.capacity = b.buffer.capacity;
1297  buffer.count = b.buffer.count;
1298  pos = b.pos;
1299 
1300  b.allocator = temp_allocator;
1301  b.cache_str = temp_cache_str;
1302  b.buffer.buf = temp_buf;
1303  b.buffer.capacity = temp_capacity;
1304  b.buffer.count = temp_count;
1305  b.pos = temp_pos;
1306 }
1307 
1308 OS::Core::GCStringValue * OS::Core::Buffer::toGCStringValue()
1309 {
1310  if(!cache_str){
1311  cache_str = allocator->core->pushStringValue((void*)buffer.buf, buffer.count);
1312  cache_str->external_ref_count++;
1313  allocator->pop();
1314  }
1315  return cache_str;
1316 }

1385 OS::String::~String()
1386 {
1387  OS_ASSERT(string->external_ref_count > 0);
1388  if(!--string->external_ref_count && !string->ref_count){
1389  allocator->core->saveFreeCandidateValue(string);
1390  }
1391  string = NULL;
1392  allocator->release();
1393 }

1395 OS::String& OS::String::operator=(const Core::String& str)
1396 {
1397  if(string != str.string){
1398  OS_ASSERT(string->external_ref_count > 0);
1399  if(!--string->external_ref_count && !string->ref_count){
1400  allocator->core->saveFreeCandidateValue(string);
1401  }
1402  string = str.string;
1403  string->external_ref_count++;
1404 #ifdef OS_DEBUG
1405  this->str = string->toChar();
1406 #endif
1407  }
1408  return *this;
1409 }

1588 bool OS::Core::Tokenizer::TokenData::isTypeOf(TokenType token_type) const
1589 {
1590  if(type == token_type){
1591  return true;
1592  }
1593  if(token_type == OS::Core::Tokenizer::SEPARATOR){
1594  switch(type)
1595  {
1596  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::BEGIN_CODE_BLOCK: // {
1597  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::END_CODE_BLOCK: // }
1598 
1599  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::BEGIN_BRACKET_BLOCK: // (
1600  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::END_BRACKET_BLOCK: // )
1601 
1602  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::BEGIN_ARRAY_BLOCK: // [
1603  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::END_ARRAY_BLOCK: // ]
1604 
1605  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::CODE_SEPARATOR: // ;
1606  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::PARAM_SEPARATOR: // ,
1607  return true;
1608  }
1609  return false;
1610  }
1611  if(token_type == BINARY_OPERATOR){
1612  switch(type)
1613  {
1614  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::PARAM_SEPARATOR:
1615  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_QUESTION:
1616 
1617  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_INDIRECT: // .
1618  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_CONCAT: // ..
1619  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::BEFORE_INJECT_VAR:
1620  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::AFTER_INJECT_VAR:
1621  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_IN: // in
1622  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_IS:
1623  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_AS:
1624 
1625  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_AND: // &&
1626  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_OR: // ||
1627  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_PTR_EQ: // ===
1628  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_PTR_NE: // !==
1629  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_EQ: // ==
1630  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_NE: // !=
1631  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_GE: // >=
1632  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_LE: // <=
1633  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_GREATER: // >
1634  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_LESS: // <
1635 
1636  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_BIT_AND: // &
1637  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_BIT_OR: // |
1638  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_BIT_XOR: // ^
1639  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_BIT_NOT: // ~
1640  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_COMPARE: // <=>
1641  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_ADD: // +
1642  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_SUB: // -
1643  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_MUL: // *
1644  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_DIV: // /
1645  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_MOD: // %
1646  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LSHIFT: // <<
1647  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_RSHIFT: // >>
1648  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_POW: // **
1649 
1650  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_BIT_AND_ASSIGN: // &=
1651  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_BIT_OR_ASSIGN: // |=
1652  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_BIT_XOR_ASSIGN: // ^=
1653  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_BIT_NOT_ASSIGN: // ~=
1654  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_ADD_ASSIGN: // +=
1655  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_SUB_ASSIGN: // -=
1656  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_MUL_ASSIGN: // *=
1657  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_DIV_ASSIGN: // /=
1658  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_MOD_ASSIGN: // %=
1659  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LSHIFT_ASSIGN: // <<=
1660  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_RSHIFT_ASSIGN: // >>=
1661  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_POW_ASSIGN: // **=
1662 
1663  case OS::Core::Tokenizer::OPERATOR_ASSIGN: // =
1664  return true;
1665  }
1666  return false;
1667  }
1668  return false;
1669 }

1746 const int OS::Core::Tokenizer::operator_count = sizeof(operator_desc) / sizeof(operator_desc[0]);
1747 
1748 int OS::Core::Tokenizer::compareOperatorDesc(const void * a, const void * b)
1749 {
1750  const OperatorDesc * op0 = (const OperatorDesc*)a;
1751  const OperatorDesc * op1 = (const OperatorDesc*)b;
1752  // return (int)OS_STRLEN(op1->name) - (int)OS_STRLEN(op0->name);
1753  return op1->len - op0->len;
1754 }
1755 
1756 void OS::Core::Tokenizer::initOperatorsTable()
1757 {
1758  if(!operator_initialized){
1759  for(int i = 0; i < operator_count; i++){
1760  operator_desc[i].len = OS_STRLEN(operator_desc[i].name);
1761  }
1762  ::qsort(operator_desc, operator_count, sizeof(operator_desc[0]), Tokenizer::compareOperatorDesc);
1763  operator_initialized = true;
1764  }
1765 }

1767 OS::Core::Tokenizer::InitOperators::InitOperators()
1768 {
1769  initOperatorsTable();
1770 }

1842 bool OS::Core::Tokenizer::parseText(const OS_CHAR * text, int len, const String& filename, bool is_real_file, OS_ESourceCodeType source_code_type, bool check_utf8_bom)
1843 {
1844  OS_ASSERT(text_data->lines.count == 0);
1845 
1846  OS * allocator = getAllocator();
1847 
1848  text_data->filename = filename;
1849  text_data->is_real_file = is_real_file;
1850 
1851  allocator->vectorClear(text_data->lines);
1852 
1853  const OS_CHAR * str = text;
1854  const OS_CHAR * str_end = str + len;
1855  while(str < str_end)
1856  {
1857 #if 0
1858  const OS_CHAR * line_end = OS_STRCHR(str, OS_TEXT('\n'));
1859  if(line_end){
1860  allocator->vectorAddItem(text_data->lines, String(allocator, str, line_end - str, false, true) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
1861  str = line_end+1;
1862  }else{
1863  allocator->vectorAddItem(text_data->lines, String(allocator, str, str_end - str, false, true) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
1864  break;
1865  }
1866 #else
1867  const OS_CHAR * line_end = str;
1868  for(; line_end < str_end && *line_end != OS_TEXT('\n'); line_end++);
1869  allocator->vectorAddItem(text_data->lines, String(allocator, str, (int)(line_end - str)) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
1870  str = line_end+1;
1871 #endif
1872  }
1873  if(parseLines(source_code_type, check_utf8_bom)){
1874  if(!tokens.count){
1875  allocator->vectorClear(text_data->lines);
1876  allocator->vectorAddItem(text_data->lines, String(allocator, OS_TEXT("return;")) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
1877  return parseLines(OS_SOURCECODE_PLAIN, false);
1878  }
1879  return true;
1880  }
1881  return false;
1882 }

1884 OS::Core::Tokenizer::TokenData * OS::Core::Tokenizer::addToken(const String& str, TokenType type, int line, int pos OS_DBG_FILEPOS_DECL)
1885 {

1887  TokenData * token = new (allocator->malloc(sizeof(TokenData) OS_DBG_FILEPOS_PARAM)) TokenData(text_data, str, type, line, pos);
1888  allocator->vectorAddItem(tokens, token OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
1889  return token;

1891 
1892 bool OS::Core::Tokenizer::parseFloat(const OS_CHAR *& str, OS_FLOAT& fval, bool parse_end_spaces)
1893 {
1894  const OS_CHAR * start = str;
1895  if(Utils::parseFloat(str, fval, Utils::PARSE_TOKEN)){
1896  if(isValidCharAfterNumber(str)){
1897  if(parse_end_spaces){
1898  parseSpaces(str);
1899  }
1900  return true;
1901  }
1902  for(int i = -1; str+i > start; i--){
1903  if(OS_IS_SPACE(str[i])){
1904  continue;
1905  }
1906  if(str[i] == OS_TEXT('.')){
1907  str += i;
1908  return true;
1909  }
1910  }
1911  if(*str == OS_TEXT('f') && isValidCharAfterNumber(str+1)){
1912  str++;
1913  if(parse_end_spaces){
1914  parseSpaces(str);
1915  }
1916  return true;
1917  }
1918  }
1919  return false;
1920 }
1921 
1922 /*
1923  implement EStringType & StringTypeStack outside of OS::Core::Tokenizer::parseLines to prevent error:
1924  template argument for template<class T> struct ObjectScript::OS::Vector
1925  uses local type ObjectScript::OS::Core::Tokenizer::parseLines(ObjectScript::OS_ESourceCodeType, bool)::EStringType
1926 */
1927 enum EStringType { NOT_STRING, SIMPLE, QUOTE, MULTI_SIMPLE, MULTI_QUOTE };
1928 struct StringTypeStack: public OS::Vector<EStringType>
1929 {
1930  OS * allocator;
1931  StringTypeStack(OS * a){ allocator = a; }
1932  ~StringTypeStack()
1933  {
1934  allocator->vectorClear(*this);
1935  }
1936 };
1937 
1938 bool OS::Core::Tokenizer::parseLines(OS_ESourceCodeType source_code_type, bool check_utf8_bom)
1939 {
1940  OS * allocator = getAllocator();
1941  cur_line = cur_pos = 0;
1942  bool template_enabled = source_code_type == OS_SOURCECODE_TEMPLATE;
1943  bool is_template = template_enabled;
1944 
1945  EStringType string_type = NOT_STRING;
1946  StringTypeStack string_type_stack(allocator);
1947  int var_in_string = 0;
1948 
1949  const char * multi_string_id = NULL;
1950  int multi_string_id_len = 0;
1951 
1952  for(; cur_line < text_data->lines.count; cur_line++){
1953  // parse line
1954  const OS_CHAR * line_start = text_data->lines[cur_line].toChar();
1955  const OS_CHAR * str = line_start;
1956 
1957  cur_pos = 0;
1958  if(!cur_line){
1959  if(check_utf8_bom){
1960  OS_ASSERT(sizeof(OS_CHAR) == sizeof(char));
1961  if(str[0] == '\xef' && str[1] == '\xbb' && str[2] == '\xbf'){
1962  line_start += 3;
1963  str = line_start;
1964  }
1965  }
1966  if(source_code_type == OS_SOURCECODE_AUTO){
1967  if(str[0] == OS_TEXT('<') && str[1] == OS_TEXT('%')){
1968  source_code_type = OS_SOURCECODE_TEMPLATE;
1969  template_enabled = true;
1970  is_template = false;
1971  str += 2;
1972  }
1973  }
1974  }
1975 
1976  for(;;){
1977  if(template_enabled && is_template){
1978  Buffer buf(allocator);
1979  for(;;){
1980  const OS_CHAR * line_pos = str;
1981  const OS_CHAR * open_os_tag = OS_STRSTR(str, OS_TEXT("<%"));
1982  if(open_os_tag){
1983  buf.append(line_pos, (int)(open_os_tag - line_pos));
1984  if(buf.getSize() > 0){
1985  addToken(buf, OUTPUT_STRING, cur_line, (int)(str - line_start) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
1986  }
1987  str = open_os_tag + 2;
1988  is_template = false;
1989 
1990  if(str[0] == OS_TEXT('=')){
1991  addToken(String(allocator, str, 1), OUTPUT_NEXT_VALUE, cur_line, (int)(str - line_pos) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
1992  str++;
1993  }
1994  break;
1995  }
1996  buf.append(line_pos);
1997  buf.append(OS_TEXT("\n"));
1998  if(cur_line+1 >= text_data->lines.count){
1999  if(buf.getSize() > 0){
2000  addToken(buf, OUTPUT_STRING, cur_line, (int)(str - line_pos) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
2001  }
2002  return true;
2003  }
2004  str = line_start = text_data->lines[++cur_line].toChar();
2005  }
2006  }
2007 
2008  // skip spaces
2009  parseSpaces(str);
2010  if(!*str){
2011  break;
2012  }
2013 
2014  if(template_enabled && !is_template && str[0] == OS_TEXT('%') && str[1] == OS_TEXT('>')){
2015  str += 2;
2016  is_template = true;
2017  continue;
2018  }
2019 
2020  if(var_in_string == 1 && *str == OS_TEXT('}')){
2021  var_in_string = 0;
2022  // OS_ASSERT(saved_string_type == QUOTE || saved_string_type == MULTI_QUOTE);
2023  addToken(String(allocator, OS_TEXT(")")), END_BRACKET_BLOCK, cur_line, (int)(str - line_start) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
2024  addToken(String(allocator, OS_TEXT("}")), AFTER_INJECT_VAR, cur_line, (int)(str - line_start) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
2025  string_type = allocator->vectorPop(string_type_stack);
2026  OS_ASSERT(string_type == QUOTE || string_type == MULTI_QUOTE);
2027  // saved_string_type = NOT_STRING;
2028  if(string_type == MULTI_QUOTE){
2029  str++;
2030  }
2031  }else if(*str == OS_TEXT('`')){
2032  const OS_CHAR * token_start = str;
2033  str = OS_STRCHR(str+1, OS_TEXT('`'));
2034  if(!str){
2035  cur_pos = OS_STRLEN(line_start);
2036  error = ERROR_CONST_STRING;
2037  return false;
2038  }
2039  str++;
2040  addToken(String(allocator, token_start+1, str-token_start-2), STRING, cur_line, (int)(token_start - line_start) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
2041  continue;
2042  }else if(*str == OS_TEXT('"')){
2043  string_type = QUOTE;
2044  }else if(*str == OS_TEXT('\'')){
2045  string_type = SIMPLE;
2046  }else if(str[0] == OS_TEXT('<') && str[1] == OS_TEXT('<') && str[2] == OS_TEXT('<')){
2047  if(var_in_string){
2048  error = ERROR_SYNTAX;
2049  cur_pos = (int)(str - line_start);
2050  return false;
2051  }
2052  str += 3;
2053  multi_string_id = str;
2054  while(*str && *str != OS_TEXT('\'') && *str != OS_TEXT('"')) str++;
2055  if(!*str || (int)(str - multi_string_id) < 2){
2056  cur_pos = (int)(str - line_start);
2057  error = ERROR_CONST_STRING;
2058  return false;
2059  }
2060  multi_string_id_len = str - multi_string_id;
2061  if(*str == OS_TEXT('\'')){
2062  string_type = MULTI_SIMPLE;
2063  str++;
2064  }else if(*str == OS_TEXT('"')){
2065  string_type = MULTI_QUOTE;
2066  str++;
2067  }else{
2068  cur_pos = (int)(str - line_start);
2069  error = ERROR_CONST_STRING;
2070  return false;
2071  }
2072  while(*str && *str <= OS_TEXT(' ')) str++;
2073  if(*str){
2074  str = multi_string_id + multi_string_id_len + 1;
2075  }else{
2076  if(cur_line+1 >= text_data->lines.count){
2077  cur_pos = (int)(str + OS_STRLEN(str) - line_start);
2078  error = ERROR_CONST_STRING;
2079  return false;
2080  }
2081  str = line_start = text_data->lines[++cur_line].toChar();
2082  }
2083  }else{
2084  string_type = NOT_STRING;
2085  }
2086  if(string_type == MULTI_QUOTE || string_type == MULTI_SIMPLE){ // begin multi line string
2087  if(var_in_string){
2088  error = ERROR_SYNTAX;
2089  cur_pos = (int)(str - line_start);
2090  return false;
2091  }
2092  Buffer buf(allocator);
2093  for(;;){
2094  const OS_CHAR * token_start = str;
2095  bool finished = false;
2096  while(*str){
2097  if(OS_MEMCMP(str, multi_string_id, multi_string_id_len) == 0){
2098  if(var_in_string){
2099  error = ERROR_SYNTAX;
2100  cur_pos = (int)(str - line_start);
2101  return false;
2102  }
2103  string_type = NOT_STRING;
2104  bool start = str == line_start;
2105  str += multi_string_id_len;
2106  if(start && buf.buffer.count >= (int)sizeof(OS_CHAR)){
2107  OS_CHAR * end = (OS_CHAR*)buf.buffer.buf + (buf.buffer.count/sizeof(OS_CHAR));
2108  if(end[-1] == OS_TEXT('\n')){
2109  buf.buffer.count -= sizeof(OS_CHAR);
2110  end--;
2111  }
2112  if(end[-1] == OS_TEXT('\r')){
2113  buf.buffer.count -= sizeof(OS_CHAR);
2114  }
2115  }
2116  addToken(buf, STRING, cur_line, (int)(token_start - line_start) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
2117  finished = true;
2118  break;
2119  }
2120  OS_CHAR c = *str++;
2121  if(string_type == MULTI_QUOTE){
2122  if(c == OS_TEXT('$') && string_type != SIMPLE && *str == OS_TEXT('{')){
2123  if(var_in_string){
2124  error = ERROR_SYNTAX;
2125  cur_pos = (int)(str - line_start);
2126  return false;
2127  }
2128  var_in_string = 1;
2129  finished = true;
2130  allocator->vectorPush(string_type_stack, string_type OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
2131  // saved_string_type = string_type;
2132  string_type = NOT_STRING;
2133  str++;
2134  addToken(buf, STRING, cur_line, (int)(token_start - line_start) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
2135  addToken(String(allocator, OS_TEXT("${")), BEFORE_INJECT_VAR, cur_line, (int)(str - 2 - line_start) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
2136  addToken(String(allocator, OS_TEXT("(")), BEGIN_BRACKET_BLOCK, cur_line, (int)(str - 2 - line_start) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
2137  break;
2138  }else if(c == OS_TEXT('\\')){
2139  switch(*str){
2140  case OS_TEXT('$'): c = OS_TEXT('$'); str++; break;
2141  }
2142  }
2143  }
2144  buf.append(c);
2145  }
2146  if(finished){
2147  break;
2148  }
2149  if(cur_line+1 >= text_data->lines.count){
2150  cur_pos = (int)(str + OS_STRLEN(str) - line_start);
2151  error = ERROR_CONST_STRING;
2152  return false;
2153  }
2154  str = line_start = text_data->lines[++cur_line].toChar();
2155  buf.append(OS_TEXT("\n"));
2156  }
2157  continue;
2158  }
2159  if( string_type != NOT_STRING){ // begin string
2160  const OS_CHAR * token_start = str;
2161  Buffer buf(allocator);
2162  OS_CHAR close_char = string_type == SIMPLE ? OS_TEXT('\'') : string_type == QUOTE ? OS_TEXT('"') : OS_TEXT('\0');
2163  bool finished = false;
2164  for(str++; *str && *str != close_char;){
2165  OS_CHAR c = *str++;
2166  if(c == OS_TEXT('$') && string_type != SIMPLE && *str == OS_TEXT('{')){
2167  if(var_in_string){
2168  error = ERROR_SYNTAX;
2169  cur_pos = (int)(str - line_start);
2170  return false;
2171  }
2172  var_in_string = 1;
2173  finished = true;
2174  allocator->vectorPush(string_type_stack, string_type OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
2175  // saved_string_type = string_type;
2176  string_type = NOT_STRING;
2177  str++;
2178  addToken(buf, STRING, cur_line, (int)(token_start - line_start) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
2179  addToken(String(allocator, OS_TEXT("${")), BEFORE_INJECT_VAR, cur_line, (int)(str - 2 - line_start) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
2180  addToken(String(allocator, OS_TEXT("(")), BEGIN_BRACKET_BLOCK, cur_line, (int)(str - 2 - line_start) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
2181  break;
2182  }else if(c == OS_TEXT('\\')){
2183  if(string_type == SIMPLE){
2184  switch(*str){
2185  case OS_TEXT('\''): c = OS_TEXT('\''); str++; break;
2186  case OS_TEXT('\\'): c = OS_TEXT('\\'); str++; break;
2187  }
2188  }else{
2189  switch(*str){
2190  case OS_TEXT('r'): c = OS_TEXT('\r'); str++; break;
2191  case OS_TEXT('n'): c = OS_TEXT('\n'); str++; break;
2192  case OS_TEXT('t'): c = OS_TEXT('\t'); str++; break;
2193  case OS_TEXT('v'): c = OS_TEXT('\v'); str++; break;
2194  case OS_TEXT('b'): c = OS_TEXT('\b'); str++; break;
2195  case OS_TEXT('f'): c = OS_TEXT('\f'); str++; break;
2196  case OS_TEXT('\"'): c = OS_TEXT('\"'); str++; break;
2197  // case OS_TEXT('\''): c = OS_TEXT('\''); str++; break;
2198  case OS_TEXT('\\'): c = OS_TEXT('\\'); str++; break;
2199  case OS_TEXT('$'): c = OS_TEXT('$'); str++; break;
2200  //case OS_TEXT('x'):
2201  default:
2202  {
2203  int val;
2204  int max_val = sizeof(OS_CHAR) == 2 ? 0xFFFF : 0xFF;
2205 
2206  if(*str == OS_TEXT('x')){ // || *str == OS_TEXT('X')){ // parse hex
2207  str++;
2208  if(!parseSimpleHex(str, val)){
2209  cur_pos = (int)(str - line_start);
2210  error = ERROR_CONST_STRING_ESCAPE_CHAR;
2211  return false;
2212  }
2213  }else if(*str == OS_TEXT('0')){ // octal
2214  if(!parseSimpleOctal(str, val)){
2215  cur_pos = (int)(str - line_start);
2216  error = ERROR_CONST_STRING_ESCAPE_CHAR;
2217  return false;
2218  }
2219  }else if(*str >= OS_TEXT('1') && *str <= OS_TEXT('9')){
2220  if(!parseSimpleDec(str, val)){
2221  cur_pos = (int)(str - line_start);
2222  error = ERROR_CONST_STRING_ESCAPE_CHAR;
2223  return false;
2224  }
2225  }else{
2226  val = c;
2227  }
2228  c = (OS_CHAR)(val <= max_val ? val : max_val);
2229  }
2230  break;
2231  }
2232  }
2233  }
2234  buf.append(c);
2235  }
2236  if(finished){
2237  continue;
2238  }
2239  OS_ASSERT(string_type == SIMPLE || string_type == QUOTE);
2240  if(*str != close_char){
2241  cur_pos = (int)(str - line_start);
2242  error = ERROR_CONST_STRING;
2243  return false;
2244  }
2245  string_type = NOT_STRING;
2246  str++;
2247  addToken(buf, STRING, cur_line, (int)(token_start - line_start) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
2248  continue;
2249  }
2250 
2251  if(*str == OS_TEXT('/')){
2252  if(str[1] == OS_TEXT('/')){ // begin line comment
2253  if(settings.save_comments){
2254  addToken(String(allocator, str), COMMENT_LINE, cur_line, (int)(str - line_start) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
2255  }
2256  break;
2257  }
2258  if(str[1] == OS_TEXT('*')){ // begin multi line comment
2259  Buffer comment(allocator);
2260  comment.append(str, 2);
2261  int startLine = cur_line;
2262  int startPos = (int)(str - line_start);
2263  for(str += 2;;){
2264  const OS_CHAR * end = OS_STRSTR(str, OS_TEXT("*/"));
2265  if(end){
2266  if(settings.save_comments){
2267  comment.append(str, (int)(end+2 - str));
2268  addToken(comment, COMMENT_MULTI_LINE, startLine, startPos OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
2269  }
2270  str = end + 2;
2271  break;
2272  }
2273  if(cur_line >= text_data->lines.count){
2274  error = ERROR_MULTI_LINE_COMMENT;
2275  cur_pos = (int)(str - line_start);
2276  return false;
2277  }
2278  if(settings.save_comments){
2279  comment.append(str);
2280  comment.append(OS_TEXT("\n")); // OS_TEXT("\r\n"));
2281  }
2282  str = line_start = text_data->lines[++cur_line].toChar();
2283  }
2284  continue;
2285  }
2286  }
2287 
2288  if(*str == OS_TEXT('_') || *str == OS_TEXT('$') // || *str == OS_TEXT('@')
2289  || (*str >= OS_TEXT('a') && *str <= OS_TEXT('z'))
2290  || (*str >= OS_TEXT('A') && *str <= OS_TEXT('Z')) )
2291  { // parse name
2292  const OS_CHAR * name_start = str;
2293  for(str++; *str; str++){
2294  if(*str == OS_TEXT('_') || *str == OS_TEXT('$') || *str == OS_TEXT('@')
2295  || (*str >= OS_TEXT('a') && *str <= OS_TEXT('z'))
2296  || (*str >= OS_TEXT('A') && *str <= OS_TEXT('Z'))
2297  || (*str >= OS_TEXT('0') && *str <= OS_TEXT('9')) )
2298  {
2299  continue;
2300  }
2301  break;
2302  }
2303  String name = String(allocator, name_start, (int)(str - name_start));
2304  addToken(name, NAME, cur_line, (int)(name_start - line_start) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
2305  continue;
2306  }
2307  // parse operator
2308  if(0 && (*str == OS_TEXT('-') || *str == OS_TEXT('+')) && (str[1] >= OS_TEXT('0') && str[1] <= OS_TEXT('9'))){
2309  // int i = 0;
2310  }else{
2311  int i;
2312  for(i = 0; i < operator_count; i++){
2313  // size_t len = OS_STRLEN(operator_desc[i].name);
2314  int len = operator_desc[i].len;
2315  if(OS_STRNCMP(str, operator_desc[i].name, len) == 0){
2316  addToken(String(allocator, str, (int)len), operator_desc[i].type, cur_line, (int)(str - line_start) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
2317  if(var_in_string && len == 1){
2318  if(*str == OS_TEXT('{')){
2319  var_in_string++;
2320  }else if(*str == OS_TEXT('}')){
2321  if(--var_in_string <= 0){
2322  error = ERROR_SYNTAX;
2323  cur_pos = (int)(str - line_start);
2324  return false;
2325  }
2326  }
2327  }
2328  str += len;
2329  break;
2330  }
2331  }
2332  if(i < operator_count){
2333  continue;
2334  }
2335  }
2336  {
2337  OS_FLOAT fval;
2338  const OS_CHAR * token_start = str;
2339  if(parseFloat(str, fval, true)){
2340  TokenData * token = addToken(String(allocator, token_start, (int)(str - token_start), false, true),
2341  NUMBER, cur_line, (int)(token_start - line_start) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
2342  token->setFloat(fval);
2343  continue;
2344  }
2345  }
2346 
2347  error = ERROR_SYNTAX;
2348  cur_pos = (int)(str - line_start);
2349  return false;
2350  }
2351  }
2352  // PrintTokens();
2353  return true;
2354 }

2663 OS::Core::String OS::Core::Compiler::Expression::getSlotStr(OS::Core::Compiler * compiler, Scope * scope, int slot_num, int up_count)
2664 {
2665  struct Lib {
2666  static String getInfoStr(OS::Core::Compiler * compiler, const String& str)
2667  {
2668  if(str.getLen() > 100){
2669  return OS::String(compiler->allocator, str.toChar(), 48) + OS_TEXT("...")
2670  + String(compiler->allocator, str.toChar() + str.getLen() - 48, 48);
2671  }
2672  return str;
2673  }
2674  };
2675  // OS_ASSERT(slot_num);
2676  OS * allocator = compiler->allocator;
2677  for(; up_count > 0; up_count--){
2678  OS_ASSERT(scope->function && scope->function->parent);
2679  scope = scope->function->parent;
2680  }
2681  if(slot_num < 0){
2682  slot_num = -slot_num-1;
2683  if(slot_num == CONST_NULL){
2684  return String(allocator, OS_TEXT("const null"));
2685  }
2686  if(slot_num == CONST_FALSE){
2687  return String(allocator, OS_TEXT("const false"));
2688  }
2689  if(slot_num == CONST_TRUE){
2690  return String(allocator, OS_TEXT("const true"));
2691  }
2692  slot_num -= CONST_STD_VALUES;
2693  if(slot_num < compiler->prog_numbers.count){
2694  OS_CHAR temp[128];
2695  OS::Utils::numToStr(temp, compiler->prog_numbers[slot_num]);
2696  return String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("const number %s"), temp); // compiler->prog_numbers[slot_num]);
2697  }
2698  slot_num -= compiler->prog_numbers.count;
2699  return String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("const string \"%s\""), Lib::getInfoStr(compiler, compiler->prog_strings[slot_num]).toChar());
2700  }
2701  if(slot_num >= scope->function->num_locals){
2702  return allocator->core->strings->var_temp_prefix;
2703  }
2704  for(;;){
2705  for(int i = scope->locals.count-1; i >= 0; i--){
2706  const Scope::LocalVar& local_var = scope->locals[i];
2707  if(local_var.index == slot_num){
2708  if(local_var.name == allocator->core->strings->var_temp_prefix){
2709  OS_ASSERT(false);
2710  return allocator->core->strings->var_temp_prefix;
2711  }
2712  return String::format(allocator, slot_num < scope->function->num_params ? OS_TEXT("param %s") : OS_TEXT("var %s"), local_var.name.toChar());
2713  }
2714  }
2715  if(scope == scope->function){
2716  OS_ASSERT(false);
2717  break;
2718  }
2719  scope = scope->parent;
2720  }
2721  return allocator->core->strings->var_temp_prefix; // shut up compiler
2722 }
2723 
2724 void OS::Core::Compiler::Expression::debugPrint(Buffer& out, OS::Core::Compiler * compiler, Scope * scope, int depth)
2725 {
2726  OS * allocator = getAllocator();
2727  compiler->debugPrintSourceLine(out, token);
2728 
2729  int i;
2730  OS_CHAR * spaces = (OS_CHAR*)alloca(sizeof(OS_CHAR)*(depth*2+1));
2731  for(i = 0; i < depth*2; i++){
2732  spaces[i] = OS_TEXT(' ');
2733  }
2734  spaces[i] = OS_TEXT('\0');
2735 
2736  const OS_CHAR * type_name, * exp_name;
2737  ECompiledValueType val_type;
2738  switch(type){
2739  default:
2740  OS_ASSERT(false);
2741  break;
2742 
2743  case EXP_TYPE_NOP:
2744  for(i = 0; i < list.count; i++){
2745  list[i]->debugPrint(out, compiler, scope, depth);
2746  }
2747  break;
2748 
2749  case EXP_TYPE_CODE_LIST:
2750  type_name = OS::Core::Compiler::getExpName(type);
2751  for(i = 0; i < list.count; i++){
2752  list[i]->debugPrint(out, compiler, scope, depth);
2753  }
2754  break;
2755 
2756  case EXP_TYPE_IF:
2757  OS_ASSERT(list.count == 2 || list.count == 3);
2758  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%sbegin if\n"), spaces);
2759  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%s begin bool exp\n"), spaces);
2760  list[0]->debugPrint(out, compiler, scope, depth+2);
2761  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%s end bool exp\n"), spaces);
2762  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%s begin then\n"), spaces);
2763  list[1]->debugPrint(out, compiler, scope, depth+2);
2764  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%s end then\n"), spaces);
2765  if(list.count == 3){
2766  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%s begin else\n"), spaces);
2767  list[2]->debugPrint(out, compiler, scope, depth+2);
2768  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%s end else\n"), spaces);
2769  }
2770  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%send if ret values %d\n"), spaces, ret_values);
2771  break;
2772 
2773  case EXP_TYPE_QUESTION:
2774  OS_ASSERT(list.count == 3);
2775  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%sbegin question\n"), spaces);
2776  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%s begin bool exp\n"), spaces);
2777  list[0]->debugPrint(out, compiler, scope, depth+2);
2778  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%s end bool exp\n"), spaces);
2779  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%s begin then value\n"), spaces);
2780  list[1]->debugPrint(out, compiler, scope, depth+2);
2781  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%s end then value\n"), spaces);
2782  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%s begin else value\n"), spaces);
2783  list[2]->debugPrint(out, compiler, scope, depth+2);
2784  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%s end else value\n"), spaces);
2785  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%send question ret values %d\n"), spaces, ret_values);
2786  break;
2787 
2788  case EXP_TYPE_TRY_CATCH:
2789  OS_ASSERT(list.count == 2);
2790  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%sbegin try catch\n"), spaces);
2791  list[0]->debugPrint(out, compiler, scope, depth+1);
2792  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%scatch\n"), spaces);
2793  list[1]->debugPrint(out, compiler, scope, depth+1);
2794  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%send try catch\n"), spaces);
2795  break;
2796 
2797  case EXP_TYPE_THROW:
2798  OS_ASSERT(list.count == 1);
2799  list[0]->debugPrint(out, compiler, scope, depth);
2800  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%sthrow: %s (%d)\n"), spaces,
2801  getSlotStr(compiler, scope, slots.a).toChar(), slots.a);
2802  break;
2803 
2804  case EXP_TYPE_PARAMS:
2805  for(i = 0; i < list.count; i++){
2806  list[i]->debugPrint(out, compiler, scope, depth);
2807  }
2808  break;
2809 
2810  case EXP_TYPE_ARRAY:
2811  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%snew array %d: %s (%d)\n"), spaces, list.count,
2812  getSlotStr(compiler, scope, slots.a).toChar(), slots.a);
2813  for(i = 0; i < list.count; i++){
2814  list[i]->debugPrint(out, compiler, scope, depth);
2815  }
2816  break;
2817 
2818  case EXP_TYPE_OBJECT:
2819  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%snew object %d: %s (%d)\n"), spaces, list.count,
2820  getSlotStr(compiler, scope, slots.a).toChar(), slots.a);
2821  for(i = 0; i < list.count; i++){
2822  list[i]->debugPrint(out, compiler, scope, depth);
2823  }
2824  break;
2825 
2826  case EXP_TYPE_FUNCTION:
2827  {
2828  Scope * scope = dynamic_cast<Scope*>(this);
2829  OS_ASSERT(scope);
2830  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%sbegin function\n"), spaces);
2831  if(scope->num_locals > 0){
2832  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%s begin locals %d, stack %d\n"), spaces, scope->num_locals, scope->stack_size);
2833  for(i = 0; i < scope->locals.count; i++){
2834  if(scope->locals[i].name == allocator->core->strings->var_temp_prefix){
2835  continue;
2836  }
2837  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%s %d %s%s%s\n"), spaces,
2838  scope->locals[i].index,
2839  scope->locals[i].name.toChar(),
2840  i < scope->num_params ? OS_TEXT(" (param)") : OS_TEXT(""),
2841  scope->locals[i].upvalue ? OS_TEXT(" (upvalue)") : OS_TEXT("")
2842  );
2843  }
2844  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%s end locals\n"), spaces);
2845  }
2846  for(i = 0; i < list.count; i++){
2847  if(i > 0){
2848  out += OS_TEXT("\n");
2849  }
2850  list[i]->debugPrint(out, compiler, scope, depth+1);
2851  }
2852  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%send function: %s (%d), index %d\n"), spaces,
2853  scope->function->parent ? scope->function->parent->getSlotStr(compiler, scope->function->parent, slots.a).toChar() : OS_TEXT("{main}"),
2854  slots.a, slots.b);
2855  break;
2856  }
2857 
2858  case EXP_TYPE_SCOPE:
2859  case EXP_TYPE_LOOP_SCOPE:
2860  case EXP_TYPE_FOR_LOOP_SCOPE:
2861  case EXP_TYPE_SWITCH_SCOPE:
2862  {
2863  Scope * scope = dynamic_cast<Scope*>(this);
2864  OS_ASSERT(scope);
2865  exp_name = OS::Core::Compiler::getExpName(type);
2866  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%sbegin %s\n"), spaces, exp_name);
2867  if(scope->locals.count > 0){
2868  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%s begin locals %d\n"), spaces, scope->locals.count);
2869  for(i = 0; i < scope->locals.count; i++){
2870  if(scope->locals[i].name == allocator->core->strings->var_temp_prefix){
2871  continue;
2872  }
2873  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%s %d %s%s%s\n"), spaces,
2874  scope->locals[i].index,
2875  scope->locals[i].name.toChar(),
2876  i < scope->num_params ? OS_TEXT(" (param)") : OS_TEXT(""),
2877  scope->locals[i].upvalue ? OS_TEXT(" (upvalue)") : OS_TEXT("")
2878  );
2879  }
2880  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%s end locals\n"), spaces);
2881  }
2882  for(i = 0; i < list.count; i++){
2883  if(i > 0){
2884  out += OS_TEXT("\n");
2885  }
2886  list[i]->debugPrint(out, compiler, scope, depth+1);
2887  }
2888  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%send %s ret values %d\n"), spaces, exp_name, ret_values);
2889  break;
2890  }
2891 
2892  case EXP_TYPE_RETURN:
2893  for(i = 0; i < list.count; i++){
2894  list[i]->debugPrint(out, compiler, scope, depth+1);
2895  }
2896  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%sreturn: %s (%d), count %d\n"), spaces,
2897  slots.a ? getSlotStr(compiler, scope, slots.a).toChar() : OS_TEXT("{main}"),
2898  slots.a, slots.b);
2899  break;
2900 
2901  case EXP_TYPE_GET_UPVALUE:
2902  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%sget upvalue: %s (%d) = %s (%d %d)\n"), spaces,
2903  getSlotStr(compiler, scope, slots.a).toChar(), slots.a,
2904  getSlotStr(compiler, scope, slots.b, slots.c).toChar(), slots.b, slots.c);
2905  break;
2906 
2907  case EXP_TYPE_SET_UPVALUE:
2908  case EXP_TYPE_SET_UPVALUE_NO_POP:

2910  if(list.count == 1){
2911  list[0]->debugPrint(out, compiler, scope, depth);
2912  }
2913  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%sset upvalue: %s (%d %d) = %s (%d)\n"), spaces,
2914  getSlotStr(compiler, scope, slots.a, slots.c).toChar(), slots.a, slots.c,
2915  getSlotStr(compiler, scope, slots.b).toChar(), slots.b);
2916  break;
2917

2919  case EXP_TYPE_GET_XCONST:

2921  list[i]->debugPrint(out, compiler, scope, depth);
2922  }
2923  if(slots.a != slots.b && slots.a){
2924  OS_ASSERT(slots.a > 0);
2925  exp_name = OS::Core::Compiler::getExpName(type);
2926  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%s%s: %s (%d) = %s (%d)\n"), spaces, exp_name,

2928  getSlotStr(compiler, scope, slots.b).toChar(), slots.b);
2929  }else if(slots.a){

2932  }
2933  break;

2937  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%sbreak\n"), spaces);
2938  break;

2942  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%scontinue\n"), spaces);
2943  break;

2954  list[1]->debugPrint(out, compiler, scope, depth+1);

3158 int OS::Core::Compiler::cacheString(Table * strings_table, Vector<String>& strings, const String& str)
3159 {
3160  Value index(str);
3161  Property * prop = strings_table->get(index, OS_VALUE_TYPE(index));
3162  if(prop){
3163  OS_ASSERT(OS_IS_VALUE_NUMBER(prop->value));
3164  int i; OS_NUMBER_TO_INT(i, OS_VALUE_NUMBER(prop->value));
3165  return i;
3166  }
3167  allocator->core->addTableProperty(strings_table, index, Value(strings_table->count));
3168  allocator->vectorAddItem(strings, str OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
3169  OS_ASSERT(strings_table->count == strings.count);
3170  return strings_table->count-1;
3171 }

3178 int OS::Core::Compiler::cacheNumber(OS_NUMBER num)
3179 {
3180  Value index(num);
3181  Property * prop = prog_numbers_table->get(index, OS_VALUE_TYPE(index));
3182  if(prop){
3183  OS_ASSERT(OS_IS_VALUE_NUMBER(prop->value));
3184  int i; OS_NUMBER_TO_INT(i, OS_VALUE_NUMBER(prop->value));
3185  return i;
3186  }
3187  allocator->core->addTableProperty(prog_numbers_table, index, Value(prog_numbers_table->count));
3188  allocator->vectorAddItem(prog_numbers, num OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
3189  OS_ASSERT(prog_numbers_table->count == prog_numbers.count);
3190  return prog_numbers_table->count-1;
3191 }

3199 void OS::Core::Compiler::writeDebugInfo(Expression * exp)
3200 {
3201  if(allocator->core->settings.create_debug_info){
3202  int opcode_pos = getOpcodePos();
3203  while(opcode_pos > prog_debug_info.count){
3204  allocator->vectorAddItem(prog_debug_info, DebugInfoItem(0, 0) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
3205  }
3206  OS_ASSERT(opcode_pos == prog_debug_info.count || opcode_pos+1 == prog_debug_info.count);
3207  DebugInfoItem item(exp->token->line + 1, exp->token->pos + 1);
3208  if(opcode_pos+1 == prog_debug_info.count){
3209  prog_debug_info.lastElement() = item;
3210  return;
3211  }
3212  allocator->vectorAddItem(prog_debug_info, item OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
3213  }
3214 }

3224 void OS::Core::Compiler::fixJumpOpcode(int offs, int pos)
3225 {
3226  Instruction instruction = prog_opcodes[pos];
3227 #ifdef OS_DEBUG
3228  OpcodeType opcode = (OpcodeType)OS_GET_OPCODE_TYPE(instruction);
3229  OS_ASSERT(opcode == OP_JUMP);
3230 #endif

3234 
3235 bool OS::Core::Compiler::writeOpcodes(Scope * scope, ExpressionList& list, bool optimization_enabled)
3236 {
3237  prog_optimize_offs = prog_opcodes.count;
3238  for(int i = 0; i < list.count; i++){
3239  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, list[i])){
3240  return false;
3241  }
3242  if(optimization_enabled && prog_opcodes.count - prog_optimize_offs >= 2){
3243  Instruction prev = prog_opcodes[prog_opcodes.count - 2];
3244  if(OS_GET_OPCODE_TYPE(prev) == OP_MOVE){
3245  Instruction cur = prog_opcodes[prog_opcodes.count - 1];
3246  if(OS_GET_OPCODE_TYPE(cur) == OP_MOVE){
3247  int prev_a = OS_GETARG_A(prev);
3248  int cur_a = OS_GETARG_A(cur);
3249  if(prev_a == OS_GETARG_B(cur) && cur_a == OS_GETARG_B(prev)){
3250  /*
3251  this optimization is incorrect for following code
3252  f = n || f
3253 
3254  OS_SETARG_B(cur, cur_a); // use value
3255  prog_opcodes[prog_opcodes.count - 1] = cur;
3256  start = prog_opcodes.count + 1;
3257  */
3258  }else if(prev_a+1 == cur_a){
3259  Instruction instruction = OS_FROM_OPCODE_TYPE(OP_MOVE2);
3260  OS_SETARG_A(instruction, prev_a);
3261  int prev_b = OS_GETARG_B(prev & ~OS_OPCODE_CONST_B);
3262  OS_SETARG_B(instruction, prev_b);
3263  int cur_b = OS_GETARG_B(cur & ~OS_OPCODE_CONST_B);
3264  OS_SETARG_C(instruction, cur_b);
3265  if(prev & OS_OPCODE_CONST_B){
3266  instruction |= OS_OPCODE_CONST_B;
3267  }
3268  if(cur & OS_OPCODE_CONST_B){
3269  instruction |= OS_OPCODE_CONST_C;
3270  }
3271  prog_opcodes[prog_opcodes.count - 2] = instruction;
3272  prog_optimize_offs = --prog_opcodes.count;
3273  }
3274  }
3275  }
3276  }
3277  }
3278  return true;
3279 }

3290  return i;

3297 
3298 int OS::Core::Compiler::writeOpcodeABC(OpcodeType p_opcode, int a, int b, int c)
3299 {
3300  int opcode = OS_FROM_OPCODE_TYPE(p_opcode);
3301  OS_ASSERT(a >= 0 && a <= OS_MAXARG_A);
3302  if(b < 0){
3303  b = -1-b;
3304  OS_ASSERT(b <= OS_MAXARG_B);
3305  opcode |= OS_OPCODE_CONST_B;
3306  }else{
3307  OS_ASSERT(b <= OS_MAXARG_B);
3308  }
3309  if(c < 0){
3310  c = -1-c;
3311  OS_ASSERT(c <= OS_MAXARG_C);
3312  opcode |= OS_OPCODE_CONST_C;
3313  }else{
3314  OS_ASSERT(c <= OS_MAXARG_C);
3315  }
3316  return writeOpcode(OS_OPCODE_ABC(opcode, a, b, c));
3317 }
3318 
3319 int OS::Core::Compiler::writeOpcodeABx(OpcodeType opcode, int a, int b)
3320 {
3321  OS_ASSERT(a >= 0 && a <= OS_MAXARG_A);
3322  OS_ASSERT(b >= 0 && b <= OS_MAXARG_Bx);
3323  Instruction instruction = OS_FROM_OPCODE_TYPE(opcode);
3324  return writeOpcode(OS_OPCODE_ABx(instruction, a, b));
3325 }

3331 
3332 bool OS::Core::Compiler::writeOpcodes(Scope * scope, Expression * exp)
3333 {
3334 #if 1
3335  int i;
3336  switch(exp->type){
3337  default:
3338  {
3339  ExpressionType exp_type = exp->type;
3340  OS_ASSERT(false); (void)exp_type;
3341  return false;
3342  }
3343 
3344  case EXP_TYPE_NOP:
3345  case EXP_TYPE_NEW_LOCAL_VAR:
3346  case EXP_TYPE_VALUE:
3347  case EXP_TYPE_CODE_LIST:
3348  case EXP_TYPE_PARAMS:
3349  case EXP_TYPE_POP_VALUE:
3350  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp->list, exp->type == EXP_TYPE_CODE_LIST || exp->type == EXP_TYPE_PARAMS)){
3351  return false;
3352  }
3353  break;
3354 
3355  case EXP_TYPE_FUNCTION:
3356  {
3357  Scope * scope = dynamic_cast<Scope*>(exp);
3358  OS_ASSERT(scope);
3359  writeDebugInfo(exp);
3360 
3361  int prog_func_index = scope->prog_func_index; // prog_functions.indexOf(scope);
3362  OS_ASSERT(prog_func_index >= 0);
3363 
3364  int pos = writeOpcodeABC(OP_NEW_FUNCTION, exp->slots.a, prog_func_index, 0); (void)pos;
3365 
3366  allocator->vectorReserveCapacity(scope->locals_compiled, scope->num_locals OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
3367  scope->locals_compiled.count = scope->num_locals;
3368 
3369  scope->opcodes_pos = getOpcodePos();
3370  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp->list, true)){
3371  return false;
3372  }
3373  writeOpcodeABC(OP_RETURN, 0, 0, 1); // return auto
3374  scope->opcodes_size = getOpcodePos() - scope->opcodes_pos;
3375 
3376  for(i = 0; i < scope->locals.count; i++){
3377  Scope::LocalVar& var = scope->locals[i];
3378  // OS_ASSERT(i == var.index);
3379  Scope::LocalVarCompiled& var_scope = scope->locals_compiled[var.index];
3380  var_scope.cached_name_index = cacheString(var.name);
3381  var_scope.start_code_pos = scope->opcodes_pos;
3382  var_scope.end_code_pos = getOpcodePos();
3383  var_scope.upvalue = var.upvalue;
3384  }
3385  break;
3386  }
3387 
3388  case EXP_TYPE_SCOPE:
3389  case EXP_TYPE_LOOP_SCOPE:
3390  case EXP_TYPE_FOR_LOOP_SCOPE:
3391  {
3392  Scope * scope = dynamic_cast<Scope*>(exp);
3393  OS_ASSERT(scope);
3394  int start_code_pos = getOpcodePos(), start_for_post = 0;
3395  if(exp->type == EXP_TYPE_FOR_LOOP_SCOPE){
3396  for(int i = 0; i < exp->list.count; i++){
3397  if(i == exp->list.count-1){
3398  start_for_post = getOpcodePos();
3399  }
3400  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp->list[i])){
3401  return false;
3402  }
3403  }
3404  }else if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp->list, true)){
3405  return false;
3406  }
3407  if(exp->type != EXP_TYPE_SCOPE){
3408  writeJumpOpcode(start_code_pos - getOpcodePos() - 2);
3409  scope->fixLoopBreaks(this,
3410  start_for_post ? start_for_post : start_code_pos,
3411  getOpcodePos());
3412  }else{
3413  OS_ASSERT(scope->loop_breaks.count == 0);
3414  }
3415  for(i = 0; i < scope->locals.count; i++){
3416  Scope::LocalVar& var = scope->locals[i];
3417  Scope::LocalVarCompiled& var_scope = scope->function->locals_compiled[var.index];
3418  var_scope.cached_name_index = cacheString(var.name);
3419  var_scope.start_code_pos = start_code_pos;
3420  var_scope.end_code_pos = getOpcodePos();
3421  var_scope.upvalue = var.upvalue;
3422  }
3423  break;
3424  }
3425 
3426  case EXP_TYPE_IF:
3427  case EXP_TYPE_QUESTION:
3428  {
3429  OS_ASSERT(exp->list.count == 2 || exp->list.count == 3);
3430  Expression * exp_compare = exp->list[0];
3431  bool inverse = exp_compare->type == EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_NOT;
3432  // DON'T allow optimize if(!(a > 0)) to if(a <= 0)
3433  if(0 && inverse){
3434  OS_ASSERT(exp_compare->list.count == 1);
3435  switch(exp_compare->list[0]->type){
3436  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_PTR_EQ:
3437  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_PTR_NE:
3438  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_EQ:
3439  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_NE:
3440  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_LE:
3441  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_GREATER:
3442  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_GE:
3443  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_LESS:
3444  exp_compare = exp_compare->list[0];
3445  break;
3446 
3447  default:
3448  OS_ASSERT(exp_compare->slots.a == exp_compare->slots.b);
3449  break;
3450  }
3451  }
3452 
3453  OpcodeType opcode;
3454  OS_ASSERT(exp_compare->slots.a >= scope->function->num_locals);
3455  switch(exp_compare->type){
3456  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_PTR_EQ:
3457  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_PTR_NE:
3458  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp_compare->list, true)){
3459  return false;
3460  }
3461  opcode = OP_LOGIC_PTR_EQ;
3462  inverse ^= exp_compare->type != EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_PTR_EQ;
3463  break;
3464 
3465  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_EQ:
3466  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_NE:
3467  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp_compare->list, true)){
3468  return false;
3469  }
3470  opcode = OP_LOGIC_EQ;
3471  if(exp_compare->list.count == 2){
3472  if(exp_compare->list[0]->local_var.type == CVT_NUMBER
3473  && exp_compare->list[1]->local_var.type == CVT_NUMBER)
3474  {
3475  opcode = OP_NUMBER_LOGIC_EQ;
3476  }
3477  }else{
3478  // int i = 0;
3479  }
3480  inverse ^= exp_compare->type != EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_EQ;
3481  break;
3482 
3483  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_LE:
3484  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_GREATER:
3485  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp_compare->list, true)){
3486  return false;
3487  }
3488  opcode = OP_LOGIC_GREATER;
3489  if(exp_compare->list.count == 2){
3490  if(exp_compare->list[0]->local_var.type == CVT_NUMBER
3491  && exp_compare->list[1]->local_var.type == CVT_NUMBER)
3492  {
3493  opcode = OP_NUMBER_LOGIC_GREATER;
3494  }
3495  }else{
3496  // int i = 0;
3497  }
3498  inverse ^= exp_compare->type != EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_GREATER;
3499  break;
3500 
3501  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_GE:
3502  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_LESS:
3503  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp_compare->list, true)){
3504  return false;
3505  }
3506  opcode = OP_LOGIC_GE;
3507  if(exp_compare->list.count == 2){
3508  if(exp_compare->list[0]->local_var.type == CVT_NUMBER
3509  && exp_compare->list[1]->local_var.type == CVT_NUMBER)
3510  {
3511  opcode = OP_NUMBER_LOGIC_GE;
3512  }
3513  }else{
3514  // int i = 0;
3515  }
3516  inverse ^= exp_compare->type != EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_GE;
3517  break;
3518 
3519  default:
3520  if(exp_compare->type == EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_NOT || exp_compare->type == EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_BOOL){
3521  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp_compare->list)){
3522  return false;
3523  }
3524  }else{
3525  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp_compare)){
3526  return false;
3527  }
3528  }
3529  opcode = OP_LOGIC_BOOL;
3530  break;
3531  }
3532  writeDebugInfo(exp);
3533 
3534  writeOpcodeABC(opcode, exp_compare->slots.a, inverse, 1);
3535  int if_jump_pos = writeOpcode(OP_JUMP);
3536 
3537  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp->list[1])){
3538  return false;
3539  }
3540  int if_jump_to = prog_optimize_offs = getOpcodePos();
3541  if(exp->list.count == 3){ // && exp->list[2]->list.count > 0){
3542  int jump_pos = writeOpcode(OP_JUMP);
3543 
3544  if_jump_to = getOpcodePos();
3545  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp->list[2])){
3546  return false;
3547  }
3548  prog_optimize_offs = getOpcodePos();
3549  fixJumpOpcode(getOpcodePos() - jump_pos - 1, jump_pos);
3550  }
3551  fixJumpOpcode(if_jump_to - if_jump_pos - 1, if_jump_pos);
3552  break;
3553  }
3554 
3555  case EXP_TYPE_TRY_CATCH:
3556  {
3557  OS_ASSERT(exp->list.count == 2);
3558  OS_ASSERT(exp->list[1]->type == EXP_TYPE_SCOPE);
3559  int op_try_start = prog_opcodes.count;
3560  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp->list[0])){
3561  return false;
3562  }
3563  // writeDebugInfo(exp);
3564  int op_jump_pos = writeOpcode(OP_JUMP);
3565  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp->list[1])){
3566  return false;
3567  }
3568 
3569  int op_jump_to = getOpcodePos();
3570  fixJumpOpcode(op_jump_to - op_jump_pos - 1, op_jump_pos);
3571  OS_ASSERT(dynamic_cast<Scope*>(exp->list[1]));
3572  scope->function->addTryBlock(op_try_start, op_jump_pos + 1, (Scope*)exp->list[1]);
3573  break;
3574  }
3575 
3576  case EXP_TYPE_THROW:
3577  OS_ASSERT(exp->list.count == 1);
3578  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp->list)){
3579  return false;
3580  }
3581  writeDebugInfo(exp);
3582  writeOpcodeABC(OP_MULTI, exp->slots.a, 0, OP_MULTI_THROW);
3583  break;
3584 
3585  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_AND: // &&
3586  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_OR: // ||
3587  {
3588  OS_ASSERT(exp->list.count == 2);
3589  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp->list[0])){
3590  return false;
3591  }
3592  writeDebugInfo(exp);
3593 
3594  // Expression * exp_compare = exp->list[0];
3595  bool inverse = exp->type == EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_OR;
3596  writeOpcodeABC(OP_LOGIC_BOOL, exp->slots.a, inverse, 1);
3597  int op_jump_pos = writeOpcode(OP_JUMP);
3598 
3599  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp->list[1])){
3600  return false;
3601  }
3602 
3603  int op_jump_to = getOpcodePos();
3604  fixJumpOpcode(op_jump_to - op_jump_pos - 1, op_jump_pos);
3605  break;
3606  }
3607 
3608  case EXP_TYPE_ARRAY:
3609  case EXP_TYPE_OBJECT:
3610  writeDebugInfo(exp);
3611  writeOpcodeABC(exp->type == EXP_TYPE_OBJECT ? OP_NEW_OBJECT : OP_NEW_ARRAY, exp->slots.a, exp->list.count);
3612  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp->list)){
3613  return false;
3614  }
3615  break;
3616 
3617  case EXP_TYPE_GET_ARGUMENTS:
3618  case EXP_TYPE_GET_REST_ARGUMENTS:
3619  OS_ASSERT(exp->list.count == 0);
3620  writeDebugInfo(exp);
3621  writeOpcodeABC(OP_MULTI, exp->slots.a, 0, exp->type == EXP_TYPE_GET_ARGUMENTS ? OP_MULTI_GET_ARGUMENTS : OP_MULTI_GET_REST_ARGUMENTS);
3622  break;
3623 
3624  case EXP_TYPE_SUPER:
3625  OS_ASSERT(exp->list.count == 0);
3626  writeDebugInfo(exp);
3627  writeOpcodeABC(OP_MULTI, exp->slots.a, 0, OP_MULTI_SUPER);
3628  break;
3629 
3630  case EXP_TYPE_DEBUGGER:
3631  OS_ASSERT(exp->list.count == 0);
3632  writeDebugInfo(exp);
3633  writeOpcodeABC(OP_MULTI, 0, 0, OP_MULTI_DEBUGGER);
3634  break;
3635 
3636  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_BOOL:
3637  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_NOT:
3638  OS_ASSERT(exp->list.count == 1);
3639  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp->list)){
3640  return false;
3641  }
3642  writeDebugInfo(exp);
3643  writeOpcodeABC(OP_LOGIC_BOOL, exp->slots.a, exp->type == EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_NOT, 0);
3644  break;
3645 
3646  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_PTR_EQ:
3647  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_PTR_NE:
3648  OS_ASSERT(exp->list.count == 2);
3649  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp->list, true)){
3650  return false;
3651  }
3652  writeDebugInfo(exp);
3653  writeOpcodeABC(OP_LOGIC_PTR_EQ, exp->slots.a, exp->type == EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_PTR_NE, 0);
3654  break;
3655 
3656  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_EQ:
3657  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_NE:
3658  OS_ASSERT(exp->list.count == 2);
3659  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp->list, true)){
3660  return false;
3661  }
3662  writeDebugInfo(exp);
3663  writeOpcodeABC(OP_LOGIC_EQ, exp->slots.a, exp->type == EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_NE, 0);
3664  break;
3665 
3666  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_LE:
3667  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_GREATER:
3668  OS_ASSERT(exp->list.count == 2);
3669  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp->list, true)){
3670  return false;
3671  }
3672  writeDebugInfo(exp);
3673  writeOpcodeABC(OP_LOGIC_GREATER, exp->slots.a, exp->type == EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_LE, 0);
3674  break;
3675 
3676  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_GE:
3677  case EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_LESS:
3678  OS_ASSERT(exp->list.count == 2);
3679  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp->list, true)){
3680  return false;
3681  }
3682  writeDebugInfo(exp);
3683  writeOpcodeABC(OP_LOGIC_GE, exp->slots.a, exp->type == EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_LESS, 0);
3684  break;
3685 
3686  case EXP_TYPE_SUPER_CALL:
3687  case EXP_TYPE_CALL:
3688  case EXP_TYPE_CALL_AUTO_PARAM:
3689  case EXP_TYPE_CALL_METHOD:
3690  case EXP_TYPE_INIT_ITER:
3691  case EXP_TYPE_TAIL_CALL:
3692  case EXP_TYPE_TAIL_CALL_METHOD:
3693 
3694  case EXP_TYPE_GET_PROPERTY:
3695  case EXP_TYPE_SET_PROPERTY:
3696  case EXP_TYPE_SET_PROPERTY_NO_POP:
3697  case EXP_TYPE_INIT_PROPERTY:
3698 
3699  case EXP_TYPE_GET_UPVALUE:
3700  case EXP_TYPE_SET_UPVALUE:
3701  case EXP_TYPE_SET_UPVALUE_NO_POP:
3702 
3703  case EXP_TYPE_MOVE:
3704  case EXP_TYPE_RETURN:
3705 
3706  case EXP_TYPE_BIT_NOT:
3707  case EXP_TYPE_PLUS:
3708  case EXP_TYPE_MINUS:
3709 
3710  case EXP_TYPE_BIT_AND:
3711  case EXP_TYPE_BIT_OR:
3712  case EXP_TYPE_BIT_XOR:
3713 
3714  // case EXP_TYPE_CONCAT:
3715  case EXP_TYPE_COMPARE:
3716  case EXP_TYPE_ADD:
3717  case EXP_TYPE_SUB:
3718  case EXP_TYPE_MUL:
3719  case EXP_TYPE_DIV:
3720  case EXP_TYPE_MOD:
3721  case EXP_TYPE_LSHIFT:
3722  case EXP_TYPE_RSHIFT:
3723  case EXP_TYPE_POW:
3724  {
3725  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp->list)){
3726  return false;
3727  }
3728  writeDebugInfo(exp);
3729  OpcodeType opcode = Program::getOpcodeType(exp->type, exp->local_var.type);
3730  switch(opcode){
3731  case OP_NUMBER_ADD:
3732  if(exp->slots.b >= 0 && exp->slots.c < 0){
3733  opcode = OP_NUMBER_ADD_LC;
3734  }else if(exp->slots.b >= 0 && exp->slots.c >= 0){
3735  opcode = OP_NUMBER_ADD_LL;
3736  }
3737  break;
3738 
3739  case OP_NUMBER_SUB:
3740  if(exp->slots.b >= 0 && exp->slots.c < 0){
3741  opcode = OP_NUMBER_SUB_LC;
3742  }else if(exp->slots.b >= 0 && exp->slots.c >= 0){
3743  opcode = OP_NUMBER_SUB_LL;
3744  }
3745  break;
3746 
3747  }
3748  writeOpcodeABC(opcode, exp->slots.a, exp->slots.b, exp->slots.c);
3749  break;
3750  }
3751 
3752  case EXP_TYPE_GET_XCONST:
3753  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp->list)){
3754  return false;
3755  }
3756  writeDebugInfo(exp);
3757  OS_ASSERT(exp->slots.b < 0);
3758  writeOpcodeABx(OP_GET_XCONST, exp->slots.a, -1-exp->slots.b);
3759  break;
3760 
3761  case EXP_TYPE_BREAK:
3762  case EXP_TYPE_CONTINUE:
3763  OS_ASSERT(exp->list.count == 0);
3764  writeDebugInfo(exp);
3765  if(!scope->addLoopBreak(writeOpcode(OP_JUMP), exp->type == EXP_TYPE_BREAK ? Scope::LOOP_BREAK : Scope::LOOP_CONTINUE)){
3766  setError(ERROR_EXPECT_LOOP_SCOPE, exp->token);
3767  return false;
3768  }
3769  break;
3770 
3771  case EXP_TYPE_SWITCH_SCOPE:
3772  {
3773  Scope * scope = dynamic_cast<Scope*>(exp);
3774  OS_ASSERT(scope);
3775  int start_code_pos = getOpcodePos();
3776  if(!writeOpcodes(scope, exp->list, true)){
3777  return false;
3778  }
3779  for(i = 0; i < scope->locals.count; i++){
3780  Scope::LocalVar& var = scope->locals[i];
3781  Scope::LocalVarCompiled& var_scope = scope->function->locals_compiled[var.index];
3782  var_scope.cached_name_index = cacheString(var.name);
3783  var_scope.start_code_pos = start_code_pos;
3784  var_scope.end_code_pos = getOpcodePos();
3785  var_scope.upvalue = var.upvalue;
3786  }
3787  // look for "default" jumper & if it is not completely initialized
3788  // (from/to values are empty) - set "to" value to end of block
3789  for(int i = 0; i < scope->case_labels.count; i++){
3790  Scope::SwitchCaseLabel& label = scope->case_labels[i];
3791  if(!label.exp && !label.to_pos)
3792  scope->setCaseLabelPos(label.key, getOpcodePos(), this);
3793  }
3794  scope->fixLoopBreaks(this, start_code_pos, getOpcodePos());
3795  break;
3796  }
3797  case EXP_TYPE_CASE:
3798  case EXP_TYPE_CASE_DEFAULT:
3799  {
3800  Scope * switch_case = scope->getSwitchScope();
3801  if(switch_case) // save address of case label
3802  switch_case->setCaseLabelPos(exp->token, getOpcodePos(), this);
3803  break;
3804  }
3805  case EXP_TYPE_CASE_JUMP:
3806  {
3807  if(scope->type == EXP_TYPE_SWITCH_SCOPE){ // CASE_JUMP expression must be in SWITCH scope
3808  int pos = getOpcodePos();
3809  writeJumpOpcode(0); // save address of JUMP instruction
3810  scope->setCaseLabelJump(exp->token, pos, this);
3811  }
3812  break;
3813  }
3814 
3815  }
3816 #endif
3817  return true;
3818 }

3822 OS::Core::Compiler::Scope::Scope(Scope * p_parent, ExpressionType type, TokenData * token): Expression(type, token)
3823 {
3824  OS_ASSERT(type == EXP_TYPE_FUNCTION || type == EXP_TYPE_SCOPE || type == EXP_TYPE_LOOP_SCOPE || type == EXP_TYPE_FOR_LOOP_SCOPE || type == EXP_TYPE_SWITCH_SCOPE);
3825  parent = p_parent;
3826  function = type == EXP_TYPE_FUNCTION ? this : parent->function;
3827  num_params = 0;
3828  num_locals = 0;
3829  max_up_count = 0;
3830  func_depth = 0;
3831  func_index = 0;
3832  num_local_funcs = 0;
3833  prog_func_index = -1;
3834  parser_started = false;
3835  stack_size = 0;
3836  stack_cur_size = 0;
3837 }

3863 bool OS::Core::Compiler::Scope::addLoopBreak(int pos, ELoopBreakType type)
3864 {
3865  Scope * scope = this;
3866  for(; scope; scope = scope->parent){
3867  if(scope->type == EXP_TYPE_LOOP_SCOPE || scope->type == EXP_TYPE_FOR_LOOP_SCOPE){
3868  break;
3869  }
3870  if(scope->type == EXP_TYPE_SWITCH_SCOPE){
3871  if(type == LOOP_CONTINUE){
3872  continue; // don't break, search loop scope
3873  }
3874  break;
3875  }
3876  if(scope->type != EXP_TYPE_SCOPE){
3877  return false;
3878  }
3879  }
3880  if(!scope){
3881  return false;
3882  }
3883  LoopBreak loop_break;
3884  loop_break.pos = pos;
3885  loop_break.type = type;
3886  getAllocator()->vectorAddItem(scope->loop_breaks, loop_break OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
3887  return true;
3888 }

3890 bool OS::Core::Compiler::Scope::addCaseLabel(TokenData * key, Expression * exp)
3891 {
3892  OS_ASSERT(!exp || exp->token == key);
3893  Scope * scope = this;
3894  if(scope && type == EXP_TYPE_SWITCH_SCOPE){
3895 #ifdef OS_DEBUG
3896  for(int i = 0; i < case_labels.count; i++)
3897  if(case_labels[i].key == key){
3898  OS_ASSERT(false);
3899  }
3900 #endif
3901  SwitchCaseLabel label;
3902  label.key = key;
3903  label.exp = exp;
3904  label.jump_exp = NULL;
3905  label.from_pos = 0;
3906  label.to_pos = 0;
3907  getAllocator()->vectorAddItem(scope->case_labels, label OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
3908  return true;
3909  }
3910 
3911  return false;
3912 }

3925 bool OS::Core::Compiler::Scope::setCaseLabelPos(TokenData * key, int pos, Compiler* cmp)
3926 {
3927  for(int i = 0; i < case_labels.count; i++){
3928  SwitchCaseLabel& sw = case_labels[i];
3929  if(sw.key == key){
3930  sw.to_pos = pos;
3931  if(sw.to_pos && sw.from_pos){
3932  cmp->fixJumpOpcode(sw.to_pos - sw.from_pos - 1, sw.from_pos);
3933  }
3934  return true;
3935  }
3936  }
3937  return false;
3938 }

3940 bool OS::Core::Compiler::Scope::setCaseLabelJump(TokenData * key, int pos, Compiler* cmp)
3941 {
3942  for(int i = 0; i < case_labels.count; i++){
3943  SwitchCaseLabel& sw = case_labels[i];
3944  if(sw.key == key){
3945  sw.from_pos = pos;
3946  if(sw.to_pos && sw.from_pos){
3947  cmp->fixJumpOpcode(sw.to_pos - sw.from_pos - 1, sw.from_pos);
3948  }
3949  return true;
3950  }
3951  }
3952  return false;

3958  return parent;

3962 OS::Core::Compiler::Scope* OS::Core::Compiler::Scope::findSwitchScope()
3963 {
3964  for(Scope * scope = this; scope; scope = scope->parent){
3965  if(scope->type == EXP_TYPE_SWITCH_SCOPE){
3966  return scope;
3967  }
3968  if(scope->type != EXP_TYPE_SCOPE){
3969  break;
3970  }
3971  }
3972  return NULL;
3973 }
3974 
3975 void OS::Core::Compiler::Scope::fixLoopBreaks(Compiler * compiler, int scope_start_pos, int scope_end_pos)
3976 {
3977  for(int i = 0; i < loop_breaks.count; i++){
3978  LoopBreak& loop_break = loop_breaks[i];
3979  if(loop_break.type == LOOP_BREAK){
3980  int offs = scope_end_pos - loop_break.pos - 1;
3981  compiler->fixJumpOpcode(offs, loop_break.pos);
3982  }else{
3983  int offs = scope_start_pos - loop_break.pos - 1;
3984  compiler->fixJumpOpcode(offs, loop_break.pos);
3985  }
3986  }
3987 }
3988 
3989 OS::Core::Compiler::Scope * OS::Core::Compiler::Scope::findLoopScope()
3990 {
3991  for(Scope * scope = this; scope; scope = scope->parent){
3992  if(scope->type == EXP_TYPE_LOOP_SCOPE || scope->type == EXP_TYPE_FOR_LOOP_SCOPE){
3993  return scope;
3994  }
3995  if(scope->type != EXP_TYPE_SCOPE && scope->type != EXP_TYPE_SWITCH_SCOPE){
3996  break;
3997  }
3998  }
3999  return NULL;
4000 }

4002 void OS::Core::Compiler::Scope::addTryBlock(int start, int end, Scope * catch_block)
4003 {
4004  OS_ASSERT(catch_block->local_var.index > 0);
4005  OS_ASSERT(catch_block->local_var.scope_type == LOCAL_GENERIC);
4006  OS_ASSERT(catch_block->local_var.up_count == 0);
4007  TryBlock t;
4008  t.start_code_pos = start;
4009  t.end_code_pos = end;
4010  t.catch_var_index = catch_block->local_var.index;
4011  getAllocator()->vectorAddItem(try_blocks, t OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
4012 }

4034 void OS::Core::Compiler::Scope::addLocalVar(const String& name, ECompiledValueType type)
4035 {

4037  OS_ASSERT(function->stack_cur_size == function->num_locals);

4040  allocator->vectorAddItem(locals, local_var OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
4041  function->stack_size = function->stack_cur_size = ++function->num_locals;
4042 }

4047  local_var.up_count = 0;

4053 int OS::Core::Compiler::Scope::allocTempVar()
4054 {

4056  OS_ASSERT(function->stack_cur_size == function->stack_size+1);
4057  function->stack_size = function->stack_cur_size;
4058  }
4059  return function->stack_cur_size-1;

4065  OS_ASSERT(function->stack_cur_size >= function->num_locals);

4095 OS::Core::Compiler::~Compiler()
4096 {

4099  }
4100  if(prog_numbers_table){
4101  allocator->core->deleteTable(prog_numbers_table);
4102  prog_numbers_table = NULL;
4103  }
4104  if(prog_strings_table){
4105  allocator->core->deleteTable(prog_strings_table);
4106  prog_strings_table = NULL;
4107  }
4108  allocator->vectorClear(prog_numbers);
4109  allocator->vectorClear(prog_strings);
4110  allocator->vectorClear(prog_functions);
4111  allocator->vectorClear(prog_opcodes);
4112  allocator->vectorClear(prog_debug_info);
