8265 OS::Core::Compiler::Expression * OS::Core::Compiler::expectSwitchExpression(Scope * parent)
8266 {
8267  OS_ASSERT(recent_token && recent_token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_switch);
8268 
8269  Scope * scope = new (malloc(sizeof(Scope) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Scope(parent, EXP_TYPE_SCOPE, recent_token);
8270  if(!expectToken(Tokenizer::BEGIN_BRACKET_BLOCK) || !expectToken()){
8271  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8272  return NULL;
8273  }
8274  Expression * switch_exp = expectSingleExpression(scope, Params().setAllowAutoCall(true).setAllowCall(true).setAllowBinaryOperator(true));
8275  if(!switch_exp){
8276  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8277  return NULL;
8278  }
8279  if(!switch_exp->ret_values){
8280  setError(ERROR_EXPECT_VALUE, switch_exp->token);
8281  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8282  allocator->deleteObj(switch_exp);
8283  return NULL;
8284  }
8285  switch_exp = expectExpressionValues(switch_exp, 1);
8286 
8287  if(recent_token->type != Tokenizer::END_BRACKET_BLOCK){
8288  setError(Tokenizer::END_BRACKET_BLOCK, recent_token);
8289  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8290  allocator->deleteObj(switch_exp);
8291  return NULL;
8292  }
8293  readToken();
8294 
8295  // check for next token is begin of code block ("{")
8296  if(!recent_token || recent_token->type != Tokenizer::BEGIN_CODE_BLOCK){
8297  setError(Tokenizer::END_BRACKET_BLOCK, recent_token);
8298  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8299  allocator->deleteObj(switch_exp);
8300  return NULL;
8301  }
8302  readToken();
8303 
8304  // check for next token is "case" or "default" expression
8305  if(!recent_token || recent_token->type != Tokenizer::NAME ||
8306  (recent_token->str != allocator->core->strings->syntax_case &&
8307  recent_token->str != allocator->core->strings->syntax_default)){
8308  setError(Tokenizer::END_BRACKET_BLOCK, recent_token);
8309  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8310  allocator->deleteObj(switch_exp);
8311  return NULL;
8312  }
8313 
8314  // rollback token paeser to allow build expression for switch scope
8315  ungetToken(); // now recent_token is point -> {
8316 
8317  /* so, logic of building switch/case construction is simple:
8318  build child block as-is, but during build of block all case:/default: elements calls
8319  methos addCaseLabel for parent (current) scope to record case/default expressions,
8320  additionaly added pseudo expression elements EXP_TYPE_CASE/EXP_TYPE_DEFAULT.
8321  such pseudo-elements are used to calculate opcode address.
8322  */
8323 
8324  Scope * switch_scope = new (malloc(sizeof(Scope) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Scope(scope, EXP_TYPE_SWITCH_SCOPE, recent_token);
8325  Expression * body_exp = expectSingleExpression(switch_scope, true, true);
8326  if(!body_exp){
8327  // free case_labels expressions
8328  for(int i = 0; i < scope->case_labels.count; i++)
8329  if(scope->case_labels[i].exp){
8330  allocator->deleteObj(scope->case_labels[i].exp);
8331  scope->case_labels[i].exp = NULL;
8332  }
8333 
8334  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8335  allocator->deleteObj(switch_exp);
8336  allocator->deleteObj(switch_scope);
8337  return NULL;
8338  }
8339 
8340  /*
8341  Generating block header: save switch expression result into local variable, after this for every record in
8342  case_labels vector generate construction like:
8343  if(expression == local_variable) goto 0 // we don't know target address yet, use 0 as default value
8344  original sequence of case block used to aloow developers use optimizations, like most often block
8345  should be first. here is exception: "default" block must be last (it is executed only in case if
8346  all other evaluations failed)
8347  */
8348 
8349  String temp_var_name = String(allocator, OS_TEXT("#switch expression result"));
8350  TokenData * temp_var_token = new (malloc(sizeof(TokenData) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) TokenData(tokenizer->getTextData(), temp_var_name, Tokenizer::NAME, switch_exp->token->line, switch_exp->token->pos);
8351 
8352  Expression * copy_exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_SET_LOCAL_VAR, temp_var_token, switch_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8353  //switch_scope->addLocalVar(temp_var_name, copy_exp->local_var);
8354 
8355  switch_scope->list.add(copy_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8356 
8357  OS_ASSERT(switch_scope->case_labels.count);
8358 
8359  Scope::SwitchCaseLabel * default_label = NULL; // flag if default value exists
8360  for(int i = 0; i < switch_scope->case_labels.count; i++){
8361  Scope::SwitchCaseLabel& case_label = switch_scope->case_labels[i];
8362  Expression * exp = case_label.exp;
8363  if(exp){
8364  OS_ASSERT(exp->ret_values == 1);
8365  OS_ASSERT(exp->token == case_label.key);
8366  OS_ASSERT(!case_label.jump_exp);
8367  Expression * temp_var = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_GET_LOCAL_VAR, temp_var_token);
8368  temp_var->ret_values = 1;
8369 
8370  Expression * equ_exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_PTR_EQ, exp->token, temp_var, exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8371  equ_exp->ret_values = 1;
8372 
8373  // EXP_TYPE_CASE_JUMP expression used because during compilation it record "from" position to case_label element
8374  case_label.jump_exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_CASE_JUMP, case_label.key);
8375  Expression * if_exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_IF, switch_exp->token, equ_exp, case_label.jump_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8376  switch_scope->list.add(if_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8377  }else{
8378  if(default_label){ // TODO: process error: only one default label allowed
8379  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, case_label.key);
8380  temp_var_token->release();
8381  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8382  allocator->deleteObj(switch_exp);
8383  allocator->deleteObj(switch_scope);
8384  return NULL;
8385  }
8386  default_label = &case_label;
8387  }
8388  }
8389 
8390  if(!default_label){
8391  // create default entry of case elements
8392  switch_scope->addCaseLabel(switch_exp->token, NULL); // save label to "switch" scope
8393  Scope::SwitchCaseLabel& case_label = switch_scope->case_labels.lastElement();
8394  OS_ASSERT(case_label.key == switch_exp->token && !case_label.exp);
8395  // write jump expression for default value
8396  case_label.jump_exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_CASE_JUMP, case_label.key);
8397  switch_scope->list.add(case_label.jump_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8398  }else{ // set default jump
8399  Scope::SwitchCaseLabel& case_label = *default_label;
8400  OS_ASSERT(!case_label.exp);
8401  case_label.jump_exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_CASE_JUMP, case_label.key);
8402  switch_scope->list.add(case_label.jump_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8403  }
8404 
8405  temp_var_token->release();
8406 
8407  switch_scope->list.add(body_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8408  scope->list.add(switch_scope OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8409  return scope;
8410 }
8411 
8412 OS::Core::Compiler::Expression * OS::Core::Compiler::expectCaseExpression(Scope * parent)
8413 {
8414  OS_ASSERT(recent_token &&
8415  (recent_token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_case ||
8416  recent_token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_default));
8417 
8418  bool is_default = recent_token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_default;
8419 
8420  if(!parent || !parent->getSwitchScope())
8421  {
8422  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, recent_token);
8423  return NULL;
8424  }
8425 
8426  if(!readToken())
8427  {
8428  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, recent_token);
8429  return NULL;
8430  }
8431 
8432  Scope * scope = parent;
8433  Expression * case_exp = 0;
8434  TokenData * current_token = recent_token;
8435 
8436  if(!is_default)
8437  {
8438  case_exp = expectSingleExpression(scope, Params().setAllowAutoCall(true).setAllowCall(true).setAllowBinaryOperator(true));
8439  if(!case_exp){
8440  return NULL;
8441  }
8442  if(!case_exp->ret_values){
8443  setError(ERROR_EXPECT_VALUE, case_exp->token);
8444  allocator->deleteObj(case_exp);
8445  return NULL;
8446  }
8447  case_exp = expectExpressionValues(case_exp, 1);
8448  }
8449 
8450  // check for next token is ":"
8451  if(!recent_token || recent_token->type != Tokenizer::OPERATOR_COLON){
8452  setError(Tokenizer::OPERATOR_COLON, recent_token);
8453  allocator->deleteObj(case_exp);
8454  return NULL;
8455  }
8456  readToken();
8457 
8458  if(!is_default){
8459  Expression * case_expression = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_CASE, case_exp->token);
8460  scope->getSwitchScope()->addCaseLabel(case_expression->token, case_exp); // save label to "switch" scope
8461  // scope->getSwitchScope()->setCaseLabelExp(case_expression->token, case_exp); // save expression to evaluate in switch head
8462  return case_expression;
8463  }else{ // create expression for "default" case. this element doesn't include expression to evaluate
8464  Expression * case_expression = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_CASE_DEFAULT, current_token);
8465  scope->getSwitchScope()->addCaseLabel(case_expression->token, NULL); // save label to "switch" scope
8466  return case_expression;
8467  }
8468 }
8469 
8470 OS::Core::Compiler::Expression * OS::Core::Compiler::expectForExpression(Scope * parent)
8471 {
8472  OS_ASSERT(recent_token && recent_token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_for);
8473 
8474  Scope * scope = new (malloc(sizeof(Scope) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Scope(parent, EXP_TYPE_SCOPE, recent_token);
8475  if(!expectToken(Tokenizer::BEGIN_BRACKET_BLOCK) || !expectToken()){
8476  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8477  return NULL;
8478  }
8479  Expression * exp = expectSingleExpression(scope, Params()
8480  .setAllowAssign(true)
8481  .setAllowAutoCall(true)
8482  .setAllowBinaryOperator(true)
8483  .setAllowParams(true)
8484  .setAllowVarDecl(true)
8485  .setAllowNopResult(true)
8486  .setAllowInOperator(false));
8487 
8488  if(!exp){
8489  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8490  return NULL;
8491  }
8492  if(!recent_token){
8493  setError(ERROR_EXPECT_TOKEN, recent_token);
8494  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8495  allocator->deleteObj(exp);
8496  return NULL;
8497  }
8498  if(recent_token->type == Tokenizer::NAME && (exp->type == EXP_TYPE_PARAMS || exp->type == EXP_TYPE_NEW_LOCAL_VAR || exp->type == EXP_TYPE_NAME)){
8499  if(recent_token->str != allocator->core->strings->syntax_in){
8500  setError(allocator->core->strings->syntax_in, recent_token);
8501  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8502  allocator->deleteObj(exp);
8503  return NULL;
8504  }
8505  ExpressionList vars(allocator);
8506  if(exp->type == EXP_TYPE_PARAMS){
8507  vars.swap(exp->list);
8508  allocator->deleteObj(exp);
8509  }else{
8510  vars.add(exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8511  }
8512  exp = NULL;
8513  for(int i = 0; i < vars.count; i++){
8514  OS_ASSERT(vars[i]->type == EXP_TYPE_NAME || vars[i]->type == EXP_TYPE_NEW_LOCAL_VAR);
8515  Expression * name_exp = vars[i];
8516  if(name_exp->type == EXP_TYPE_NAME){
8517  name_exp->type = EXP_TYPE_NOP;
8518  }
8519  }
8520  if(!expectToken()){
8521  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8522  return NULL;
8523  }
8524  exp = expectSingleExpression(scope, Params().setAllowBinaryOperator(true).setAllowAutoCall(true)); // true, false, false, false, true);
8525  if(!recent_token || recent_token->type != Tokenizer::END_BRACKET_BLOCK){
8526  setError(Tokenizer::END_BRACKET_BLOCK, recent_token);
8527  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8528  allocator->deleteObj(exp);
8529  return NULL;
8530  }
8531  if(!exp->ret_values){
8532  setError(ERROR_EXPECT_VALUE, exp->token);
8533  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8534  allocator->deleteObj(exp);
8535  return NULL;
8536  }
8537  exp = expectExpressionValues(exp, 1);
8538  if(!expectToken()){
8539  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8540  allocator->deleteObj(exp);
8541  return NULL;
8542  }
8543  Scope * loop_scope = new (malloc(sizeof(Scope) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Scope(scope, EXP_TYPE_LOOP_SCOPE, recent_token);
8544  Expression * body_exp = expectSingleExpression(loop_scope, true, true);
8545  if(!body_exp){
8546  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8547  allocator->deleteObj(exp);
8548  allocator->deleteObj(loop_scope);
8549  return NULL;
8550  }
8551  body_exp = expectExpressionValues(body_exp, 0);
8552 
8553 #if 1
8554  exp = expectExpressionValues(exp, 1);
8555  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_INIT_ITER, exp->token, exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8556  exp->ret_values = 1;
8557 #else
8558  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_CALL_METHOD, exp->token, exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8559  {
8560  Expression * params = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_PARAMS, exp->token);
8561 
8562  String method_name = allocator->core->strings->__iter;
8563  TokenData * token = new (malloc(sizeof(TokenData) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) TokenData(tokenizer->getTextData(), method_name, Tokenizer::NAME, exp->token->line, exp->token->pos);
8564  Expression * exp_method_name = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_CONST_STRING, token);
8565  exp_method_name->ret_values = 1;
8566  token->release();
8567 
8568  params->list.add(exp_method_name OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8569  params->ret_values = 1;
8570  exp->list.add(params OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8571  }
8572  exp = expectExpressionValues(exp, 1); // vars.count + 1);
8573 #endif
8574  int num_locals = vars.count;
8575 
8576  const int temp_count = 2;
8577  const OS_CHAR * temp_names[temp_count] = {
8578  OS_TEXT("#func"), OS_TEXT("#valid")
8579  };
8580  for(int i = 0; i < temp_count; i++){
8581  String name(allocator, temp_names[i]);
8582  TokenData * token = new (malloc(sizeof(TokenData) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) TokenData(tokenizer->getTextData(), name, Tokenizer::NAME, exp->token->line, exp->token->pos);
8583  Expression * name_exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_NEW_LOCAL_VAR, token);
8584  vars.add(name_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8585  token->release();
8586 
8587  scope->addLocalVar(name, name_exp->local_var);
8588  OS_ASSERT(scope->function);
8589  name_exp->active_locals = scope->function->num_locals;
8590  name_exp->local_var.scope_type = LOCAL_TEMP;
8591  }
8592 
8593  ExpressionList list(allocator);
8594 
8595  // OS: var func = (in_exp).__iter()
8596  {
8597  Expression * params = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_PARAMS, exp->token);
8598  for(int i = num_locals; i < vars.count-1; i++){
8599  Expression * var_exp = vars[i];
8600  Expression * name_exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_NAME, var_exp->token);
8601  OS_ASSERT(scope->function);
8602  name_exp->active_locals = scope->function->num_locals;
8603  name_exp->ret_values = 1;
8604  params->list.add(name_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8605  }
8606  params->ret_values = params->list.count;
8607 
8608  String assing_operator(allocator, OS_TEXT("="));
8609  TokenData * assign_token = new (malloc(sizeof(TokenData) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) TokenData(tokenizer->getTextData(), assing_operator, Tokenizer::OPERATOR_ASSIGN, exp->token->line, exp->token->pos);
8610  exp = newBinaryExpression(scope, EXP_TYPE_ASSIGN, assign_token, params, exp);
8611  OS_ASSERT(exp && (exp->type == EXP_TYPE_SET_LOCAL_VAR && exp->ret_values == 0
8612  || exp->type == EXP_TYPE_SET_LOCAL_VAR_NO_POP && exp->ret_values == 1));
8613  assign_token->release();
8614 
8615  list.add(exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS); exp = NULL;
8616  }
8617  /* OS:
8618  begin loop
8619  var valid, k, v = func(state, state2)
8620  if(!valid) break
8621 
8622  body_exp
8623 
8624  end loop
8625  */
8626  list.add(loop_scope OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8627  {
8628  // OS: var valid, k, v
8629  Expression * params = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_PARAMS, loop_scope->token);
8630  for(int i = 0; i < num_locals+1; i++){
8631  Expression * var_exp = !i ? vars.lastElement() : vars[i-1];
8632  Expression * name_exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_NAME, var_exp->token);
8633  OS_ASSERT(scope->function);
8634  name_exp->active_locals = scope->function->num_locals;
8635  name_exp->ret_values = 1;
8636  params->list.add(name_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8637  }
8638  params->ret_values = params->list.count;
8639 
8640  // OS: func(state, state2)
8641  Expression * call_exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_CALL, loop_scope->token);
8642  {
8643  Expression * var_exp = vars[num_locals]; // func
8644  Expression * name_exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_NAME, var_exp->token);
8645  OS_ASSERT(scope->function);
8646  name_exp->active_locals = scope->function->num_locals;
8647  name_exp->ret_values = 1;
8648  call_exp->list.add(name_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8649 
8650  Expression * params = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_PARAMS, loop_scope->token);
8651  for(int i = num_locals+1; i < vars.count-1; i++){
8652  Expression * var_exp = vars[i];
8653  Expression * name_exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_NAME, var_exp->token);
8654  OS_ASSERT(scope->function);
8655  name_exp->active_locals = scope->function->num_locals;
8656  name_exp->ret_values = 1;
8657  params->list.add(name_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8658  }
8659  params->ret_values = params->list.count;
8660  call_exp->list.add(params OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8661  }
8662  call_exp->ret_values = params->list.count;
8663 
8664  // OS: var valid, k, v = func(state, state2)
8665  String assing_operator(allocator, OS_TEXT("="));
8666  TokenData * assign_token = new (malloc(sizeof(TokenData) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) TokenData(tokenizer->getTextData(), assing_operator,
8667  Tokenizer::OPERATOR_ASSIGN, loop_scope->token->line, loop_scope->token->pos);
8668  exp = newBinaryExpression(scope, EXP_TYPE_ASSIGN, assign_token, params, call_exp);
8669  OS_ASSERT(exp && (exp->type == EXP_TYPE_SET_LOCAL_VAR && exp->ret_values == 0
8670  || exp->type == EXP_TYPE_SET_LOCAL_VAR_NO_POP && exp->ret_values == 1));
8671  assign_token->release();
8672 
8673  loop_scope->list.add(exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS); exp = NULL;
8674  }
8675 
8676  // OS: if(!valid) break
8677  {
8678  Expression * var_exp = vars.lastElement(); // valid var
8679  Expression * name_exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_NAME, var_exp->token);
8680  OS_ASSERT(scope->function);
8681  name_exp->active_locals = scope->function->num_locals;
8682  name_exp->ret_values = 1;
8683 
8684  Expression * not_exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_NOT, loop_scope->token, name_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8685  not_exp->ret_values = 1;
8686 
8687  Expression * break_exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_BREAK, loop_scope->token);
8688  Expression * if_exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_IF, loop_scope->token, not_exp, break_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8689  loop_scope->list.add(if_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8690  }
8691  loop_scope->list.add(body_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8692 
8693  // assemble all exps
8694  scope->list.swap(vars);
8695  scope->list.add(newExpressionFromList(list, 0) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8696  return scope;
8697  }
8698  Expression * pre_exp = exp;
8699  if(recent_token->type != Tokenizer::CODE_SEPARATOR){
8700  setError(Tokenizer::CODE_SEPARATOR, recent_token);
8701  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8702  allocator->deleteObj(pre_exp);
8703  return NULL;
8704  }
8705  readToken();
8706  Expression * bool_exp;
8707  if(recent_token->type == Tokenizer::CODE_SEPARATOR){
8708  bool_exp = NULL;
8709  }else{
8710  bool_exp = expectSingleExpression(scope, Params().setAllowAutoCall(true).setAllowBinaryOperator(true));
8711  if(!bool_exp){
8712  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8713  allocator->deleteObj(pre_exp);
8714  return NULL;
8715  }
8716  bool_exp = expectExpressionValues(bool_exp, 1);
8717  }
8718  if(bool_exp && !bool_exp->ret_values){
8719  setError(ERROR_EXPECT_VALUE, bool_exp->token);
8720  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8721  allocator->deleteObj(pre_exp);
8722  allocator->deleteObj(bool_exp);
8723  return NULL;
8724  }
8725  if(recent_token->type != Tokenizer::CODE_SEPARATOR){
8726  setError(Tokenizer::CODE_SEPARATOR, recent_token);
8727  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8728  allocator->deleteObj(pre_exp);
8729  allocator->deleteObj(bool_exp);
8730  return NULL;
8731  }
8732  readToken();
8733  Expression * post_exp = expectSingleExpression(scope, Params()
8734  .setAllowAssign(true)
8735  .setAllowAutoCall(true)
8736  .setAllowBinaryOperator(true)
8737  .setAllowParams(true)
8738  .setAllowNopResult(true));
8739  if(!post_exp){
8740  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8741  allocator->deleteObj(pre_exp);
8742  allocator->deleteObj(bool_exp);
8743  return NULL;
8744  }
8745  if(recent_token->type != Tokenizer::END_BRACKET_BLOCK){
8746  setError(Tokenizer::END_BRACKET_BLOCK, recent_token);
8747  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8748  allocator->deleteObj(pre_exp);
8749  allocator->deleteObj(bool_exp);
8750  allocator->deleteObj(post_exp);
8751  return NULL;
8752  }
8753  readToken();
8754 
8755  Scope * loop_scope = new (malloc(sizeof(Scope) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Scope(scope, EXP_TYPE_FOR_LOOP_SCOPE, recent_token);
8756  Expression * body_exp = expectSingleExpression(loop_scope, true, true);
8757  if(!body_exp){
8758  allocator->deleteObj(scope);
8759  allocator->deleteObj(pre_exp);
8760  allocator->deleteObj(bool_exp);
8761  allocator->deleteObj(post_exp);
8762  allocator->deleteObj(loop_scope);
8763  return NULL;
8764  }
8765  if(bool_exp){
8766  bool_exp = expectExpressionValues(bool_exp, 1);
8767  Expression * not_exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_NOT, bool_exp->token, bool_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8768  not_exp->ret_values = 1;
8769 
8770  Expression * break_exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_BREAK, bool_exp->token);
8771  Expression * if_exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_IF, bool_exp->token, not_exp, break_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8772 
8773  loop_scope->list.add(if_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8774  }
8775  body_exp = expectExpressionValues(body_exp, 0);
8776  loop_scope->list.add(body_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8777 
8778  post_exp = expectExpressionValues(post_exp, 0);
8779  loop_scope->list.add(post_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8780 
8781  scope->list.add(pre_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8782  scope->list.add(loop_scope OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8783  return scope;
8784 }

8811 OS::Core::Compiler::Expression * OS::Core::Compiler::expectTryExpression(Scope * scope)
8812 {
8813  OS_ASSERT(recent_token && recent_token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_try);
8814  if(!expectToken()){
8815  return NULL;
8816  }
8817  Expression * try_exp;
8818  if(recent_token->type == Tokenizer::BEGIN_CODE_BLOCK){
8819  try_exp = expectCodeExpression(scope);
8820  }else{
8821  try_exp = expectSingleExpression(scope, true);
8822  if(recent_token && recent_token->type == Tokenizer::CODE_SEPARATOR){
8823  readToken();
8824  }
8825  }
8826  if(!try_exp){
8827  return NULL;
8828  }
8829  if(recent_token->type != Tokenizer::NAME){
8830  setError(Tokenizer::NAME, recent_token);
8831  allocator->deleteObj(try_exp);
8832  return NULL;
8833  }
8834  if(recent_token->str != allocator->core->strings->syntax_catch){
8835  setError(allocator->core->strings->syntax_catch, recent_token);
8836  allocator->deleteObj(try_exp);
8837  return NULL;
8838  }
8839  TokenData * catch_token = recent_token;
8840  if(!expectToken(Tokenizer::BEGIN_BRACKET_BLOCK) || !expectToken(Tokenizer::NAME)){
8841  allocator->deleteObj(try_exp);
8842  return NULL;
8843  }
8844 
8845  Scope * catch_scope = new (malloc(sizeof(Scope) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Scope(scope, EXP_TYPE_SCOPE, catch_token);
8846  catch_scope->addLocalVar(recent_token->str, catch_scope->local_var);
8847 
8848  if(!expectToken(Tokenizer::END_BRACKET_BLOCK) || !expectToken()){
8849  allocator->deleteObj(try_exp);
8850  allocator->deleteObj(catch_scope);
8851  return NULL;
8852  }
8853  Expression * catch_exp;
8854  if(recent_token->type == Tokenizer::BEGIN_CODE_BLOCK){
8855  catch_exp = expectCodeExpression(catch_scope);
8856  }else{
8857  catch_exp = expectSingleExpression(catch_scope, true);
8858  if(recent_token && recent_token->type == Tokenizer::CODE_SEPARATOR){
8859  readToken();
8860  }
8861  }
8862  if(!catch_exp){
8863  allocator->deleteObj(try_exp);
8864  allocator->deleteObj(catch_scope);
8865  return NULL;
8866  }
8867  catch_scope->list.add(catch_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8868  return new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_TRY_CATCH, try_exp->token, try_exp, catch_scope OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8869 }

8907 OS::Core::Compiler::Expression * OS::Core::Compiler::expectIfExpression(Scope * scope)
8908 {
8909  OS_ASSERT(recent_token && (recent_token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_if
8910  || recent_token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_elseif));
8911  if(!expectToken(Tokenizer::BEGIN_BRACKET_BLOCK) || !expectToken()){
8912  return NULL;
8913  }
8914  TokenData * token = recent_token;
8915  Expression * if_exp = expectSingleExpression(scope, Params().setAllowBinaryOperator(true)); // .setAllowNopResult(true));
8916  if(!if_exp){
8917  //setError(ERROR_EXPECT_VALUE, token); // error is created in nested expectSingleExpression call
8918  return NULL;
8919  }
8920  if_exp = expectExpressionValues(if_exp, 1);
8921  if(!recent_token || recent_token->type != Tokenizer::END_BRACKET_BLOCK){
8922  setError(Tokenizer::END_BRACKET_BLOCK, recent_token);
8923  allocator->deleteObj(if_exp);
8924  return NULL;
8925  }
8926  if(!expectToken()){
8927  allocator->deleteObj(if_exp);
8928  return NULL;
8929  }
8930  if(!recent_token){
8931  setError(ERROR_EXPECT_TOKEN, recent_token);
8932  allocator->deleteObj(if_exp);
8933  return NULL;
8934  }
8935  token = recent_token;
8936  Expression * then_exp;
8937  if(recent_token->type == Tokenizer::BEGIN_CODE_BLOCK){
8938  then_exp = expectCodeExpression(scope);
8939  }else{
8940  then_exp = expectSingleExpression(scope, true);
8941  if(recent_token && recent_token->type == Tokenizer::CODE_SEPARATOR){
8942  readToken();
8943  }
8944  }
8945  if(!then_exp){
8946  allocator->deleteObj(if_exp);
8947  return NULL;
8948  }
8949  then_exp = expectExpressionValues(then_exp, 0);
8950  if(recent_token && recent_token->type == Tokenizer::NAME){
8951  Expression * else_exp = NULL;
8952  if(recent_token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_elseif){
8953  else_exp = expectIfExpression(scope);
8954  }else if(recent_token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_else){
8955  if(!expectToken()){
8956  allocator->deleteObj(if_exp);
8957  allocator->deleteObj(then_exp);
8958  return NULL;
8959  }
8960  token = recent_token;
8961  else_exp = expectSingleExpression(scope, true, true);
8962  }else{
8963  return new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_IF, if_exp->token, if_exp, then_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8964  }
8965  if(!else_exp){
8966  allocator->deleteObj(if_exp);
8967  allocator->deleteObj(then_exp);
8968  return NULL;
8969  }
8970  else_exp = expectExpressionValues(else_exp, 0);
8971  return new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_IF, if_exp->token, if_exp, then_exp, else_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8972  }
8973  return new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_IF, if_exp->token, if_exp, then_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
8974 }

8976 OS::Core::Compiler::Expression * OS::Core::Compiler::expectReturnExpression(Scope * scope)
8977 {
8978  OS_ASSERT(recent_token && recent_token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_return);
8979  Expression * ret_exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_RETURN, recent_token);
8980  if(!readToken()){
8981  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, recent_token);
8982  allocator->deleteObj(ret_exp);
8983  return NULL;
8984  }
8985  switch(recent_token->type){
8986  case Tokenizer::END_ARRAY_BLOCK:
8987  case Tokenizer::END_BRACKET_BLOCK:
8988  case Tokenizer::END_CODE_BLOCK:
8989  case Tokenizer::CODE_SEPARATOR:
8990  return ret_exp;
8991  }
8992  Expression * exp = expectSingleExpression(scope, Params().setAllowBinaryOperator(true).setAllowParams(true));
8993  if(!exp){
8994  allocator->deleteObj(ret_exp);
8995  return NULL;
8996  }
8997  switch(exp->type){
8998  case EXP_TYPE_SET_LOCAL_VAR:
8999  case EXP_TYPE_SET_PROPERTY:
9000  case EXP_TYPE_SET_DIM:
9001  exp = expectExpressionValues(exp, 1);
9002  }
9003  if(exp->type == EXP_TYPE_PARAMS){
9004  ret_exp->list.swap(exp->list);
9005  ret_exp->ret_values = exp->ret_values;
9006  allocator->deleteObj(exp);
9007  }else{
9008  ret_exp->list.add(exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
9009  ret_exp->ret_values = exp->ret_values;
9010  }
9011  return ret_exp;
9012 }

9014 OS::Core::Compiler::Expression * OS::Core::Compiler::newBinaryExpression(Scope * scope, ExpressionType exp_type, TokenData * token, Expression * left_exp, Expression * right_exp)
9015 {
9016  if(left_exp->isConstValue() && right_exp->isConstValue()){
9017  struct Lib {
9018  Compiler * compiler;
9019  TokenData * token;
9020 
9021  void * malloc(int size OS_DBG_FILEPOS_DECL)
9022  {
9023  return compiler->malloc(size OS_DBG_FILEPOS_PARAM);
9024  }
9025 
9026  Expression * newExpression(const String& str, Expression * left_exp, Expression * right_exp)
9027  {
9028  token = new (malloc(sizeof(TokenData) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) TokenData(token->text_data, str, Tokenizer::STRING, token->line, token->pos);
9029  Expression * exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_CONST_STRING, token);
9030  exp->ret_values = 1;
9031  token->release();
9032  compiler->allocator->deleteObj(left_exp);
9033  compiler->allocator->deleteObj(right_exp);
9034  return exp;
9035  }
9036 
9037  Expression * newExpression(OS_FLOAT val, Expression * left_exp, Expression * right_exp)
9038  {
9039  token = new (malloc(sizeof(TokenData) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) TokenData(token->text_data, String(compiler->allocator, (OS_FLOAT)val), Tokenizer::NUMBER, token->line, token->pos);
9040  token->setFloat(val);
9041  Expression * exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_CONST_NUMBER, token);
9042  exp->ret_values = 1;
9043  token->release();
9044  compiler->allocator->deleteObj(left_exp);
9045  compiler->allocator->deleteObj(right_exp);
9046  return exp;
9047  }
9048 
9049  Expression * newExpression(OS_INT val, Expression * left_exp, Expression * right_exp)
9050  {
9051  return newExpression((OS_FLOAT)val, left_exp, right_exp);
9052  }
9053 
9054  Expression * switchExpression(bool ret_left, Expression * left_exp, Expression * right_exp)
9055  {
9056  if(ret_left){
9057  compiler->allocator->deleteObj(right_exp);
9058  return left_exp;
9059  }
9060  compiler->allocator->deleteObj(left_exp);
9061  return right_exp;
9062  }
9063 
9064  } lib = {this, token};
9065 
9066  if(exp_type == EXP_TYPE_CONCAT || exp_type == EXP_TYPE_BEFORE_INJECT_VAR || exp_type == EXP_TYPE_AFTER_INJECT_VAR){
9067  return lib.newExpression(String(allocator, left_exp->toString(), right_exp->toString()), left_exp, right_exp);
9068  }else if(left_exp->type != EXP_TYPE_CONST_STRING && right_exp->type != EXP_TYPE_CONST_STRING
9069  && left_exp->type != EXP_TYPE_CONST_NULL && right_exp->type != EXP_TYPE_CONST_NULL)
9070  switch(exp_type){
9071  case EXP_TYPE_CONCAT: // ..
9072  case EXP_TYPE_BEFORE_INJECT_VAR: // ..
9073  case EXP_TYPE_AFTER_INJECT_VAR: // ..
9074  return lib.newExpression(String(allocator, left_exp->toString(), right_exp->toString()), left_exp, right_exp);
9075 
9076  case EXP_TYPE_BIT_AND: // &
9077  return lib.newExpression(left_exp->toInt() & right_exp->toInt(), left_exp, right_exp);
9078 
9079  case EXP_TYPE_BIT_OR: // |
9080  return lib.newExpression(left_exp->toInt() | right_exp->toInt(), left_exp, right_exp);
9081 
9082  case EXP_TYPE_BIT_XOR: // ^
9083  return lib.newExpression(left_exp->toInt() ^ right_exp->toInt(), left_exp, right_exp);
9084 
9085  case EXP_TYPE_ADD: // +
9086  return lib.newExpression(left_exp->toNumber() + right_exp->toNumber(), left_exp, right_exp);
9087 
9088  case EXP_TYPE_SUB: // -
9089  return lib.newExpression(left_exp->toNumber() - right_exp->toNumber(), left_exp, right_exp);
9090 
9091  case EXP_TYPE_MUL: // *
9092  return lib.newExpression(left_exp->toNumber() * right_exp->toNumber(), left_exp, right_exp);
9093 
9094  case EXP_TYPE_DIV: // /
9095  if(!right_exp->toNumber()){
9096  // allow throw exception in runtime
9097  break;
9098  }
9099  return lib.newExpression(left_exp->toNumber() / right_exp->toNumber(), left_exp, right_exp);
9100 
9101  case EXP_TYPE_MOD: // %
9102  if(!right_exp->toNumber()){
9103  // allow throw exception in runtime
9104  break;
9105  }
9106  return lib.newExpression(OS_MATH_MOD_OPERATOR(left_exp->toNumber(), right_exp->toNumber()), left_exp, right_exp);
9107 
9108  case EXP_TYPE_LSHIFT: // <<
9109  return lib.newExpression(left_exp->toInt() << right_exp->toInt(), left_exp, right_exp);
9110 
9111  case EXP_TYPE_RSHIFT: // >>
9112  return lib.newExpression(left_exp->toInt() >> right_exp->toInt(), left_exp, right_exp);
9113 
9114  case EXP_TYPE_POW: // **
9115  return lib.newExpression(OS_MATH_POW_OPERATOR(left_exp->toNumber(), right_exp->toNumber()), left_exp, right_exp);
9116  }
9117  }
9118  switch(exp_type){
9119  case EXP_TYPE_CONCAT:
9120  case EXP_TYPE_BEFORE_INJECT_VAR:
9121  case EXP_TYPE_AFTER_INJECT_VAR:
9122  if(left_exp->type == EXP_TYPE_CONST_STRING && left_exp->token->str.isEmpty()){
9123  allocator->deleteObj(left_exp);
9124  return right_exp;
9125  }
9126  if(right_exp->type == EXP_TYPE_CONST_STRING && right_exp->token->str.isEmpty()){
9127  allocator->deleteObj(right_exp);
9128  return left_exp;
9129  }
9130  break;
9131 
9132  case EXP_TYPE_QUESTION:
9133  return finishQuestionOperator(scope, token, left_exp, right_exp);
9134 
9135  case EXP_TYPE_BIT_AND_ASSIGN: // &=
9136  case EXP_TYPE_BIT_OR_ASSIGN: // |=
9137  case EXP_TYPE_BIT_XOR_ASSIGN: // ^=
9138  case EXP_TYPE_BIT_NOT_ASSIGN: // ~=
9139  case EXP_TYPE_ADD_ASSIGN: // +=
9140  case EXP_TYPE_SUB_ASSIGN: // -=
9141  case EXP_TYPE_MUL_ASSIGN: // *=
9142  case EXP_TYPE_DIV_ASSIGN: // /=
9143  case EXP_TYPE_MOD_ASSIGN: // %=
9144  case EXP_TYPE_LSHIFT_ASSIGN: // <<=
9145  case EXP_TYPE_RSHIFT_ASSIGN: // >>=
9146  case EXP_TYPE_POW_ASSIGN: // **=
9147  case EXP_TYPE_ASSIGN:
9148  {
9149  if(left_exp->type != EXP_TYPE_PARAMS){
9150  right_exp = expectExpressionValues(right_exp, 1);
9151  Expression * values_exp = newAssingExpression(scope, left_exp, right_exp);
9152  if(exp_type != EXP_TYPE_ASSIGN){
9153  Expression * exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(exp_type, token, values_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
9154  exp->ret_values = values_exp->ret_values;
9155  return exp;
9156  }
9157  return values_exp;
9158  }
9159  Expression * values_exp = expectExpressionValues(right_exp, left_exp->list.count);
9160  for(int i = left_exp->list.count-1; i >= 0; i--){
9161  OS_ASSERT(values_exp->ret_values > 0);
9162 
9163  Expression * var_exp = left_exp->list[i];
9164  left_exp->list.removeIndex(i); // left_exp is going to be deleted
9165 
9166  values_exp = newAssingExpression(scope, var_exp, values_exp);
9167  if(!values_exp){
9168  break;
9169  }
9170  }
9171  allocator->deleteObj(left_exp);
9172  if(!values_exp)
9173  return NULL;
9174  OS_ASSERT(values_exp->ret_values == 0);
9175  if(exp_type != EXP_TYPE_ASSIGN){
9176  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, token);
9177  allocator->deleteObj(values_exp);
9178  return NULL;
9179  /* Expression * exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(exp_type, token, values_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
9180  exp->ret_values = values_exp->ret_values;
9181  return exp; */
9182  }
9183  return values_exp;
9184  }
9185  }
9186  if(left_exp->type == EXP_TYPE_PARAMS){
9187  OS_ASSERT(right_exp->type != EXP_TYPE_PARAMS);
9188  right_exp = expectExpressionValues(right_exp, 1);
9189  left_exp->list.add(right_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
9190  left_exp->ret_values++;
9191  return left_exp;
9192  }
9193  if(right_exp->type == EXP_TYPE_PARAMS){
9194  Expression * params = right_exp;
9195  OS_ASSERT(params->list.count > 0);
9196  if(params->list.count == 1){
9197  right_exp = params->list[0];
9198  allocator->vectorClear(params->list);
9199  allocator->deleteObj(params);
9200  }else{
9201  left_exp = expectExpressionValues(left_exp, 1);
9202  allocator->vectorInsertAtIndex(params->list, 0, left_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
9203  params->ret_values++;
9204  return params;
9205  }
9206  }
9207  left_exp = expectExpressionValues(left_exp, 1);
9208  right_exp = expectExpressionValues(right_exp, 1);
9209  Expression * exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(exp_type, token, left_exp, right_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
9210  exp->ret_values = exp_type == EXP_TYPE_PARAMS ? 2 : 1;
9211  return exp;
9212 }

9214 OS::Core::Compiler::Scope::LocalVar& OS::Core::Compiler::Scope::getLocalVar(const LocalVarDesc& var)
9215 {
9216  Scope * scope = this;
9217  int i;
9218  /* for(i = 0; i < var.up_scope_count; i++){
9219  scope = scope->parent;
9220  OS_ASSERT(scope);
9221  } */

9229  break;
9230  }

9239 bool OS::Core::Compiler::findLocalVar(LocalVarDesc& desc, Scope * scope, const String& name, int active_locals, bool all_scopes, bool decl)
9240 {
9241  OS_ASSERT(scope);
9242  for(int up_count = 0, up_scope_count = 0;;){
9243  for(int i = scope->locals.count-1; i >= 0; i--){
9244  const Scope::LocalVar& local_var = scope->locals[i];
9245  if((up_count || (decl && !up_scope_count) || local_var.index < active_locals) && local_var.name == name){
9246  desc.index = local_var.index;
9247  desc.up_count = up_count;
9248  desc.up_scope_count = up_scope_count;
9249  desc.scope_type = i < scope->num_params ? LOCAL_PARAM : (name.toChar()[0] != OS_TEXT('#') ? LOCAL_GENERIC : LOCAL_TEMP);
9250  return true;
9251  }
9252  }
9253  if(scope->parent){
9254  if(!all_scopes){
9255  return false;
9256  }
9257  if(scope->type == EXP_TYPE_FUNCTION){
9258  up_count++;
9259  }
9260  up_scope_count++;
9261  scope = scope->parent;
9262  continue;
9263  }
9264  break;
9265  }
9266  return false;
9267 }
9268 
9269 void OS::Core::Compiler::registerUpvalue(Scope * scope, Expression * exp)
9270 {
9271 #if 1
9272  OS_ASSERT(scope && exp && exp->local_var.up_count > 0);
9273  for(int up_count = exp->local_var.up_count; up_count > 0; up_count--){
9274  OS_ASSERT(scope->function && scope->function->parent);
9275  scope = scope->function->parent;
9276  }
9277  for(;;){
9278  for(int i = scope->locals.count-1; i >= 0; i--){
9279  Scope::LocalVar& local_var = scope->locals[i];
9280  if(local_var.index == exp->local_var.index){
9281  local_var.upvalue = true;
9282  return;
9283  }
9284  }
9285  if(scope == scope->function){
9286  OS_ASSERT(false);
9287  break;
9288  }
9289  scope = scope->parent;
9290  }
9291 #else
9292 #if 1
9293  OS_ASSERT(scope && exp && exp->local_var.up_scope_count > 0);
9294  for(int up_count = exp->local_var.up_scope_count; up_count > 0; up_count--){
9295  OS_ASSERT(scope->parent);
9296  scope = scope->parent;
9297  }
9298 #else
9299  OS_ASSERT(scope && exp && exp->local_var.up_count > 0);
9300  for(int up_count = exp->local_var.up_count; up_count > 0;){
9301  OS_ASSERT(scope->parent);
9302  if(scope->type == EXP_TYPE_FUNCTION){
9303  up_count--;
9304  }
9305  scope = scope->parent;
9306  }
9307  // OS_ASSERT(scope->function);
9308  // scope = scope->function;
9309 #endif
9310  for(int i = scope->locals.count-1; i >= 0; i--){
9311  Scope::LocalVar& local_var = scope->locals[i];
9312  if(local_var.index == exp->local_var.index){
9313  local_var.upvalue = true;
9314  return;
9315  }
9316  }
9317 #endif
9318  OS_ASSERT(false);
9319 }
9320 
9321 OS::Core::Compiler::Expression * OS::Core::Compiler::newAssingExpression(Scope * scope, Expression * var_exp, Expression * value_exp)
9322 {
9323  switch(var_exp->type){
9324  case EXP_TYPE_CALL_DIM:
9325  {
9326  // Expression * name_exp = var_exp->list[0];
9327  Expression * params = var_exp->list[1];
9328  OS_ASSERT(params->type == EXP_TYPE_PARAMS); (void)params;
9329  allocator->vectorInsertAtIndex(var_exp->list, 0, value_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
9330  var_exp->type = EXP_TYPE_SET_DIM;
9331  var_exp->ret_values = value_exp->ret_values-1;
9332  return var_exp;
9333  }
9334 
9335  case EXP_TYPE_INDIRECT:
9336  {
9337  OS_ASSERT(var_exp->list.count == 2);
9338  Expression * var_exp_left = var_exp->list[0];
9339  switch(var_exp_left->type){
9340  case EXP_TYPE_NAME:
9341  {
9342  OS_ASSERT(var_exp_left->ret_values == 1);
9343  if(findLocalVar(var_exp_left->local_var, scope, var_exp_left->token->str, var_exp_left->active_locals, true)){
9344  var_exp_left->type = EXP_TYPE_GET_LOCAL_VAR_AUTO_CREATE;
9345  if(scope->function->max_up_count < var_exp_left->local_var.up_count){
9346  scope->function->max_up_count = var_exp_left->local_var.up_count;
9347  }
9348  }else{
9349  var_exp_left->type = EXP_TYPE_GET_ENV_VAR_AUTO_CREATE;
9350  }
9351  break;
9352  }
9353  case EXP_TYPE_CONST_NULL:
9354  case EXP_TYPE_CONST_NUMBER:
9355  case EXP_TYPE_CONST_STRING:
9356  case EXP_TYPE_CONST_TRUE:
9357  case EXP_TYPE_CONST_FALSE:
9358  setError(ERROR_EXPECT_WRITEABLE, var_exp_left->token);
9359  allocator->deleteObj(var_exp);
9360  allocator->deleteObj(value_exp);
9361  return NULL;
9362  }
9363  ExpressionType exp_type = EXP_TYPE_SET_PROPERTY;
9364  Expression * var_exp_right = var_exp->list[1];
9365  switch(var_exp_right->type){
9366  case EXP_TYPE_NAME:
9367  OS_ASSERT(var_exp_right->ret_values == 1);
9368  var_exp_right->type = EXP_TYPE_CONST_STRING;
9369  break;
9370 
9371  case EXP_TYPE_CALL:
9372  case EXP_TYPE_CALL_AUTO_PARAM:
9373  OS_ASSERT(false);
9374  return NULL;
9375 
9376  case EXP_TYPE_CALL_DIM:
9377  OS_ASSERT(false);
9378  return NULL;
9379  }
9380  Expression * exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(exp_type, var_exp->token, value_exp, var_exp_left, var_exp_right OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
9381  exp->ret_values = value_exp->ret_values-1;
9382  allocator->vectorClear(var_exp->list);
9383  allocator->deleteObj(var_exp);
9384  return exp;
9385  }
9386  break;
9387 
9388  case EXP_TYPE_NAME:
9389  if(findLocalVar(var_exp->local_var, scope, var_exp->token->str, var_exp->active_locals, true)){
9390  var_exp->type = EXP_TYPE_SET_LOCAL_VAR;
9391  if(scope->function->max_up_count < var_exp->local_var.up_count){
9392  scope->function->max_up_count = var_exp->local_var.up_count;
9393  }
9394  }else{
9395  var_exp->type = EXP_TYPE_SET_ENV_VAR;
9396  }
9397  var_exp->list.add(value_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
9398  var_exp->ret_values = value_exp->ret_values-1;
9399  return var_exp;
9400 
9401  default:
9402  // OS_ASSERT(false);
9403  if(!var_exp->isWriteable()){
9404  setError(ERROR_EXPECT_WRITEABLE, var_exp->token);
9405  allocator->deleteObj(var_exp);
9406  allocator->deleteObj(value_exp);
9407  return NULL;
9408  }
9409  }
9410  var_exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_ASSIGN, var_exp->token, var_exp, value_exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
9411  var_exp->ret_values = 1;
9412  return var_exp;
9413 }
9414 
9415 OS::Core::Compiler::Expression * OS::Core::Compiler::finishBinaryOperator(Scope * scope, OpcodeLevel prev_level, Expression * exp,
9416  const Params& _p, bool& is_finished)
9417 {
9418  TokenData * binary_operator = recent_token;
9419  OS_ASSERT(binary_operator->isTypeOf(Tokenizer::BINARY_OPERATOR));
9420 
9421  Params p = Params(_p)
9422  .setAllowAssign(false)
9423  .setAllowBinaryOperator(false)
9424  .setAllowInOperator(_p.allow_in_operator)
9425  // .setAllowParams(false)
9426  .setAllowAutoCall(false) // binary_operator->type == Tokenizer::OPERATOR_ASSIGN)
9427  .setAllowRootBlocks(false);
9428 
9429  readToken();
9430  Expression * exp2 = expectSingleExpression(scope, Params(p).setAllowParams(false)); // false, allow_param, false, false, false);
9431  if(!exp2){
9432  is_finished = true;
9433  allocator->deleteObj(exp);
9434  return NULL;
9435  }
9436  // exp2 = expectExpressionValues(exp2, 1);
9437  if(recent_token && recent_token->type == Tokenizer::NAME){
9438  if(recent_token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_in){
9439  if(p.allow_in_operator){
9440  recent_token->type = Tokenizer::OPERATOR_IN;
9441  }
9442  }else if(recent_token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_is){
9443  recent_token->type = Tokenizer::OPERATOR_IS;
9444  }else if(recent_token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_as){
9445  recent_token->type = Tokenizer::OPERATOR_AS;
9446  }
9447  }
9448  if(!recent_token || !recent_token->isTypeOf(Tokenizer::BINARY_OPERATOR) || (!p.allow_params && recent_token->type == Tokenizer::PARAM_SEPARATOR)){
9449  is_finished = true;
9450  return newBinaryExpression(scope, getExpressionType(binary_operator->type), binary_operator, exp, exp2);
9451  }
9452  ExpressionType left_exp_type = getExpressionType(binary_operator->type);
9453  ExpressionType right_exp_type = getExpressionType(recent_token->type);
9454  OpcodeLevel left_level = getOpcodeLevel(left_exp_type);
9455  OpcodeLevel right_level = getOpcodeLevel(right_exp_type);
9456  if(left_exp_type != EXP_TYPE_PARAMS && Expression::isAssignOperator(right_exp_type)){ // == EXP_TYPE_ASSIGN){
9457  right_level = (OpcodeLevel)(left_level + 1);
9458  /* }else if(left_exp_type == EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_AND && right_exp_type == EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_AND){
9459  right_level = (OpcodeLevel)(left_level + 1);
9460  }else if(left_exp_type == EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_OR && right_exp_type == EXP_TYPE_LOGIC_OR){
9461  right_level = (OpcodeLevel)(left_level + 1); */
9462  }
9463  if(left_level == right_level){
9464  exp = newBinaryExpression(scope, left_exp_type, binary_operator, exp, exp2);
9465  return finishBinaryOperator(scope, prev_level, exp, p, is_finished);
9466  }
9467  if(left_level > right_level){
9468  exp = newBinaryExpression(scope, left_exp_type, binary_operator, exp, exp2);
9469  if(prev_level >= right_level){
9470  is_finished = false;
9471  return exp;
9472  }
9473  return finishBinaryOperator(scope, prev_level, exp, p, is_finished);
9474  }
9475  exp2 = finishBinaryOperator(scope, left_level, exp2, p, is_finished);
9476  if(!exp2){
9477  allocator->deleteObj(exp);
9478  return NULL;
9479  }
9480  exp = newBinaryExpression(scope, left_exp_type, binary_operator, exp, exp2);
9481  if(is_finished){
9482  return exp;
9483  }
9484  return finishBinaryOperator(scope, prev_level, exp, p, is_finished);
9485 }

9487 OS::Core::Compiler::Expression * OS::Core::Compiler::finishValueExpressionNoAutoCall(Scope * scope, Expression * exp, const Params& p)
9488 {
9489  return finishValueExpression(scope, exp, Params(p).setAllowAutoCall(false));
9490 }

9492 OS::Core::Compiler::Expression * OS::Core::Compiler::finishValueExpressionNoNextCall(Scope * scope, Expression * exp, const Params& p)
9493 {
9494  if(recent_token && recent_token->type == Tokenizer::BEGIN_BRACKET_BLOCK){
9495  return exp;
9496  }
9497  return finishValueExpression(scope, exp, Params(p).setAllowAutoCall(false));
9498 }

9500 OS::Core::Compiler::Expression * OS::Core::Compiler::finishValueExpression(Scope * scope, Expression * exp, const Params& _p)
9501 {
9502  bool is_finished;
9503  Params p = Params(_p)
9504  .setAllowRootBlocks(false);
9505  bool next_allow_auto_call = false;
9506  for(;; p.allow_auto_call = next_allow_auto_call, next_allow_auto_call = false){
9507  if(!recent_token){
9508  return exp;
9509  }
9510  Expression * exp2;
9511  TokenData * token = recent_token;
9512  TokenType token_type = token->type;
9513  switch(token_type){
9514  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_INDIRECT: // .
9515  token = expectToken(Tokenizer::NAME);
9516  if(!token){
9517  allocator->deleteObj(exp);
9518  return NULL;
9519  }
9520  exp2 = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_NAME, token);
9521  exp2->ret_values = 1;
9522  OS_ASSERT(scope->function);
9523  exp2->active_locals = scope->function->num_locals;
9524  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_INDIRECT, exp2->token, exp, exp2 OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
9525  exp->ret_values = 1;
9526  readToken();
9527  next_allow_auto_call = p.allow_auto_call;
9528  continue;
9529 
9530  // post ++, post --
9531  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_INC:
9532  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_DEC:
9533  if(exp->type != EXP_TYPE_NAME && exp->type != EXP_TYPE_INDIRECT
9534  && exp->type != EXP_TYPE_CALL_DIM)
9535  {
9536  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, exp->token);
9537  allocator->deleteObj(exp);
9538  return NULL;
9539  }
9540  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(token_type == Tokenizer::OPERATOR_INC ? EXP_TYPE_POST_INC : EXP_TYPE_POST_DEC, exp->token, exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
9541  exp->ret_values = 1;
9542  readToken();
9543  return finishValueExpressionNoAutoCall(scope, exp, p);
9544 
9545  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_CONCAT: // ..
9546  case Tokenizer::BEFORE_INJECT_VAR: // ..
9547  case Tokenizer::AFTER_INJECT_VAR: // ..
9548 
9549  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_AND: // &&
9550  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_OR: // ||
9551 
9552  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_PTR_EQ: // ===
9553  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_PTR_NE: // !==
9554  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_EQ: // ==
9555  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_NE: // !=
9556  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_GE: // >=
9557  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_LE: // <=
9558  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_GREATER: // >
9559  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_LESS: // <
9560  // case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_NOT: // !
9561 
9562  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_QUESTION: // ?
9563 
9564  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_BIT_AND: // &
9565  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_BIT_OR: // |
9566  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_BIT_XOR: // ^
9567  // case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_BIT_NOT: // ~
9568  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_COMPARE: // <=>
9569  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_ADD: // +
9570  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_SUB: // -
9571  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_MUL: // *
9572  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_DIV: // /
9573  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_MOD: // %
9574  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LSHIFT: // <<
9575  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_RSHIFT: // >>
9576  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_POW: // **
9577  if(!p.allow_binary_operator){
9578  return exp;
9579  }
9580  exp = finishBinaryOperator(scope, OP_LEVEL_NOTHING, exp, p, is_finished);
9581  if(!exp){
9582  return NULL;
9583  }
9584  OS_ASSERT(is_finished);
9585  continue;
9586 
9587  case Tokenizer::PARAM_SEPARATOR:
9588  if(!p.allow_params){
9589  return exp;
9590  }
9591  exp = finishBinaryOperator(scope, OP_LEVEL_NOTHING, exp, p, is_finished);
9592  if(!exp){
9593  return NULL;
9594  }
9595  OS_ASSERT(is_finished);
9596  continue;
9597 
9598  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_BIT_AND_ASSIGN: // &=
9599  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_BIT_OR_ASSIGN: // |=
9600  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_BIT_XOR_ASSIGN: // ^=
9601  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_BIT_NOT_ASSIGN: // ~=
9602  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_ADD_ASSIGN: // +=
9603  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_SUB_ASSIGN: // -=
9604  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_MUL_ASSIGN: // *=
9605  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_DIV_ASSIGN: // /=
9606  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_MOD_ASSIGN: // %=
9607  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LSHIFT_ASSIGN: // <<=
9608  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_RSHIFT_ASSIGN: // >>=
9609  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_POW_ASSIGN: // **=
9610  exp = exp;
9611  /* setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, token);
9612  allocator->deleteObj(exp);
9613  return NULL; */
9614 
9615  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_ASSIGN: // =
9616  if(!p.allow_binary_operator){ // allow_assing){ // allow_binary_operator){
9617  return exp;
9618  }
9619  exp = finishBinaryOperator(scope, OP_LEVEL_NOTHING, exp, Params(p).setAllowAssign(false), is_finished);
9620  if(!exp){
9621  return NULL;
9622  }
9623  OS_ASSERT(is_finished);
9624  return exp;
9625 
9626  case Tokenizer::END_ARRAY_BLOCK:
9627  case Tokenizer::END_BRACKET_BLOCK:
9628  case Tokenizer::END_CODE_BLOCK:
9629  case Tokenizer::CODE_SEPARATOR:
9630  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_COLON:
9631  return exp;
9632 
9633  case Tokenizer::BEGIN_CODE_BLOCK: // {
9634  switch(exp->type){
9635  case EXP_TYPE_CONST_NUMBER:
9636  case EXP_TYPE_CONST_STRING:
9637  case EXP_TYPE_CONST_FALSE:
9638  case EXP_TYPE_CONST_TRUE:
9639  case EXP_TYPE_CONST_NULL:
9640  return exp;
9641  }
9642  exp2 = expectObjectOrFunctionExpression(scope, p, false);
9643  if(!exp2){
9644  allocator->deleteObj(exp);
9645  return NULL;
9646  }
9647  OS_ASSERT(exp2->ret_values == 1);
9648  exp2 = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_PARAMS, exp2->token, exp2 OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
9649  exp2->ret_values = 1;
9650  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_CALL_AUTO_PARAM, token, exp, exp2 OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
9651  exp->ret_values = 1;
9652  // allow_auto_call = false;
9653  continue;
9654 
9655  case Tokenizer::NAME:
9656  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_in){
9657  if(!p.allow_in_operator || !p.allow_binary_operator){
9658  return exp;
9659  }
9660  token->type = Tokenizer::OPERATOR_IN;
9661  exp = finishBinaryOperator(scope, OP_LEVEL_NOTHING, exp, p, is_finished);
9662  if(!exp){
9663  return NULL;
9664  }
9665  OS_ASSERT(is_finished);
9666  continue;
9667  }
9668  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_is){
9669  if(!p.allow_binary_operator){
9670  return exp;
9671  }
9672  token->type = Tokenizer::OPERATOR_IS;
9673  exp = finishBinaryOperator(scope, OP_LEVEL_NOTHING, exp, p, is_finished);
9674  if(!exp){
9675  return NULL;
9676  }
9677  OS_ASSERT(is_finished);
9678  continue;
9679  }
9680  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_as){
9681  if(!p.allow_binary_operator){
9682  return exp;
9683  }
9684  token->type = Tokenizer::OPERATOR_AS;
9685  exp = finishBinaryOperator(scope, OP_LEVEL_NOTHING, exp, p, is_finished);
9686  if(!exp){
9687  return NULL;
9688  }
9689  OS_ASSERT(is_finished);
9690  continue;
9691  }
9692  // no break
9693 
9694  default:
9695  if(!p.allow_auto_call){
9696  return exp;
9697  }
9698  if(token->type == Tokenizer::NAME){
9699  Core::Strings * strings = allocator->core->strings;
9700  if(token->str == strings->syntax_var
9701  || token->str == strings->syntax_local
9702  // || token->str == strings->syntax_function
9703  || token->str == strings->syntax_return
9704  || token->str == strings->syntax_if
9705  || token->str == strings->syntax_else
9706  || token->str == strings->syntax_elseif
9707  || token->str == strings->syntax_for
9708  || token->str == strings->syntax_break
9709  || token->str == strings->syntax_continue
9710  || token->str == strings->syntax_in
9711  || token->str == strings->syntax_class
9712  || token->str == strings->syntax_enum
9713  || token->str == strings->syntax_switch
9714  || token->str == strings->syntax_case
9715  || token->str == strings->syntax_default
9716  || token->str == strings->syntax_try
9717  || token->str == strings->syntax_catch
9718  || token->str == strings->syntax_finally
9719  || token->str == strings->syntax_throw
9720  || token->str == strings->syntax_new
9721  || token->str == strings->syntax_while
9722  || token->str == strings->syntax_do
9723  || token->str == strings->syntax_const
9724  || token->str == strings->syntax_public
9725  || token->str == strings->syntax_protected
9726  || token->str == strings->syntax_private
9727  || token->str == strings->syntax_yield
9728  || token->str == strings->syntax_static
9729  || token->str == strings->syntax_debugger
9730  // || token->str == strings->syntax_debuglocals
9731  // || token->str == strings->syntax_line
9732  // || token->str == strings->syntax_file
9733  )
9734  {
9735  return exp;
9736  }
9737  }
9738  exp2 = expectSingleExpression(scope, Params(p)
9739  .setAllowAssign(false)
9740  .setAllowAutoCall(false)
9741  .setAllowParams(false)
9742  .setAllowRootBlocks(false)); // allow_binary_operator, false, false, false, false);
9743  if(!exp2){
9744  allocator->deleteObj(exp);
9745  return NULL;
9746  }
9747  // OS_ASSERT(exp2->ret_values == 1);
9748  exp2 = expectExpressionValues(exp2, 1);
9749  exp2 = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_PARAMS, exp2->token, exp2 OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
9750  exp2->ret_values = 1;
9751  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_CALL_AUTO_PARAM, token, exp, exp2 OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
9752  exp->ret_values = 1;
9753  // allow_auto_call = false;
9754  continue;
9755 
9756  case Tokenizer::BEGIN_BRACKET_BLOCK: // (
9757  if(!p.allow_call){
9758  return exp;
9759  }
9760  exp2 = expectParamsExpression(scope);
9761  if(!exp2){
9762  allocator->deleteObj(exp);
9763  return NULL;
9764  }
9765  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_CALL, token, exp, exp2 OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
9766  exp->ret_values = 1;
9767  continue;
9768 
9769  case Tokenizer::BEGIN_ARRAY_BLOCK: // [
9770  exp2 = expectParamsExpression(scope);
9771  if(!exp2){
9772  allocator->deleteObj(exp);
9773  return NULL;
9774  }
9775  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_CALL_DIM, token, exp, exp2 OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
9776  exp->ret_values = 1;
9777  if(0 && !p.allow_binary_operator){
9778  return exp;
9779  }
9780  continue;
9781  }
9782  }
9783  return NULL; // shut up compiler
9784 }

9859 bool OS::Core::Compiler::isVarNameValid(const String& name)
9860 {
9861  Core::Strings * strings = allocator->core->strings;
9862  return !(name == strings->syntax_super
9863  || name == strings->syntax_is
9864  || name == strings->syntax_extends
9865  || name == strings->syntax_delete
9866  || name == strings->syntax_prototype
9867  || name == strings->syntax_var
9868  || name == strings->syntax_local
9869  || name == strings->syntax_arguments
9870  || name == strings->syntax_function
9871  || name == strings->syntax_null
9872  || name == strings->syntax_true
9873  || name == strings->syntax_false
9874  || name == strings->syntax_return
9875  || name == strings->syntax_class
9876  || name == strings->syntax_enum
9877  || name == strings->syntax_switch
9878  || name == strings->syntax_case
9879  || name == strings->syntax_default
9880  || name == strings->syntax_if
9881  || name == strings->syntax_else
9882  || name == strings->syntax_elseif
9883  || name == strings->syntax_for
9884  || name == strings->syntax_in
9885  || name == strings->syntax_break
9886  || name == strings->syntax_continue
9887  || name == strings->syntax_try
9888  || name == strings->syntax_catch
9889  || name == strings->syntax_finally
9890  || name == strings->syntax_throw
9891  || name == strings->syntax_new
9892  || name == strings->syntax_while
9893  || name == strings->syntax_do
9894  || name == strings->syntax_const
9895  || name == strings->syntax_public
9896  || name == strings->syntax_protected
9897  || name == strings->syntax_private
9898  || name == strings->syntax_yield
9899  || name == strings->syntax_static
9900  || name == strings->syntax_debugger
9901  || name == strings->syntax_debuglocals

9904  || name == strings->syntax_dir

9907  || name == strings->var_env
9908  || name == strings->var_globals
9909  );
9910 }

9912 OS::Core::Compiler::Expression * OS::Core::Compiler::expectSingleExpression(Scope * scope, bool allow_nop_result,
9913  bool allow_inline_nested_block, bool allow_params)
9914 {
9915  return expectSingleExpression(scope, Params()
9916  .setAllowAssign(true)
9917  .setAllowAutoCall(true)
9918  .setAllowBinaryOperator(true)
9919  .setAllowParams(allow_params)
9920  .setAllowRootBlocks(true)
9921  .setAllowNopResult(allow_nop_result)
9922  .setAllowInlineNestedBlock(allow_inline_nested_block));
9923 }
9924 
9925 OS::Core::Compiler::Expression * OS::Core::Compiler::expectSingleExpression(Scope * scope, const Params& p)
9926 {
9927 #ifdef OS_DEBUG
9928  allocator->checkNativeStackUsage(OS_TEXT("OS::Core::Compiler::expectSingleExpression"));
9929 #endif
9930  TokenData * token = recent_token; // readToken();
9931  if(!token){
9932  setError(ERROR_EXPECT_EXPRESSION, token);
9933  return NULL;
9934  }
9935  Expression * exp;
9936  TokenType token_type = token->type;
9937  switch(token_type){
9938  // begin unary operators
9939  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_ADD:
9940  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_SUB:
9941  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LENGTH:
9942  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_BIT_NOT:
9943  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_NOT:
9944  if(!expectToken()){
9945  return NULL;
9946  }
9947  exp = expectSingleExpression(scope, Params());
9948  if(!exp){
9949  return NULL;
9950  }
9951  OS_ASSERT(exp->ret_values == 1);
9952  switch(exp->type){
9953  case EXP_TYPE_CONST_NUMBER:
9954  case EXP_TYPE_CONST_NULL:
9955  case EXP_TYPE_CONST_TRUE:
9956  case EXP_TYPE_CONST_FALSE:
9957  switch(token_type){
9958  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_ADD:
9959  exp->type = EXP_TYPE_CONST_NUMBER;
9960  exp->token->setFloat(exp->toNumber());
9961  return finishValueExpressionNoAutoCall(scope, exp, p);
9962 
9963  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_SUB:
9964  exp->type = EXP_TYPE_CONST_NUMBER;
9965  exp->token->setFloat(-exp->toNumber());
9966  return finishValueExpressionNoAutoCall(scope, exp, p);
9967 
9968  // case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LENGTH:
9969  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_BIT_NOT:
9970  exp->type = EXP_TYPE_CONST_NUMBER;
9971  exp->token->setFloat((OS_FLOAT)~exp->toInt());
9972  return finishValueExpressionNoAutoCall(scope, exp, p);
9973 
9974  /* case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_NOT:
9975  {
9976  bool b = !exp->toInt();
9977  exp->type = b ? EXP_TYPE_CONST_TRUE : EXP_TYPE_CONST_FALSE;
9978  exp->token->setFloat((OS_FLOAT)b);
9979  return finishValueExpressionNoAutoCall(scope, exp, p);
9980  } */
9981  }
9982  break;
9983  }
9984  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(getUnaryExpressionType(token_type), exp->token, exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
9985  exp->ret_values = 1;
9986  return finishValueExpressionNoAutoCall(scope, exp, p);
9987 
9988  // pre ++, pre --
9989  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_INC:
9990  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_DEC:
9991  if(!expectToken()){
9992  return NULL;
9993  }
9994  exp = expectSingleExpression(scope, Params());
9995  if(!exp){
9996  return NULL;
9997  }
9998  if(exp->type != EXP_TYPE_NAME && exp->type != EXP_TYPE_INDIRECT
9999  && exp->type != EXP_TYPE_CALL_DIM)
10000  {
10001  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, exp->token);
10002  allocator->deleteObj(exp);
10003  return NULL;
10004  }
10005  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(token_type == Tokenizer::OPERATOR_INC ? EXP_TYPE_PRE_INC : EXP_TYPE_PRE_DEC, exp->token, exp OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
10006  exp->ret_values = 1;
10007  return finishValueExpressionNoAutoCall(scope, exp, p);
10008  // end unary operators
10009 
10010  case Tokenizer::OPERATOR_THIS:
10011  readToken();
10012  if(recent_token && recent_token->type == Tokenizer::BEGIN_CODE_BLOCK){
10013  exp = expectFunctionBlockExpression(scope);
10014  return exp ? finishValueExpression(scope, exp, p) : NULL;
10015  }
10016  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_GET_THIS, token);
10017  exp->ret_values = 1;
10018  if(recent_token && recent_token->type == Tokenizer::NAME){
10019  Expression * exp2 = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_NAME, recent_token);
10020  exp2->ret_values = 1;
10021  OS_ASSERT(scope->function);
10022  exp2->active_locals = scope->function->num_locals; // TODO: remove it?
10023  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_INDIRECT, exp2->token, exp, exp2 OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
10024  exp->ret_values = 1;
10025  readToken();
10026  }
10027  return finishValueExpression(scope, exp, p);
10028 
10029  case Tokenizer::BEGIN_CODE_BLOCK:
10030  if(p.allow_root_blocks && !isNextToken(Tokenizer::OPERATOR_BIT_OR) && !isNextToken(Tokenizer::OPERATOR_LOGIC_OR)){
10031  if(!p.allow_inline_nested_block){
10032  TokenData * check_token = getPrevToken();
10033  if(!check_token || (check_token->type != Tokenizer::CODE_SEPARATOR && check_token->type != Tokenizer::BEGIN_CODE_BLOCK)){
10034  setError(ERROR_EXPECT_CODE_SEP_BEFORE_NESTED_BLOCK, recent_token);
10035  return NULL;
10036  }
10037  }
10038  return expectCodeExpression(scope);
10039  }
10040  return expectObjectOrFunctionExpression(scope, p);
10041 
10042  case Tokenizer::BEGIN_ARRAY_BLOCK:
10043  return expectArrayExpression(scope, p);
10044 
10045  case Tokenizer::BEGIN_BRACKET_BLOCK:
10046  return expectBracketExpression(scope, p);
10047 
10048  case Tokenizer::STRING:
10049  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_CONST_STRING, token);
10050  exp->ret_values = 1;
10051  readToken();
10052  return finishValueExpressionNoNextCall(scope, exp, p);
10053 
10054  case Tokenizer::NUMBER:
10055  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_CONST_NUMBER, token);
10056  exp->ret_values = 1;
10057  readToken();
10058  return finishValueExpressionNoNextCall(scope, exp, p);
10059 
10060  case Tokenizer::REST_ARGUMENTS:
10061  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_GET_REST_ARGUMENTS, token);
10062  exp->ret_values = 1;
10063  readToken();
10064  return finishValueExpressionNoNextCall(scope, exp, p);
10065 
10066  case Tokenizer::CODE_SEPARATOR:
10067  case Tokenizer::END_ARRAY_BLOCK:
10068  case Tokenizer::END_BRACKET_BLOCK:
10069  case Tokenizer::END_CODE_BLOCK:
10070  if(!p.allow_nop_result){
10071  return NULL;
10072  }
10073  return new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_NOP, token);
10074 
10075  case Tokenizer::NAME:
10076  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_var || token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_local){
10077  if(!p.allow_var_decl){
10078  setError(ERROR_NESTED_ROOT_BLOCK, token);
10079  return NULL;
10080  }
10081  return expectVarExpression(scope);
10082  }
10083  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_function){
10084  exp = expectFunctionExpression(scope);
10085  if(!exp){
10086  return NULL;
10087  }
10088  if(!exp->ret_values){
10089  return exp;
10090  }
10091  return finishValueExpression(scope, exp, p);
10092  }
10093  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_return){
10094  return expectReturnExpression(scope);
10095  }
10096  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_if){
10097  if(!p.allow_root_blocks){
10098  setError(ERROR_NESTED_ROOT_BLOCK, token);
10099  return NULL;
10100  }
10101  return expectIfExpression(scope);
10102  }
10103  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_else){
10104  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, token);
10105  return NULL;
10106  }
10107  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_elseif){
10108  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, token);
10109  return NULL;
10110  }
10111  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_for){
10112  if(!p.allow_root_blocks){
10113  setError(ERROR_NESTED_ROOT_BLOCK, token);
10114  return NULL;
10115  }
10116  return expectForExpression(scope);
10117  }
10118  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_in){
10119  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, token);
10120  return NULL;
10121  }
10122  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->var_this){
10123  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_GET_THIS, token);
10124  exp->ret_values = 1;
10125  readToken();
10126  return finishValueExpression(scope, exp, p);
10127  }
10128  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_arguments){
10129  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_GET_ARGUMENTS, token);
10130  exp->ret_values = 1;
10131  readToken();
10132  return finishValueExpressionNoAutoCall(scope, exp, p);
10133  }
10134  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_null){
10135  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_CONST_NULL, token);
10136  exp->ret_values = 1;
10137  readToken();
10138  return finishValueExpressionNoAutoCall(scope, exp, p);
10139  }
10140  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_true){
10141  token->setFloat(1);
10142  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_CONST_TRUE, token);
10143  exp->ret_values = 1;
10144  readToken();
10145  return finishValueExpressionNoAutoCall(scope, exp, p);
10146  }
10147  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_false){
10148  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_CONST_FALSE, token);
10149  exp->ret_values = 1;
10150  readToken();
10151  return finishValueExpressionNoAutoCall(scope, exp, p);
10152  }
10153  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_extends){
10154  exp = expectExtendsExpression(scope);
10155  if(!exp){
10156  return NULL;
10157  }
10158  return finishValueExpressionNoAutoCall(scope, exp, p);
10159  }
10160  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_delete){
10161  if(!p.allow_root_blocks){
10162  setError(ERROR_NESTED_ROOT_BLOCK, token);
10163  return NULL;
10164  }
10165  return expectDeleteExpression(scope);
10166  }
10167  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_break){
10168  if(!p.allow_root_blocks){
10169  // setError(ERROR_NESTED_ROOT_BLOCK, token);
10170  // return NULL;
10171  int i = 0;
10172  }
10173  if(!scope->findLoopScope() && !scope->findSwitchScope()){
10174  setError(ERROR_EXPECT_LOOP_SCOPE, token);
10175  return NULL;
10176  }
10177  readToken();
10178  return new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_BREAK, token);
10179  }
10180  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_continue){
10181  if(!p.allow_root_blocks){
10182  // setError(ERROR_NESTED_ROOT_BLOCK, token);
10183  // return NULL;
10184  int i = 0;
10185  }
10186  if(!scope->findLoopScope()){
10187  setError(ERROR_EXPECT_LOOP_SCOPE, token);
10188  return NULL;
10189  }
10190  readToken();
10191  return new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_CONTINUE, token);
10192  }
10193  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_debugger){
10194  if(!p.allow_root_blocks){
10195  setError(ERROR_NESTED_ROOT_BLOCK, token);
10196  return NULL;
10197  }
10198  readToken();
10199  return new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_DEBUGGER, token);
10200  }
10201  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_debuglocals){
10202  exp = expectDebugLocalsExpression(scope);
10203  if(!exp){
10204  return NULL;
10205  }
10206  return finishValueExpressionNoAutoCall(scope, exp, p);
10207  }
10208  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_line){
10209  token->setFloat((OS_FLOAT)(token->line + 1));
10210  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_CONST_NUMBER, token);
10211  exp->ret_values = 1;
10212  readToken();
10213  return finishValueExpressionNoNextCall(scope, exp, p);
10214  }
10215  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_file){
10216  exp = expectFilenameExpression(scope, GET_FILENAME);
10217  return finishValueExpression(scope, exp, p);
10218  }
10219  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_dir){
10220  exp = expectFilenameExpression(scope, GET_DIRNAME);
10221  return finishValueExpression(scope, exp, p);
10222  }
10223  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_is){
10224  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, token);
10225  return NULL;
10226  }
10227  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_class){
10228  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, token);
10229  return NULL;
10230  }
10231  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_enum){
10232  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, token);
10233  return NULL;
10234  }
10235  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_switch){
10236  if(!p.allow_root_blocks){
10237  setError(ERROR_NESTED_ROOT_BLOCK, token);
10238  return NULL;
10239  }
10240  return expectSwitchExpression(scope);
10241  }
10242  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_case || token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_default){
10243  return expectCaseExpression(scope);
10244  }
10245  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_try){
10246  return expectTryExpression(scope);
10247  }
10248  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_catch){
10249  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, token);
10250  return NULL;
10251  }
10252  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_finally){
10253  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, token);
10254  return NULL;
10255  }
10256  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_throw){
10257  return expectThrowExpression(scope);
10258  }
10259  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_new){
10260  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, token);
10261  return NULL;
10262  }
10263  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_while){
10264  if(!p.allow_root_blocks){
10265  setError(ERROR_NESTED_ROOT_BLOCK, token);
10266  return NULL;
10267  }
10268  return expectWhileExpression(scope);
10269  }
10270  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_do){
10271  if(!p.allow_root_blocks){
10272  setError(ERROR_NESTED_ROOT_BLOCK, token);
10273  return NULL;
10274  }
10275  return expectDoExpression(scope);
10276  }
10277  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_const){
10278  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, token);
10279  return NULL;
10280  }
10281  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_public){
10282  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, token);
10283  return NULL;
10284  }
10285  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_protected){
10286  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, token);
10287  return NULL;
10288  }
10289  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_private){
10290  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, token);
10291  return NULL;
10292  }
10293  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_yield){
10294  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, token);
10295  return NULL;
10296  }
10297  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_static){
10298  setError(ERROR_SYNTAX, token);
10299  return NULL;
10300  }
10301  if(token->str == allocator->core->strings->syntax_super){
10302  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_SUPER, token);
10303  exp->ret_values = 1;
10304  readToken();
10305  return finishValueExpression(scope, exp, p);
10306  }
10307  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_NAME, token);
10308  exp->ret_values = 1;
10309  OS_ASSERT(scope->function);
10310  exp->active_locals = scope->function->num_locals;
10311  readToken();
10312  return finishValueExpression(scope, exp, p);
10313 
10314  case Tokenizer::OUTPUT_STRING:
10315  case Tokenizer::OUTPUT_NEXT_VALUE:
10316  {
10317  TokenData * globals_name_token = new (malloc(sizeof(TokenData) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) TokenData(tokenizer->getTextData(),
10318  allocator->core->strings->var_globals, Tokenizer::NAME, token->line, token->pos);
10319  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_NAME, globals_name_token);
10320  exp->ret_values = 1;
10321  exp->active_locals = scope->function->num_locals;
10322 
10323  TokenData * name_token = new (malloc(sizeof(TokenData) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) TokenData(tokenizer->getTextData(),
10324  allocator->core->strings->func_echo, Tokenizer::NAME, token->line, token->pos);
10325  Expression * exp2 = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_NAME, name_token);
10326  exp2->ret_values = 1;
10327  exp2->active_locals = scope->function->num_locals;
10328 
10329  exp = new (malloc(sizeof(Expression) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Expression(EXP_TYPE_INDIRECT, token, exp, exp2 OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
10330  exp->ret_values = 1;
10331 
10332  name_token->release();
10333  globals_name_token->release();
10334 
10335  if(recent_token->type == Tokenizer::OUTPUT_STRING){
10336  recent_token->type = Tokenizer::STRING;
10337  }else{
10338  recent_token->type = Tokenizer::NAME;
10339  readToken();
10340  }
10341  return finishValueExpression(scope, exp, p);
10342  }
10343  }
10344  setError(ERROR_EXPECT_EXPRESSION, token);
10345  return NULL;
10346 }
10347 
10348 void OS::Core::Compiler::debugPrintSourceLine(Buffer& out, TokenData * token)
10349 {
10350  if(!token){
10351  return;
10352  }
10353 
10354  bool filePrinted = false;
10355  if(recent_printed_text_data != token->text_data){
10356  if(recent_printed_text_data){
10357  recent_printed_text_data->release();
10358  }
10359  filePrinted = true;
10360  recent_printed_line = -1;
10361  recent_printed_text_data = token->text_data->retain();
10362  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("\n[FILE] %s"), token->text_data->filename.toChar());
10363  }
10364  if(recent_printed_line != token->line && token->line >= 0){
10365  recent_printed_line = token->line;
10366  String line(allocator, token->text_data->lines[token->line], true, true);
10367  // line could be very long so DON'T use format because of the format uses temp buffer of 10 Kb only
10368  // out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("\n[%d] %s\n\n"), token->line+1, line.toChar());
10369  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("\n[%d] "), token->line+1);
10370  out += line;
10371  out += OS_TEXT("\n\n");
10372  }
10373  else if(filePrinted){
10374  out += String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("\n"));
10375  }
10376  return;
10377 }

10379 const OS_CHAR * OS::Core::Compiler::getExpName(ExpressionType type, ECompiledValueType val_type)
10380 {
10381  switch(type){
10382  case EXP_TYPE_NOP:
10383  return OS_TEXT("nop");
10384 
10385  case EXP_TYPE_CODE_LIST:
10386  return OS_TEXT("code list");
10387 
10388  case EXP_TYPE_CONST_NUMBER:
10389  return OS_TEXT("const number");
10390 
10391  case EXP_TYPE_CONST_STRING:
10392  return OS_TEXT("const string");
10393 
10394  case EXP_TYPE_CONST_NULL:
10395  return OS_TEXT("const null");
10396 
10397  case EXP_TYPE_CONST_TRUE:
10398  return OS_TEXT("const true");
10399 
10400  case EXP_TYPE_CONST_FALSE:
10401  return OS_TEXT("const false");
10402 
10403  case EXP_TYPE_NAME:
10404  return OS_TEXT("name");
10405 
10406  case EXP_TYPE_PARAMS:
10407  return OS_TEXT("params");
10408 
10409  case EXP_TYPE_INDIRECT:
10410  return OS_TEXT("indirect");
10411 
10412  case EXP_TYPE_SET_PROPERTY:
10413  case EXP_TYPE_SET_PROPERTY_NO_POP:
10414  return OS_TEXT("set property");
10415 
10416  case EXP_TYPE_INIT_PROPERTY:
10417  return OS_TEXT("init property");
10418 
10419  case EXP_TYPE_SET_PROPERTY_BY_LOCALS_AUTO_CREATE:
10420  return OS_TEXT("set property by locals auto create");
10421 
10422  case EXP_TYPE_GET_SET_PROPERTY_BY_LOCALS_AUTO_CREATE:
10423  return OS_TEXT("get & set property by locals auto create");
10424 
10425  case EXP_TYPE_GET_PROPERTY:
10426  return OS_TEXT("get property");
10427 
10428  case EXP_TYPE_GET_THIS_PROPERTY_BY_STRING:
10429  return OS_TEXT("get this property by string");
10430 
10431  case EXP_TYPE_GET_PROPERTY_BY_LOCALS:
10432  return OS_TEXT("get property by locals");
10433 
10434  case EXP_TYPE_GET_PROPERTY_BY_LOCAL_AND_NUMBER:
10435  return OS_TEXT("get property by local & number");
10436 
10437  case EXP_TYPE_GET_PROPERTY_AUTO_CREATE:
10438  return OS_TEXT("get property auto create");
10439 
10440  case EXP_TYPE_SET_DIM:
10441  return OS_TEXT("set dim");
