10755 OS::Core::Program::Program(OS * allocator): filename(allocator)
10756 {
10757  this->allocator = allocator;
10758  ref_count = 1;
10759  const_values = NULL;
10760  num_numbers = 0;
10761  num_strings = 0;
10762 }
10763 
10764 OS::Core::Program::~Program()
10765 {
10766  OS_ASSERT(ref_count == 0);
10767  int i;
10768  for(i = 0; i < num_strings; i++){
10769  int j = i + num_numbers + CONST_STD_VALUES;
10770  OS_ASSERT(OS_VALUE_TYPE(const_values[j]) == OS_VALUE_TYPE_STRING);
10771  OS_ASSERT(dynamic_cast<GCStringValue*>(OS_VALUE_VARIANT(const_values[j]).string));
10772  GCStringValue * string = OS_VALUE_VARIANT(const_values[j]).string;
10773  OS_ASSERT(string->external_ref_count > 0);
10774  if(!--string->external_ref_count && !string->ref_count){
10775  allocator->core->saveFreeCandidateValue(string);
10776  }
10777  }
10778 
10779  allocator->free(const_values);
10780  const_values = NULL;
10781 
10782  for(i = 0; i < num_functions; i++){
10783  FunctionDecl * func = functions + i;
10784  for(int j = 0; j < func->num_locals; j++){
10785  func->locals[j].~LocalVar();
10786  }
10787  allocator->free(func->locals);
10788  func->locals = NULL;
10789  allocator->free(func->try_blocks);
10790  func->try_blocks = NULL;
10791  func->~FunctionDecl();
10792  }
10793  allocator->free(functions);
10794  functions = NULL;
10795 
10796  allocator->vectorClear(opcodes);
10797  allocator->vectorClear(debug_info);
10798 }
10799 
10800 bool OS::Core::Compiler::saveToStream(StreamWriter * writer)
10801 {
10802  writer->writeBytes(OS_COMPILED_HEADER, (int)OS_STRLEN(OS_COMPILED_HEADER));
10803 
10804  int i, len = (int)OS_STRLEN(OS_VERSION)+1;
10805  writer->writeByte(len);
10806  writer->writeBytes(OS_VERSION, len);
10807 
10808  MemStreamWriter int_stream(allocator);
10809  MemStreamWriter float_stream(allocator);
10810  MemStreamWriter double_stream(allocator);
10811  MemStreamWriter long_double_stream(allocator);
10812  int int_count = 0, float_count = 0, double_count = 0, long_double_count = 0;
10813  int int_index = 0, float_index = 0, double_index = 0, long_double_index = 0;
10814  for(i = 0; i < prog_numbers.count; i++){
10815  long double val = prog_numbers[i];
10816  if(val >= 0 && (long double)(int)val == val){
10817  int_count++;
10818  int_stream.writeUVariable(i - int_index); int_index = i;
10819  int_stream.writeUVariable((int)val);
10820  continue;
10821  }
10822  if((long double)(float)val == val){
10823  float_count++;
10824  float_stream.writeUVariable(i - float_index); float_index = i;
10825  float_stream.writeFloat((float)val);
10826  continue;
10827  }
10828  if((long double)(double)val == val){
10829  double_count++;
10830  double_stream.writeUVariable(i - double_index); double_index = i;
10831  double_stream.writeDouble((double)val);
10832  continue;
10833  }
10834  long_double_count++;
10835  long_double_stream.writeUVariable(i - long_double_index); long_double_index = i;
10836  long_double_stream.writeLongDouble(val);
10837  }
10838 
10839  writer->writeUVariable(int_count);
10840  writer->writeUVariable(float_count);
10841  writer->writeUVariable(double_count);
10842  writer->writeUVariable(long_double_count);
10843  writer->writeUVariable(prog_strings.count);
10844  writer->writeUVariable(prog_functions.count);
10845  writer->writeUVariable(prog_opcodes.count);
10846  writer->writeUVariable(prog_debug_info.count);
10847  writer->writeUVariable(prog_filename_string_index);
10848 
10849  writer->writeBytes(int_stream.buffer.buf, int_stream.buffer.count);
10850  writer->writeBytes(float_stream.buffer.buf, float_stream.buffer.count);
10851  writer->writeBytes(double_stream.buffer.buf, double_stream.buffer.count);
10852  writer->writeBytes(long_double_stream.buffer.buf, long_double_stream.buffer.count);
10853 
10854  for(i = 0; i < prog_strings.count; i++){
10855  const String& str = prog_strings[i];
10856  int data_size = str.getDataSize();
10857  writer->writeUVariable(data_size);
10858  writer->writeBytes(str.toChar(), data_size);
10859  }
10860  for(i = 0; i < prog_functions.count; i++){
10861  Compiler::Scope * func_scope = prog_functions[i];
10862  writer->writeUVariable(func_scope->parent ? func_scope->parent->func_index+1 : 0); // prog_functions.indexOf(func_scope->parent));
10863  writer->writeUVariable(func_scope->stack_size);
10864  writer->writeUVariable(func_scope->num_locals);
10865  writer->writeUVariable(func_scope->num_params);
10866  writer->writeUVariable(func_scope->max_up_count);
10867  writer->writeUVariable(func_scope->func_depth);
10868  writer->writeUVariable(func_scope->func_index);
10869  writer->writeUVariable(func_scope->num_local_funcs);
10870  writer->writeUVariable(func_scope->try_blocks.count);
10871  writer->writeUVariable(func_scope->opcodes_pos);
10872  writer->writeUVariable(func_scope->opcodes_size);
10873 
10874  OS_ASSERT(func_scope->locals_compiled.count == func_scope->num_locals);
10875  int j;
10876  for(j = 0; j < func_scope->locals_compiled.count; j++){
10877  Compiler::Scope::LocalVarCompiled& var_scope = func_scope->locals_compiled[j];
10878  OS_ASSERT(var_scope.start_code_pos >= func_scope->opcodes_pos && var_scope.start_code_pos < func_scope->opcodes_pos+func_scope->opcodes_size);
10879  OS_ASSERT(var_scope.end_code_pos > func_scope->opcodes_pos && var_scope.end_code_pos <= func_scope->opcodes_pos+func_scope->opcodes_size);
10880  writer->writeUVariable(var_scope.cached_name_index);
10881  writer->writeUVariable(var_scope.start_code_pos - func_scope->opcodes_pos);
10882  writer->writeUVariable(var_scope.end_code_pos - func_scope->opcodes_pos);
10883  writer->writeByte(var_scope.upvalue);
10884  }
10885  for(j = 0; j < func_scope->try_blocks.count; j++){
10886  Compiler::Scope::TryBlock& t = func_scope->try_blocks[j];
10887  OS_ASSERT(t.catch_var_index >= 0 && t.catch_var_index < func_scope->locals_compiled.count);
10888  OS_ASSERT(t.end_code_pos > t.start_code_pos);
10889  OS_ASSERT(t.start_code_pos >= func_scope->opcodes_pos);
10890  OS_ASSERT(t.start_code_pos <= func_scope->opcodes_pos + func_scope->opcodes_size);
10891  OS_ASSERT(t.end_code_pos >= func_scope->opcodes_pos);
10892  OS_ASSERT(t.end_code_pos <= func_scope->opcodes_pos + func_scope->opcodes_size);
10893  writer->writeUVariable(t.start_code_pos - func_scope->opcodes_pos);
10894  writer->writeUVariable(t.end_code_pos - func_scope->opcodes_pos);
10895  writer->writeUVariable(t.catch_var_index);
10896  }
10897  }
10898 
10899  for(i = 0; i < prog_opcodes.count; i++){
10900  writer->writeInt32(prog_opcodes[i]);
10901  }
10902 
10903  for(i = 0; i < prog_debug_info.count; i++){
10904  DebugInfoItem& item = prog_debug_info[i];
10905  writer->writeUVariable(item.line);
10906  writer->writeUVariable(item.pos);
10907  }
10908 
10909  return true;
10910 }
10911 
10912 bool OS::Core::Program::loadFromStream(StreamReader * reader)
10913 {
10914  OS_ASSERT(!opcodes.count && !const_values && !num_numbers && !num_strings && !debug_info.count);
10915 
10916  int i, len = (int)OS_STRLEN(OS_COMPILED_HEADER);
10917  if(!reader->checkBytes(OS_COMPILED_HEADER, len)){
10918  return false;
10919  }
10920 
10921  len = (int)OS_STRLEN(OS_VERSION)+1;
10922  reader->movePos(1);
10923  if(!reader->checkBytes(OS_VERSION, len)){
10924  return false;
10925  }
10926 
10927  int int_count = reader->readUVariable();
10928  int float_count = reader->readUVariable();
10929  int double_count = reader->readUVariable();
10930  int long_double_count = reader->readUVariable();
10931  num_numbers = int_count + float_count + double_count + long_double_count;
10932  num_strings = reader->readUVariable();
10933  num_functions = reader->readUVariable();
10934  int opcodes_size = reader->readUVariable();
10935  int num_debug_infos = reader->readUVariable();
10936  // OS_ASSERT(!num_debug_infos || num_debug_infos == opcodes_size || num_debug_infos + 1 == opcodes_size);
10937  int prog_filename_string_index = reader->readUVariable();
10938  OS_ASSERT(prog_filename_string_index >= 0 && prog_filename_string_index < num_strings);
10939 
10940  const_values = (Value*)allocator->malloc(sizeof(Value) * (num_numbers + num_strings + CONST_STD_VALUES) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
10941 
10942  const_values[CONST_NULL] = Value();
10943  const_values[CONST_TRUE] = Value(true);
10944  const_values[CONST_FALSE] = Value(false);
10945 
10946  int num_index = 0;
10947  for(i = 0; i < int_count; i++){
10948  num_index += reader->readUVariable();
10949  OS_ASSERT(num_index >= 0 && num_index < num_numbers);
10950  OS_NUMBER number = (OS_NUMBER)reader->readUVariable();
10951  const_values[num_index + CONST_STD_VALUES] = number;
10952  }
10953  for(num_index = 0, i = 0; i < float_count; i++){
10954  num_index += reader->readUVariable();
10955  OS_ASSERT(num_index >= 0 && num_index < num_numbers);
10956  OS_NUMBER number = (OS_NUMBER)reader->readFloat();
10957  const_values[num_index + CONST_STD_VALUES] = number;
10958  }
10959  for(num_index = 0, i = 0; i < double_count; i++){
10960  num_index += reader->readUVariable();
10961  OS_ASSERT(num_index >= 0 && num_index < num_numbers);
10962  OS_NUMBER number = (OS_NUMBER)reader->readDouble();
10963  const_values[num_index + CONST_STD_VALUES] = number;
10964  }
10965  for(num_index = 0, i = 0; i < long_double_count; i++){
10966  num_index += reader->readUVariable();
10967  OS_ASSERT(num_index >= 0 && num_index < num_numbers);
10968  OS_NUMBER number = (OS_NUMBER)reader->readLongDouble();
10969  const_values[num_index + CONST_STD_VALUES] = number;
10970  }
10971 
10972  Buffer buf(allocator);
10973  for(i = 0; i < num_strings; i++){
10974  int data_size = reader->readUVariable();
10975  buf.reserveCapacity(data_size);
10976  reader->readBytes(buf.buffer.buf, data_size);
10977  buf.buffer.count = data_size;
10978 
10979  GCStringValue * string = buf.toGCStringValue();
10980  string->external_ref_count++;
10981  const_values[i + num_numbers + CONST_STD_VALUES] = string;
10982  buf.freeCacheStr();
10983  }
10984  filename = String(allocator, OS_VALUE_VARIANT(const_values[prog_filename_string_index + num_numbers + CONST_STD_VALUES]).string);
10985 
10986  functions = (FunctionDecl*)allocator->malloc(sizeof(FunctionDecl) * num_functions OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
10987  for(i = 0; i < num_functions; i++){
10988  FunctionDecl * func = functions + i;
10989  new (func) FunctionDecl();
10990 #ifdef OS_DEBUG
10991  func->prog_func_index = i;
10992 #endif
10993  func->prog_parent_func_index = reader->readUVariable() - 1;
10994  func->stack_size = reader->readUVariable();
10995  func->num_locals = reader->readUVariable();
10996  func->num_params = reader->readUVariable();
10997  func->max_up_count = reader->readUVariable();
10998  func->func_depth = reader->readUVariable();
10999  func->func_index = reader->readUVariable();
11000  func->num_local_funcs = reader->readUVariable();
11001  func->num_try_blocks = reader->readUVariable();
11002  func->opcodes_pos = reader->readUVariable();
11003  func->opcodes_size = reader->readUVariable();
11004 
11005  func->locals = (FunctionDecl::LocalVar*)allocator->malloc(sizeof(FunctionDecl::LocalVar) * func->num_locals OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
11006  int j;
11007  for(j = 0; j < func->num_locals; j++){
11008  int cached_name_index = reader->readUVariable();
11009  OS_ASSERT(cached_name_index >= 0 && cached_name_index < num_strings);
11010  FunctionDecl::LocalVar * local_var = func->locals + j;
11011  OS_ASSERT(dynamic_cast<GCStringValue*>(OS_VALUE_VARIANT(const_values[cached_name_index + num_numbers + CONST_STD_VALUES]).string));
11012  String var_name(allocator, OS_VALUE_VARIANT(const_values[cached_name_index + num_numbers + CONST_STD_VALUES]).string);
11013  new (local_var) FunctionDecl::LocalVar(var_name);
11014  local_var->start_code_pos = reader->readUVariable() + func->opcodes_pos;
11015  local_var->end_code_pos = reader->readUVariable() + func->opcodes_pos;
11016  local_var->upvalue = reader->readByte() ? true : false;
11017  }
11018 
11019  func->try_blocks = (FunctionDecl::TryBlock*)allocator->malloc(sizeof(FunctionDecl::TryBlock) * func->num_try_blocks OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
11020  for(j = 0; j < func->num_try_blocks; j++){
11021  FunctionDecl::TryBlock * try_block = func->try_blocks + j;
11022  try_block->start_code_pos = reader->readUVariable() + func->opcodes_pos;
11023  try_block->end_code_pos = reader->readUVariable() + func->opcodes_pos;
11024  try_block->catch_var_index = reader->readUVariable();
11025  }
11026  }
11027 
11028  allocator->vectorReserveCapacity(opcodes, opcodes_size OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
11029  opcodes.count = opcodes_size;
11030  for(i = 0; i < opcodes_size; i++){
11031  opcodes[i] = (OS_U32)reader->readInt32();
11032  }
11033 
11034  allocator->vectorReserveCapacity(debug_info, num_debug_infos OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
11035  for(i = 0; i < num_debug_infos; i++){
11036  int line = reader->readUVariable();
11037  int pos = reader->readUVariable();
11038  allocator->vectorAddItem(debug_info, DebugInfoItem(line, pos) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
11039  }
11040 
11041  return true;
11042 }
11043 
11044 OS::Core::Program::DebugInfoItem * OS::Core::Program::getDebugInfo(int opcode_pos)
11045 {
11046  // opcode_pos is next opcode of needed
11047  opcode_pos--;
11048  if(opcode_pos >= 0 && opcode_pos < debug_info.count){
11049  return &debug_info[opcode_pos];
11050  }
11051  return NULL;
11052 }

11060 void OS::Core::Program::pushStartFunction()
11061 {
11062  int opcode = opcodes[0];
11063  if(OS_GET_OPCODE_TYPE(opcode) != OP_NEW_FUNCTION){
11064  OS_ASSERT(false);
11065  allocator->pushNull();
11066  return;
11067  }
11068 
11069  int prog_func_index = OS_GETARG_B(opcode);
11070  OS_ASSERT(prog_func_index == 0 && !OS_GETARG_A(opcode));
11071  FunctionDecl * func_decl = functions + prog_func_index;
11072  OS_ASSERT(func_decl->max_up_count == 0);
11073 
11074  GCFunctionValue * func_value = allocator->core->pushFunctionValue(NULL, this, func_decl, allocator->core->global_vars, Value());
11075  // allocator->core->pushValue(func_value);
11076  if(!filename.isEmpty()){
11077  allocator->core->setValue(func_value->name, allocator->core->strings->func_main.string);
11078  }else{
11079  allocator->core->setValue(func_value->name, allocator->core->strings->func_core.string);
11080  }
11081  // func_value->name->external_ref_count++;
11082  // allocator->core->gcMarkProgram(this);
11083 }
11084 
11085 OS::Core::Program * OS::Core::Program::retain()
11086 {
11087  ref_count++;
11088  return this;
11089 }
11090 
11091 void OS::Core::Program::release()
11092 {
11093  if(--ref_count <= 0){
11094  OS_ASSERT(ref_count == 0);
11095  OS * allocator = this->allocator;
11096  this->~Program();
11097  allocator->free(this);
11098  }
11099 }
11100 
11101 OS::Core::OpcodeType OS::Core::Program::getOpcodeType(Compiler::ExpressionType exp_type, Compiler::ECompiledValueType value_type)
11102 {
11103  struct Lib {
11104  static OpcodeType get(Compiler::ECompiledValueType value_type, OpcodeType num_type, OpcodeType type)
11105  {
11106  if(value_type == Compiler::CVT_NUMBER){
11107  return num_type;
11108  }
11109  return type;
11110  }
11111  };
11112 
11113  switch(exp_type){
11114  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_CALL: return OP_CALL;
11115  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_CALL_AUTO_PARAM: return OP_CALL;
11116  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_CALL_METHOD: return OP_CALL_METHOD;
11117 #ifdef OS_TAIL_CALL_ENABLED
11118  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_TAIL_CALL: return OP_TAIL_CALL;
11119  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_TAIL_CALL_METHOD: return OP_TAIL_CALL_METHOD;
11120 #endif
11121  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_SUPER_CALL: return OP_SUPER_CALL;
11122  // case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_SUPER: return OP_SUPER;
11123  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_INIT_ITER: return OP_INIT_ITER;
11124 
11125  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_GET_PROPERTY: return OP_GET_PROPERTY;
11126  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_SET_PROPERTY: return OP_SET_PROPERTY;
11127  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_INIT_PROPERTY: return OP_INIT_PROPERTY;
11128  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_SET_PROPERTY_NO_POP: return OP_SET_PROPERTY;
11129 
11130  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_GET_UPVALUE: return OP_GET_UPVALUE;
11131  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_SET_UPVALUE: return OP_SET_UPVALUE;
11132  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_SET_UPVALUE_NO_POP: return OP_SET_UPVALUE;
11133 
11134  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_MOVE: return OP_MOVE;
11135  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_RETURN: return OP_RETURN;
11136 
11137  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_BIT_NOT: return OP_BIT_NOT;
11138  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_PLUS: return OP_PLUS;
11139  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_MINUS: return OP_MINUS;
11140 
11141  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_BIT_AND: return Lib::get(value_type, OP_NUMBER_BIT_AND, OP_BIT_AND);
11142  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_BIT_OR: return Lib::get(value_type, OP_NUMBER_BIT_OR, OP_BIT_OR);
11143  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_BIT_XOR: return Lib::get(value_type, OP_NUMBER_BIT_XOR, OP_BIT_XOR);
11144 
11145  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_COMPARE: return Lib::get(value_type, OP_NUMBER_SUB, OP_COMPARE);
11146  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_ADD: return Lib::get(value_type, OP_NUMBER_ADD, OP_ADD);
11147  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_SUB: return Lib::get(value_type, OP_NUMBER_SUB, OP_SUB);
11148  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_MUL: return Lib::get(value_type, OP_NUMBER_MUL, OP_MUL);
11149  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_DIV: return Lib::get(value_type, OP_NUMBER_DIV, OP_DIV);
11150  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_MOD: return Lib::get(value_type, OP_NUMBER_MOD, OP_MOD);
11151  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_LSHIFT: return Lib::get(value_type, OP_NUMBER_LSHIFT, OP_LSHIFT);
11152  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_RSHIFT: return Lib::get(value_type, OP_NUMBER_RSHIFT, OP_RSHIFT);
11153  case Compiler::EXP_TYPE_POW: return Lib::get(value_type, OP_NUMBER_POW, OP_POW);
11154  }
11155  OS_ASSERT(false);
11156  return OP_ADD;
11157 }

11172 void OS::Core::StreamWriter::writeFromStream(StreamReader * reader)
11173 {
11174  int size = reader->getSize() - reader->getPos();
11175  int buf_size = 1024 * 128;
11176  void * buf = allocator->malloc(buf_size < size ? buf_size : size OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
11177  OS_ASSERT(buf || !size);
11178  for(; size > 0; size -= buf_size){
11179  int chunk_size = buf_size <= size ? buf_size : size;
11180  reader->readBytes(buf, chunk_size);
11181  writeBytes(buf, chunk_size);
11182  }
11183  allocator->free(buf);
11184 }

11200 void OS::Core::StreamWriter::writeUVariable(int value)
11201 {
11202  OS_ASSERT(value >= 0);
11203  for(;;){
11204  if(value >= 0x7f){
11205  writeByte((value & 0x7f) | 0x80);
11206  value >>= 7;
11207  }else{
11208  writeByte(value);
11209  return;
11210  }
11211  }
11212 }

11351 void OS::Core::MemStreamWriter::reserveCapacity(int new_capacity)
11352 {
11353  if(buffer.capacity < new_capacity){
11354  buffer.capacity = buffer.capacity > 0 ? buffer.capacity*2 : 4;
11355  if(buffer.capacity < new_capacity){
11356  buffer.capacity = new_capacity; // (capacity+3) & ~3;
11357  }
11358  OS_BYTE * new_buf = (OS_BYTE*)allocator->malloc(sizeof(OS_BYTE)*buffer.capacity OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
11359  OS_ASSERT(new_buf);
11360  OS_MEMCPY(new_buf, buffer.buf, sizeof(OS_BYTE) * buffer.count);
11361  allocator->free(buffer.buf);
11362  buffer.buf = new_buf;
11363  }
11364 }
11365 
11366 void OS::Core::MemStreamWriter::writeBytes(const void * buf, int len)
11367 {
11368  reserveCapacity(pos + len);
11369  int save_pos = pos;
11370  pos += len;
11371  if(buffer.count <= pos){
11372  buffer.count = pos;
11373  }
11374  writeBytesAtPos(buf, len, save_pos);
11375 }
11376 
11377 void OS::Core::MemStreamWriter::writeBytesAtPos(const void * buf, int len, int pos)
11378 {
11379  OS_ASSERT(pos >= 0 && pos <= buffer.count-len);
11380  OS_MEMCPY(buffer.buf+pos, buf, len);
11381 }
11382 
11383 void OS::Core::MemStreamWriter::writeByte(int value)
11384 {
11385  OS_ASSERT(value >= 0 && value <= 0xff);
11386  if(pos < buffer.count){
11387  OS_ASSERT(pos >= 0);
11388  buffer[pos++] = (OS_BYTE)value;
11389  }else{
11390  allocator->vectorAddItem(buffer, (OS_BYTE)value OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
11391  pos++;
11392  }
11393 }
11394 
11395 void OS::Core::MemStreamWriter::writeByteAtPos(int value, int pos)
11396 {
11397  OS_ASSERT(value >= 0 && value <= 0xff);
11398  OS_ASSERT(pos >= 0 && pos <= buffer.count-1);
11399  buffer[pos] = (OS_BYTE)value;
11400 }

11477 int OS::Core::StreamReader::readUVariable()
11478 {
11479  int value = readByte();
11480  if(!(value & 0x80)){
11481  return value;
11482  }
11483  value &= 0x7f;
11484  for(int i = 7;; i += 7){
11485  int b = readByte();
11486  if(b & 0x80){
11487  value |= (b & 0x7f) << i;
11488  }else{
11489  OS_ASSERT((value | (b << i)) >= 0);
11490  return value | (b << i);
11491  }
11492  }
11493  return 0; // shut up compiler
11494 }

11499  readBytes(&le_value, sizeof(le_value));

11501 }

11594 long double OS::Core::StreamReader::readLongDouble()

11792  && (!size2 || OS_MEMCMP(src + size1, buf2, size2) == 0);

11805 bool OS::Core::isEqual(const Value& index, int hash, const void * buf1, int size1, const void * buf2, int size2)

11808  int src_size = OS_VALUE_VARIANT(index).string->data_size;
11809  if(OS_VALUE_VARIANT(index).string->hash != hash || src_size != size1 + size2){
11810  return false;
11811  }

11813  return Utils::cmp(src, size1, buf1, size1) == 0

11819 template <class T> int getNumberHash(T val)
11820 {
11821  return (int)val;
11822 }
11823 template <> int getNumberHash<double>(double val)
11824 {
11825  float t = (float)val;
11826  return *(int*)&t;
11827 }
11828 template <> int getNumberHash<float>(float t)
11829 {
11830  return *(int*)&t;
11831 }
11832 template <> int getNumberHash<int>(int t)
11833 {
11834  return t;
11835 }
11836 
11837 #define OS_CALC_VALUE_HASH(_value, _type) \
11838  do { \
11839  OS_ASSERT(OS_VALUE_TYPE(_value) == (_type)); \
11840  switch(_type){ \
11841  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_NULL: \
11842  hash = 0; \
11843  break; \
11844  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_BOOL: \
11845  hash = OS_VALUE_VARIANT(_value).boolean; \
11846  break; \
11847  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_NUMBER: \
11848  float d = (float)OS_VALUE_NUMBER(_value); \
11849  OS_BYTE * buf = (OS_BYTE*)&d; \
11850  hash = OS_STR_HASH_START_VALUE; \
11851  OS_ADD_STR_HASH_VALUE; buf++; \
11852  OS_ADD_STR_HASH_VALUE; buf++; \
11853  OS_ADD_STR_HASH_VALUE; buf++; \
11854  OS_ADD_STR_HASH_VALUE; \
11855  break; \
11856  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_STRING: \
11857  hash = OS_VALUE_VARIANT(_value).string->hash; \
11858  break; \
11859  default: \
11860  /* all other values share same area with index.v.value so just use it as hash */ \
11861  hash = OS_PTR_HASH(OS_VALUE_VARIANT(_value).value); \
11862  break; \
11863  } \
11864  } while(false)
11865

11867 int OS::Core::getValueHash(const Value& index, int type)
11868 {
11869  OS_ASSERT(OS_VALUE_TYPE(index) == type);
11870 #if 000
11871  int hash;
11872  OS_CALC_VALUE_HASH(index, type);
11873  return hash;
11874 #else
11875  switch(type){
11876  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_NULL:
11877  return 0;
11878 
11879  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_BOOL:
11880  return OS_VALUE_VARIANT(index).boolean;
11881 
11882  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_NUMBER:
11883  {
11884 #if 0 // calculate hash accuratelly
11885  int i; OS_NUMBER_TO_INT(i, OS_VALUE_NUMBER(index));
11886  return i;
11887 #elif 1 // it's really faster
11888  float d = (float)OS_VALUE_NUMBER(index);
11889  OS_ASSERT(sizeof(d) == 4);
11890  OS_BYTE * buf = (OS_BYTE*)&d;
11891  int hash = OS_STR_HASH_START_VALUE;
11892  OS_ADD_STR_HASH_VALUE; buf++;
11893  OS_ADD_STR_HASH_VALUE; buf++;
11894  OS_ADD_STR_HASH_VALUE; buf++;
11895  OS_ADD_STR_HASH_VALUE;
11896  return hash;
11897 /*
11898 inline std::size_t float_hash_value(T v)
11899  {
11900  using namespace std;
11901  switch (fpclassify(v)) {
11902  case FP_ZERO:
11903  return 0;
11904  case FP_INFINITE:
11905  return (std::size_t)(v > 0 ? -1 : -2);
11906  case FP_NAN:
11907  return (std::size_t)(-3);
11908  case FP_NORMAL:
11909  case FP_SUBNORMAL:
11910  return float_hash_impl(v);
11911  default:
11912  BOOST_ASSERT(0);
11913  return 0;
11914  }
11915  }
11916 */
11917 #else
11918  union {
11919  double d;
11920  OS_INT32 p[2];
11921  } u;
11922  u.d = (double)OS_VALUE_NUMBER(index); // + 1.0f;
11923  return u.p[0] + u.p[1];
11924 #endif
11925  }
11926 
11927  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_STRING:
11928  return OS_VALUE_VARIANT(index).string->hash;
11929  }
11930  // all other values share same area with index.v.value so just use it as hash
11931  return OS_PTR_HASH(OS_VALUE_VARIANT(index).value);
11932 #endif
11933 }

12004 void OS::Core::Table::removeIterator(IteratorState * iter)
12005 {
12006  OS_ASSERT(containsIterator(iter));
12007  IteratorState * prev = NULL;
12008  for(IteratorState * cur = iterators; cur; prev = cur, cur = cur->next){
12009  if(cur == iter){
12010  if(!prev){
12011  iterators = cur->next;
12012  }else{
12013  prev->next = cur->next;
12014  }
12015  cur->table = NULL;
12016  cur->next = NULL;
12017  cur->prop = NULL;
12018  return;
12019  }
12020  }

12029 void OS::Core::clearTable(Table * table)

12033

12035  table->first = NULL;
12036  table->last = NULL;

12039  prev = prop->prev;
12040  prop->hash_next = NULL;
12041  prop->prev = NULL;
12042  prop->next = NULL;
12043  releaseValue(prop->index);
12044  releaseValue(prop->value);
12045  prop->~Property();

12047  }
12048

12050  table->removeIterator(table->iterators);
12051  }
12052 
12053  // OS_ASSERT(table->count == 0 && !table->first && !table->last);
12054  free(table->heads);

12068 OS::Core::Property * OS::Core::addTableProperty(Table * table, const Value& index, const Value& value)
12069 {
12070  OS_ASSERT(!table->get(index, OS_VALUE_TYPE(index)));
12071 
12072  Property * prop = new (malloc(sizeof(Property) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Property(index, value);
12073  OS_ASSERT(prop->next == NULL);
12074 
12075  retainValue(prop->index);
12076  retainValue(prop->value);
12077 
12078  if((table->count>>HASH_GROW_SHIFT) >= table->head_mask){
12079  int new_size = table->heads ? (table->head_mask+1) * 2 : 4;
12080  int alloc_size = sizeof(Property*)*new_size;
12081  Property ** new_heads = (Property**)malloc(alloc_size OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
12082  OS_ASSERT(new_heads);
12083  OS_MEMSET(new_heads, 0, alloc_size);
12084 
12085  Property ** old_heads = table->heads;
12086  table->heads = new_heads;
12087  table->head_mask = new_size-1;
12088 
12089  for(Property * cur = table->first; cur; cur = cur->next){
12090  int type = OS_VALUE_TYPE(cur->index);
12091 #if 000
12092  int hash;
12093  OS_CALC_VALUE_HASH(cur->index, type);
12094  int slot = hash & table->head_mask;
12095 #else
12096  int slot = getValueHash(cur->index, type) & table->head_mask;
12097 #endif
12098  cur->hash_next = table->heads[slot];
12099  table->heads[slot] = cur;
12100  }
12101 
12102  // delete [] old_heads;
12103  free(old_heads);
12104  }
12105 
12106  int type = OS_VALUE_TYPE(prop->index);
12107 #if 000
12108  int hash;
12109  OS_CALC_VALUE_HASH(prop->index, type);
12110  int slot = hash & table->head_mask;
12111 #else
12112  int slot = getValueHash(prop->index, type) & table->head_mask;
12113 #endif
12114  prop->hash_next = table->heads[slot];
12115  table->heads[slot] = prop;
12116 
12117  if(!table->first){
12118  table->first = prop;
12119  }else{
12120  OS_ASSERT(table->last);
12121  table->last->next = prop;
12122  prop->prev = table->last;
12123  }
12124  table->last = prop;
12125 
12126  if(type == OS_VALUE_TYPE_NUMBER && table->next_index <= OS_VALUE_NUMBER(prop->index)){
12127  table->next_index = (OS_INT) OS_VALUE_NUMBER(prop->index) + 1;
12128  }
12129 
12130  table->count++;
12131 
12132  return prop;
12133 }

12135 void OS::Core::changePropertyIndex(Table * table, Property * prop, const Value& new_index)
12136 {
12137  int type = OS_VALUE_TYPE(prop->index);
12138 #if 000
12139  int hash;
12140  OS_CALC_VALUE_HASH(prop->index, type);
12141  int slot = hash & table->head_mask;
12142 #else
12143  int slot = getValueHash(prop->index, type) & table->head_mask;
12144 #endif
12145  Property * cur = table->heads[slot], * chain_prev = NULL;
12146  for(; cur; chain_prev = cur, cur = cur->hash_next){
12147  if(cur == prop){ // cur->isEqual(index)){
12148  if(chain_prev){
12149  chain_prev->hash_next = cur->hash_next;
12150  }else{
12151  table->heads[slot] = cur->hash_next;
12152  }
12153  break;
12154  }
12155  }
12156  OS_ASSERT(cur && cur == prop);
12157  if(cur){
12158  // *prop = new_index;
12159  setValue(prop->index, new_index);
12160 
12161 #if 000
12162  OS_CALC_VALUE_HASH(prop->index, type);
12163  slot = hash & table->head_mask;
12164 #else
12165  slot = getValueHash(prop->index, type) & table->head_mask;
12166 #endif
12167  prop->hash_next = table->heads[slot];
12168  table->heads[slot] = prop;
12169 
12170  if(type == OS_VALUE_TYPE_NUMBER && table->next_index <= OS_VALUE_NUMBER(prop->index)){
12171  table->next_index = (OS_INT)OS_VALUE_NUMBER(prop->index) + 1;
12172  }
12173  }
12174 }

12176 // performance optimization
12177 #define OS_EQUAL_EXACTLY(temp, left_value, right_value) \
12178  ((temp = OS_VALUE_TYPE(left_value)) == OS_VALUE_TYPE(right_value) \
12179  && (temp == OS_VALUE_TYPE_NUMBER ? OS_VALUE_NUMBER(left_value) == OS_VALUE_NUMBER(right_value) \
12180  : temp == OS_VALUE_TYPE_BOOL ? OS_VALUE_VARIANT(left_value).boolean == OS_VALUE_VARIANT(right_value).boolean \
12181  : temp == OS_VALUE_TYPE_NULL ? true \
12182  : OS_VALUE_VARIANT(left_value).value == OS_VALUE_VARIANT(right_value).value))
12183 
12184 #ifdef OS_DEBUG
12185 int OS::Core::checkSavedType(int type, const Value& value)
12186 {
12187  OS_ASSERT(type == OS_VALUE_TYPE(value));
12188  return type;
12189 }
12190 #else
12191 #define checkSavedType(type, value) (type)
12192 #endif
12193 
12194 #define OS_EQUAL_EXACTLY_BY_SAVED_TYPE(temp, left_value, right_value) \
12195  (checkSavedType(temp, left_value) == OS_VALUE_TYPE(right_value) \
12196  && (temp == OS_VALUE_TYPE_NUMBER ? OS_VALUE_NUMBER(left_value) == OS_VALUE_NUMBER(right_value) \
12197  : temp == OS_VALUE_TYPE_BOOL ? OS_VALUE_VARIANT(left_value).boolean == OS_VALUE_VARIANT(right_value).boolean \
12198  : temp == OS_VALUE_TYPE_NULL ? true \
12199  : OS_VALUE_VARIANT(left_value).value == OS_VALUE_VARIANT(right_value).value))

12201 bool OS::Core::deleteTableProperty(Table * table, const Value& index)
12202 {
12203  OS_ASSERT(table);
12204  int type = OS_VALUE_TYPE(index);
12205 #if 000
12206  int hash;
12207  OS_CALC_VALUE_HASH(index, type);
12208  int slot = hash & table->head_mask;
12209 #else
12210  int slot = getValueHash(index, type) & table->head_mask;
12211 #endif
12212  Property * cur = table->heads[slot], * chain_prev = NULL;
12213  for(; cur; chain_prev = cur, cur = cur->hash_next){
12214  // if(isEqualExactly(cur->index, index)){
12215  // performance optimization
12216  if(OS_EQUAL_EXACTLY_BY_SAVED_TYPE(type, index, cur->index)){
12217  if(table->first == cur){
12218  table->first = cur->next;
12219  if(table->first){
12220  table->first->prev = NULL;
12221  }
12222  }else{
12223  OS_ASSERT(cur->prev);
12224  cur->prev->next = cur->next;
12225  }
12226 
12227  if(table->last == cur){
12228  table->last = cur->prev;
12229  if(table->last){
12230  table->last->next = NULL;
12231  }
12232  }else{
12233  OS_ASSERT(cur->next);
12234  cur->next->prev = cur->prev;
12235  }
12236 
12237  if(chain_prev){
12238  chain_prev->hash_next = cur->hash_next;
12239  }else{
12240  table->heads[slot] = cur->hash_next;
12241  }
12242 
12243  for(Table::IteratorState * iter = table->iterators; iter; iter = iter->next){
12244  if(iter->prop == cur){
12245  iter->prop = iter->ascending ? cur->next : cur->prev;
12246  }
12247  }
12248 
12249  cur->next = NULL;
12250  cur->prev = NULL;
12251  cur->hash_next = NULL;
12252  // cur->value.clear();
12253 
12254  releaseValue(cur->index);
12255  releaseValue(cur->value);
12256 
12257  table->count--;
12258 
12259  cur->~Property();
12260  free(cur);
12261  return true;
12262  }
12263  }
12264  return false;
12265 }
12266 
12267 void OS::Core::deleteValueProperty(GCValue * table_value, Value index, bool del_enabled, bool prototype_enabled)
12268 {
12269  int index_type = OS_VALUE_TYPE(index);
12270  if(table_value->type == OS_VALUE_TYPE_ARRAY && index_type == OS_VALUE_TYPE_NUMBER){
12271  OS_ASSERT(dynamic_cast<GCArrayValue*>(table_value));
12272  GCArrayValue * arr = (GCArrayValue*)table_value;
12273  int i; OS_NUMBER_TO_INT(i, OS_VALUE_NUMBER(index)); // = (int)valueToInt(index);
12274  if((i >= 0 || (i += arr->values.count) >= 0) && i < arr->values.count){
12275  releaseValue(arr->values.buf[i]);
12276  allocator->vectorRemoveAtIndex(arr->values, i);
12277  }
12278  return;
12279  }
12280  Table * table = table_value->table;
12281  if(table && deleteTableProperty(table, index)){
12282  return;
12283  }
12284  if(1){ // prototype_enabled){
12285  GCValue * cur_value = table_value;
12286  while(cur_value->prototype){
12287  cur_value = cur_value->prototype;
12288  Table * cur_table = cur_value->table;
12289  if(!cur_table){
12290  continue;
12291  }
12292  if(prototype_enabled){
12293  if(cur_table && deleteTableProperty(cur_table, index)){
12294  return;
12295  }
12296  }else{
12297  if(cur_table && cur_table->get(index, index_type)){
12298  return;
12299  }
12300  }
12301  }
12302  }
12303  if(OS_VALUE_TYPE(index) == OS_VALUE_TYPE_STRING && strings->syntax_prototype == OS_VALUE_VARIANT(index).string){
12304  return;
12305  }
12306  if(del_enabled /*&& !hasSpecialPrefix(index)*/){
12307  Value value;
12308  bool prototype_enabled = true;
12309  if(OS_VALUE_TYPE(index) == OS_VALUE_TYPE_STRING){
12310  const void * buf1 = strings->__delAt.toChar();
12311  int size1 = strings->__delAt.getDataSize();
12312  const void * buf2 = OS_VALUE_VARIANT(index).string->toChar();
12313  int size2 = OS_VALUE_VARIANT(index).string->getDataSize();
12314  GCStringValue * del_name = pushStringValue(buf1, size1, buf2, size2);
12315  if(getPropertyValue(value, table_value, del_name, prototype_enabled)){
12316  pop(); // del_name
12317  pushValue(value);
12318  pushValue(table_value);
12319  pushValue(index);
12320  callFT(1, 0, OS_CALLTYPE_FUNC);
12321  return;
12322  }
12323  pop(); // del_name
12324 
12325  buf1 = strings->__getAt.toChar();
12326  size1 = strings->__getAt.getDataSize();
12327  GCStringValue * getter_name = pushStringValue(buf1, size1, buf2, size2);
12328  if(getPropertyValue(value, table_value, getter_name, prototype_enabled)){
12329  pop();
12330  allocator->setException(String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%s is readonly property, you should not delete the one"), valueToString(index).toChar()));
12331  return;
12332  }
12333  pop();
12334  }
12335  if(getPropertyValue(value, table_value, strings->__del, prototype_enabled)){
12336  pushValue(value);
12337  pushValue(table_value);
12338  pushValue(index);
12339  callFT(1, 0, OS_CALLTYPE_FUNC);
12340  }
12341  }
12342 }
12343 
12344 void OS::Core::deleteValueProperty(const Value& table_value, const Value& index, bool del_enabled, bool prototype_enabled)
12345 {
12346  switch(OS_VALUE_TYPE(table_value)){
12347  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_NULL:
12348  return;
12349 
12350  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_BOOL:
12351  if(prototype_enabled){
12352  return deleteValueProperty(prototypes[PROTOTYPE_BOOL], index, del_enabled, prototype_enabled);
12353  }
12354  return;
12355 
12356  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_NUMBER:
12357  if(prototype_enabled){
12358  return deleteValueProperty(prototypes[PROTOTYPE_NUMBER], index, del_enabled, prototype_enabled);
12359  }
12360  return;
12361 
12362  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_STRING:
12363  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_ARRAY:
12364  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_OBJECT:
12365  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_USERDATA:
12366  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_USERPTR:
12367  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_FUNCTION:
12368  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_CFUNCTION:
12369  return deleteValueProperty(OS_VALUE_VARIANT(table_value).value, index, del_enabled, prototype_enabled);
12370  }
12371 }

12389 void OS::Core::sortTable(Table * table, int(*comp)(OS*, const void*, const void*, void*), void * user_param, bool reorder_keys)
12390 {
12391  if(table->count > 1){
12392  Property ** props = (Property**)malloc(sizeof(Property*) * table->count OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
12393  int i = 0;
12394  Property * cur = table->first;
12395  for(; cur; cur = cur->next, i++){
12396  OS_ASSERT(i < table->count);
12397  props[i] = cur;
12398  }
12399  OS_ASSERT(!cur && i == table->count);
12400  allocator->qsort(props, table->count, sizeof(Core::Property*), comp, user_param);
12401  table->first = props[0];
12402  props[0]->prev = NULL;
12403  for(i = 1; i < table->count; i++){
12404  props[i-1]->next = props[i];
12405  props[i]->prev = props[i-1];
12406  }
12407  props[i-1]->next = NULL;
12408  table->last = props[i-1];
12409 
12410  if(reorder_keys){
12411 #if 1 // performance optimization
12412  OS_MEMSET(table->heads, 0, sizeof(Property*)*(table->head_mask+1));
12413  for(i = 0; i < table->count; i++){
12414  Property * cur = props[i];
12415  setValue(cur->index, Value(i));
12416  int type = OS_VALUE_TYPE(cur->index);
12417 #if 000
12418  int hash;
12419  OS_CALC_VALUE_HASH(cur->index, type);
12420  int slot = hash & table->head_mask;
12421 #else
12422  int slot = getValueHash(cur->index, type) & table->head_mask;
12423 #endif
12424  cur->hash_next = table->heads[slot];
12425  table->heads[slot] = cur;
12426  }
12427 #else
12428  for(i = 0; i < table->count; i++){
12429  changePropertyIndex(table, props[i], Value(i));
12430  }
12431 #endif
12432  table->next_index = table->count;
12433  }
12434 
12435  free(props);
12436  }
12437 }
12438 
12439 void OS::Core::sortArray(GCArrayValue * arr, int(*comp)(OS*, const void*, const void*, void*), void * user_param)
12440 {
12441  allocator->qsort(arr->values.buf, arr->values.count, sizeof(Value), comp, user_param);
12442 }

12564 OS::Core::Property * OS::Core::Table::get(const Value& index, int type)
12565 {
12566  if(heads){
12567  OS_ASSERT(OS_VALUE_TYPE(index) == type);
12568 #if 000
12569  int hash;
12570  OS_CALC_VALUE_HASH(index, type);
12571  Property * cur = heads[hash & head_mask];
12572 #else
12573  Property * cur = heads[getValueHash(index, type) & head_mask];
12574 #endif
12575  for(; cur; cur = cur->hash_next){
12576  if(OS_EQUAL_EXACTLY_BY_SAVED_TYPE(type, index, cur->index)){
12577  return cur;
12578  }
12579  }
12580  }
12581  return NULL;
12582 }

12602 OS::Core::GCFunctionValue * OS::Core::pushFunctionValue(StackFunction * stack_func, Program * prog, FunctionDecl * func_decl, Value env, Value self)
12603 {
12604  GCFunctionValue * func_value = new (allocator->malloc(sizeof(GCFunctionValue) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) GCFunctionValue();
12605  func_value->type = OS_VALUE_TYPE_FUNCTION;
12606  retainValue(func_value->prototype = pushObjectValue(prototypes[PROTOTYPE_FUNCTION])); pop();
12607  // func_value->prototype->ref_count++;
12608  func_value->prog = prog->retain();
12609  func_value->func_decl = func_decl;
12610  setValue(func_value->env, env); // global_vars;
12611  setValue(func_value->self, self); // 'this' where function has been created
12612  func_value->locals = stack_func ? stack_func->locals->retain() : NULL;
12613  registerValueAndPush(func_value);
12614  return func_value;
12615 }

12620

12623  func_value->locals = NULL;
12624  }

12626  releaseValueAndClear(func_value->self); // = (GCValue*)NULL;
12627  OS_ASSERT(func_value->func_decl);
12628 
12629  releaseValueAndClear(func_value->name);
12630  releaseValueAndClear(func_value->prototype);
12631 
12632  func_value->func_decl = NULL;
12633 
12634  func_value->prog->release();
12635  func_value->prog = NULL;

12638  // free(func_value);

12856 OS::Core::GCStringValue * OS::Core::GCStringValue::allocAndPush(OS * allocator, int p_hash, const void * buf, int data_size OS_DBG_FILEPOS_DECL)
12857 {
12858  OS_ASSERT(data_size >= 0);
12859  if(data_size < 0) data_size = 0;
12860  int alloc_size = data_size + sizeof(GCStringValue) + sizeof(wchar_t) + sizeof(wchar_t)/2;
12861  GCStringValue * string = new (allocator->malloc(alloc_size OS_DBG_FILEPOS_PARAM)) GCStringValue(data_size);
12862  string->type = OS_VALUE_TYPE_STRING;
12863  allocator->core->retainValue(string->prototype = allocator->core->prototypes[PROTOTYPE_STRING]);
12864  // string->prototype->ref_count++;
12865  OS_BYTE * data_buf = string->toBytes();
12866  OS_MEMCPY(data_buf, buf, data_size);
12867  OS_MEMSET(data_buf + data_size, 0, sizeof(wchar_t) + sizeof(wchar_t)/2);
12868  if(p_hash){
12869  OS_ASSERT(p_hash == Utils::keyToHash(string->toBytes(), string->data_size));
12870  string->hash = p_hash;
12871  }else{
12872  string->calcHash();
12873  }
12874  allocator->core->registerValueAndPush(string);
12875  allocator->core->registerStringRef(string);
12876 #ifdef OS_DEBUG
12877  string->str = string->toChar();
12878 #endif
12879  return string;
12880 }
12881 
12882 OS::Core::GCStringValue * OS::Core::GCStringValue::allocAndPush(OS * allocator, int p_hash, const void * buf1, int len1, const void * buf2, int len2 OS_DBG_FILEPOS_DECL)
12883 {
12884  OS_ASSERT(len1 >= 0 && len2 >= 0);
12885  if(len1 < 0) len1 = 0;
12886  if(len2 < 0) len2 = 0;
12887  int alloc_size = len1 + len2 + sizeof(GCStringValue) + sizeof(wchar_t) + sizeof(wchar_t)/2;
12888  GCStringValue * string = new (allocator->malloc(alloc_size OS_DBG_FILEPOS_PARAM)) GCStringValue(len1 + len2);
12889  string->type = OS_VALUE_TYPE_STRING;
12890  allocator->core->retainValue(string->prototype = allocator->core->prototypes[PROTOTYPE_STRING]);
12891  // string->prototype->ref_count++;
12892  OS_BYTE * data_buf = string->toBytes();
12893  OS_MEMCPY(data_buf, buf1, len1); data_buf += len1;
12894  if(len2){ OS_MEMCPY(data_buf, buf2, len2); data_buf += len2; }
12895  OS_MEMSET(data_buf, 0, sizeof(wchar_t) + sizeof(wchar_t)/2);
12896  if(p_hash){
12897  OS_ASSERT(p_hash == Utils::keyToHash(string->toBytes(), string->data_size));
12898  string->hash = p_hash;
12899  }else{
12900  string->calcHash();
12901  }
12902  allocator->core->registerValueAndPush(string);
12903  allocator->core->registerStringRef(string);
12904 #ifdef OS_DEBUG
12905  string->str = string->toChar();
12906 #endif
12907  return string;
12908 }
12909 
12910 OS::Core::GCStringValue * OS::Core::GCStringValue::allocAndPush(OS * allocator, GCStringValue * a, GCStringValue * b OS_DBG_FILEPOS_DECL)
12911 {
12912  return allocAndPush(allocator, 0, a->toMemory(), a->data_size, b->toMemory(), b->data_size OS_DBG_FILEPOS_PARAM);
12913 }

12915 bool OS::Core::GCStringValue::isNumber(OS_NUMBER* p_val) const
12916 {
12917  const OS_CHAR * str = toChar();
12918  const OS_CHAR * end = str + getLen();
12919  OS_FLOAT val;
12920  if(Utils::parseFloat(str, val, Utils::PARSE_FLOAT) && (str == end || (*str==OS_TEXT('f') && str+1 == end))){
12921  if(p_val) *p_val = (OS_NUMBER)val;
12922  return true;
12923  }
12924  if(p_val) *p_val = 0;
12925  return false;
12926 }

13282 void OS::Core::registerStringRef(GCStringValue * str_ref)
13283 {
13284  if((string_refs.count>>HASH_GROW_SHIFT) >= string_refs.head_mask){
13285  int new_size = string_refs.heads ? (string_refs.head_mask+1) * 2 : 32;
13286  int alloc_size = sizeof(GCStringValue*) * new_size;
13287  GCStringValue ** new_heads = (GCStringValue**)malloc(alloc_size OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
13288  OS_ASSERT(new_heads);
13289  OS_MEMSET(new_heads, 0, alloc_size);
13290 
13291  GCStringValue ** old_heads = string_refs.heads;
13292  int old_mask = string_refs.head_mask;
13293 
13294  string_refs.heads = new_heads;
13295  string_refs.head_mask = new_size-1;
13296 
13297  if(old_heads){
13298  for(int i = 0; i <= old_mask; i++){
13299  for(GCStringValue * str_ref = old_heads[i], * next; str_ref; str_ref = next){
13300  next = str_ref->hash_next_ref;
13301  int slot = str_ref->hash & string_refs.head_mask;
13302  str_ref->hash_next_ref = string_refs.heads[slot];
13303  string_refs.heads[slot] = str_ref;
13304  }
13305  }
13306  free(old_heads);
13307  }
13308  }
13309 
13310  int slot = str_ref->hash & string_refs.head_mask;
13311  str_ref->hash_next_ref = string_refs.heads[slot];
13312  string_refs.heads[slot] = str_ref;
13313  string_refs.count++;
13314 }
13315 
13316 void OS::Core::unregisterStringRef(GCStringValue * str_ref)
13317 {
13318  int slot = str_ref->hash & string_refs.head_mask;
13319  GCStringValue * cur = string_refs.heads[slot], * prev = NULL;
13320  for(; cur; prev = cur, cur = cur->hash_next_ref){
13321  if(cur == str_ref){
13322  if(prev){
13323  prev->hash_next_ref = cur->hash_next_ref;
13324  }else{
13325  string_refs.heads[slot] = cur->hash_next_ref;
13326  }
13327  OS_ASSERT(string_refs.count > 0);
13328  string_refs.count--;
13329  cur->hash_next_ref = NULL;
13330  return;
13331  }
13332  }
13333  OS_ASSERT(false);
13334 }
13335 
13336 void OS::Core::deleteStringRefs()
13337 {
13338  if(!string_refs.heads){
13339  return;
13340  }
13341  for(int i = 0; i <= string_refs.head_mask; i++){
13342  while(string_refs.heads[i]){
13343  GCStringValue * cur = string_refs.heads[i];
13344  string_refs.heads[i] = cur->hash_next_ref;
13345  free(cur);
13346  }
13347  }
13348  free(string_refs.heads);
13349  string_refs.heads = NULL;
13350  string_refs.head_mask = 0;
13351  string_refs.count = 0;
13352 }

13389  next = user_pointer_ref->hash_next_ref;

13392  userptr_refs.heads[slot] = user_pointer_ref;
13393  }

13401  userptr_refs.heads[slot] = user_pointer_ref;

13425 void OS::Core::unregisterUserptrRef(void * ptr, int value_id)
13426 {
13427  if(userptr_refs.count > 0){
13428  OS_ASSERT(userptr_refs.heads && userptr_refs.head_mask);
13429  int hash = OS_PTR_HASH(ptr);
13430  int slot = hash & userptr_refs.head_mask;
13431  GCUserdataValue * userptr_ref = userptr_refs.heads[slot];
13432  for(GCUserdataValue * prev = NULL; userptr_ref; prev = userptr_ref, userptr_ref = userptr_ref->hash_next_ref){
13433  if(userptr_ref->value_id == value_id){
13434  if(!prev){
13435  userptr_refs.heads[slot] = userptr_ref->hash_next_ref;
13436  }else{
13437  prev->hash_next_ref = userptr_ref->hash_next_ref;
13438  }
13439  // free(userptr_ref);
13440  userptr_refs.count--;
13441  return;
13442  }
13443  }
13444  }
13445 }

13447 void OS::Core::deleteUserptrRefs()

13450  return;
13451  }

13453  while(userptr_refs.heads[i]){
13454  GCUserdataValue * cur = userptr_refs.heads[i];
13455  userptr_refs.heads[i] = cur->hash_next_ref;
13456  cur->hash_next_ref = NULL;
13457  // free(cur);
13458  }
13459  }
13460  free(userptr_refs.heads);
13461  userptr_refs.heads = NULL;
13462  userptr_refs.head_mask = 0;
13463  userptr_refs.count = 0;
13464 }

13482 void OS::Core::registerCFuncRef(GCCFunctionValue * cfunc_ref)
13483 {
13484  OS_ASSERT(!cfunc_ref->hash_next_ref);
13485  OS_ASSERT(cfunc_ref->cfunc_hash);
13486  if((cfunc_refs.count>>HASH_GROW_SHIFT) >= cfunc_refs.head_mask){
13487  int new_size = cfunc_refs.heads ? (cfunc_refs.head_mask+1) * 2 : 32;
13488  int alloc_size = sizeof(GCCFunctionValue*) * new_size;
13489  GCCFunctionValue ** new_heads = (GCCFunctionValue**)malloc(alloc_size OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
13490  OS_ASSERT(new_heads);
13491  OS_MEMSET(new_heads, 0, alloc_size);
13492 
13493  GCCFunctionValue ** old_heads = cfunc_refs.heads;
13494  int old_mask = cfunc_refs.head_mask;
13495 
13496  cfunc_refs.heads = new_heads;
13497  cfunc_refs.head_mask = new_size-1;
13498 
13499  if(old_heads){
13500  for(int i = 0; i <= old_mask; i++){
13501  for(GCCFunctionValue * cfunc_ref = old_heads[i], * next; cfunc_ref; cfunc_ref = next){
13502  next = cfunc_ref->hash_next_ref;
13503  int slot = cfunc_ref->cfunc_hash & cfunc_refs.head_mask;
13504  cfunc_ref->hash_next_ref = cfunc_refs.heads[slot];
13505  cfunc_refs.heads[slot] = cfunc_ref;
13506  }
13507  }
13508  free(old_heads);
13509  }
13510  }
13511 
13512  int slot = cfunc_ref->cfunc_hash & cfunc_refs.head_mask;
13513  cfunc_ref->hash_next_ref = cfunc_refs.heads[slot];
13514  cfunc_refs.heads[slot] = cfunc_ref;
13515  cfunc_refs.count++;
13516 }
13517 
13518 void OS::Core::unregisterCFuncRef(GCCFunctionValue * cfunc_ref)
13519 {
13520  int slot = cfunc_ref->cfunc_hash & cfunc_refs.head_mask;
13521  GCCFunctionValue * cur = cfunc_refs.heads[slot], * prev = NULL;
13522  for(; cur; prev = cur, cur = cur->hash_next_ref){
13523  if(cur == cfunc_ref){
13524  if(prev){
13525  prev->hash_next_ref = cur->hash_next_ref;
13526  }else{
13527  cfunc_refs.heads[slot] = cur->hash_next_ref;
13528  }
13529  OS_ASSERT(cfunc_refs.count > 0);
13530  cfunc_refs.count--;
13531  cur->hash_next_ref = NULL;
13532  return;
13533  }
13534  }
13535  OS_ASSERT(false);
13536 }

13538 void OS::Core::unregisterCFuncRef(OS_CFunction func, void * user_param, int value_id)
13539 {
13540  if(cfunc_refs.count > 0){
13541  OS_ASSERT(cfunc_refs.heads && cfunc_refs.head_mask);
13542  int hash = Utils::keyToHash(&func, sizeof(func), user_param ? &user_param : NULL, user_param ? sizeof(user_param) : 0);
13543  int slot = hash & cfunc_refs.head_mask;
13544  GCCFunctionValue * cfunc_ref = cfunc_refs.heads[slot];
13545  for(GCCFunctionValue * prev = NULL; cfunc_ref; prev = cfunc_ref, cfunc_ref = cfunc_ref->hash_next_ref){
13546  if(cfunc_ref->value_id == value_id){
13547  if(!prev){
13548  cfunc_refs.heads[slot] = cfunc_ref->hash_next_ref;
13549  }else{
13550  prev->hash_next_ref = cfunc_ref->hash_next_ref;
13551  }
13552  // free(cfunc_ref);
13553  cfunc_refs.count--;
13554  return;
13555  }
13556  }
13557  }
13558 }

13746 void OS::Core::registerFreeCandidateValue(GCValue * value)
13747 {
13748  OS_ASSERT(value->value_id);
13749  OS_ASSERT(!gc_candidate_values.get(value->value_id));
13750  if((gc_candidate_values.count>>HASH_GROW_SHIFT) >= gc_candidate_values.head_mask){
13751  int new_size = gc_candidate_values.heads ? (gc_candidate_values.head_mask+1) * 2 : 32;
13752  int alloc_size = sizeof(GCValue*) * new_size;
13753  GCValue ** new_heads = (GCValue**)malloc(alloc_size OS_DBG_FILEPOS); // new Value*[new_size];
13754  OS_ASSERT(new_heads);
13755  OS_MEMSET(new_heads, 0, alloc_size);
13756 
13757  GCValue ** old_heads = gc_candidate_values.heads;
13758  int old_mask = gc_candidate_values.head_mask;
13759 
13760  gc_candidate_values.heads = new_heads;
13761  gc_candidate_values.head_mask = new_size-1;
13762 
13763  if(old_heads){
13764  for(int i = 0; i <= old_mask; i++){
13765  for(GCValue * value = old_heads[i], * next; value; value = next){
13766  next = value->hash_next_free_candidate;
13767  int slot = value->value_id & gc_candidate_values.head_mask;
13768  value->hash_next_free_candidate = gc_candidate_values.heads[slot];
13769  gc_candidate_values.heads[slot] = value;
13770  }
13771  }
13772  free(old_heads);
13773  }
13774  }else if(0 && (gc_candidate_values.head_mask>>1) > gc_candidate_values.count && gc_candidate_values.head_mask >= 256-1){
13775  int new_size = (gc_candidate_values.head_mask+1) >> 1;
13776  int alloc_size = sizeof(GCValue*) * new_size;
13777  GCValue ** new_heads = (GCValue**)malloc(alloc_size OS_DBG_FILEPOS); // new Value*[new_size];
13778  OS_ASSERT(new_heads);
13779  OS_MEMSET(new_heads, 0, alloc_size);
13780 
13781  GCValue ** old_heads = gc_candidate_values.heads;
13782  int old_mask = gc_candidate_values.head_mask;
13783 
13784  gc_candidate_values.heads = new_heads;
13785  gc_candidate_values.head_mask = new_size-1;
13786 
13787  for(int i = 0; i <= old_mask; i++){
13788  for(GCValue * value = old_heads[i], * next; value; value = next){
13789  next = value->hash_next_free_candidate;
13790  int slot = value->value_id & gc_candidate_values.head_mask;
13791  value->hash_next_free_candidate = gc_candidate_values.heads[slot];
13792  gc_candidate_values.heads[slot] = value;
13793  }
13794  }
13795  free(old_heads);
13796  }
13797 
13798  int slot = value->value_id & gc_candidate_values.head_mask;
13799  value->hash_next_free_candidate = gc_candidate_values.heads[slot];
13800  // value->mark_created_values = num_created_values;
13801  value->gc_step_type = gc_step_type;
13802  gc_candidate_values.heads[slot] = value;
13803  gc_candidate_values.count++;
13804 }
13805 
13806 void OS::Core::unregisterFreeCandidateValue(GCValue * value)
13807 {
13808  int slot = value->value_id & gc_candidate_values.head_mask;
13809  GCValue * candidate = gc_candidate_values.heads[slot], * prev = NULL;
13810  for(; candidate; prev = candidate, candidate = candidate->hash_next_free_candidate){
13811  if(candidate == value){
13812  if(prev){
13813  prev->hash_next_free_candidate = candidate->hash_next_free_candidate;
13814  }else{
13815  gc_candidate_values.heads[slot] = candidate->hash_next_free_candidate;
13816  }
13817  OS_ASSERT(gc_candidate_values.count > 0);
13818  candidate->hash_next_free_candidate = NULL;
13819  gc_candidate_values.count--;
13820  return;
13821  }
13822  }
13823 }

13832  gc_candidate_values.heads[i] = candidate->hash_next_free_candidate;

13834  gc_candidate_values.count--;
13835  // free(candidate);
13836  }
13837  }
13838  if(!gc_candidate_values.count){
13839  break;

13841  }
13842  }
13843  OS_ASSERT(!gc_candidate_values.count);
13844  if(gc_candidate_values.heads && gc_candidate_values.count == 0){
13845  free(gc_candidate_values.heads);

13980  {

13989 
13990  void mark(GCValue * cur)
13991  {
13992  OS_ASSERT(cur);
13993  OS_ASSERT((OS_U32)(intptr_t)cur != 0xdededede);
13994  OS_ASSERT(gc_step_type == allocator->core->gc_step_type);
13995  if(cur->gc_step_type == allocator->core->gc_step_type){
13996  return;
13997  }
13998  cur->gc_step_type = allocator->core->gc_step_type;
13999  if(cur->prototype){
14000  mark(cur->prototype);
14001  }
14002  if(cur->name){
14003  mark(cur->name);
14004  }
14005  if(cur->table){
14006  mark(cur->table);
14007  }
14008  switch(cur->type){
14009  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_STRING:
14010  {
14011  OS_ASSERT(dynamic_cast<GCStringValue*>(cur));
14012  GCStringValue * string = (GCStringValue*)cur;
14013  OS_ASSERT(!string->table);
14014  break;
14015  }
14016 
14017  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_ARRAY:
14018  {
14019  OS_ASSERT(dynamic_cast<GCArrayValue*>(cur));
14020  GCArrayValue * arr = (GCArrayValue*)cur;
14021  for(int i = 0; i < arr->values.count; i++){
14022  mark(arr->values[i]);
14023  }
14024  break;
14025  }
14026 
14027  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_OBJECT:
14028  OS_ASSERT(dynamic_cast<GCObjectValue*>(cur));
14029  break;
14030 
14031  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_USERDATA:
14032  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_USERPTR:
14033  OS_ASSERT(dynamic_cast<GCUserdataValue*>(cur));
14034  break;
14035 
14036  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_FUNCTION:
14037  {
14038  OS_ASSERT(dynamic_cast<GCFunctionValue*>(cur));
14039  GCFunctionValue * func_value = (GCFunctionValue*)cur;
14040  mark(func_value->env);
14041  mark(func_value->self);
14042  if(func_value->locals){
14043  mark(func_value->locals);
14044  }
14045  if(0) // strings use external ref count
14046  for(int i = 0; i < func_value->prog->num_strings + func_value->prog->num_numbers + CONST_STD_VALUES; i++){
14047  mark(func_value->prog->const_values[i]);
14048  }
14049  break;
14050  }
14051 
14052  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_CFUNCTION:
14053  {
14054  OS_ASSERT(dynamic_cast<GCCFunctionValue*>(cur));
14055  GCCFunctionValue * func_value = (GCCFunctionValue*)cur;
14056  Value * closure_values = (Value*)(func_value + 1);
14057  for(int i = 0; i < func_value->num_closure_values; i++){
14058  mark(closure_values[i]);
14059  }
14060  break;
14061  }
14062 
14063  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_NULL:
14064  break;
14065 
14066  default:
14067  OS_ASSERT(false);
14068  }
14069  }
14070 
14071 #if defined OS_DEBUG && 00
14072  bool checkValid(const Value& val)
14073  {
14074  if(OS_IS_VALUE_GC(val)){
14075  GCValue * value = dynamic_cast<GCValue*>(OS_VALUE_VARIANT(val).value);
14076  return value->value_id > 0;
14077  }
14078  return true;
14079  }

14088  Property * prop = value->table->first;
14089  for(; prop; prop = prop->next){
14090  if(prop->index.getGCValue() == v){
14091  return true;
14092  }
14093  if(prop->value.getGCValue() == v){
14094  return true;
14095  }
14096  }
14097  }
14098  }
14099  }
14100  return false;
14101  }
14102 #endif
14103  } lib(allocator);
14104 
14105  int i;
14106  lib.gc_step_type = ++gc_step_type;
14107  GCValue * candidate, * next, * prev;
14108  for(i = 0; i < stack_values.count; i++){
14109  Value& value = stack_values[i];
14110  if(OS_IS_VALUE_GC(value)){
14111  OS_ASSERT(OS_VALUE_VARIANT(value).value);
14112  if((candidate = gc_candidate_values.get(OS_VALUE_VARIANT(value).value->value_id))){
14113  candidate->gc_step_type = gc_step_type;
14114  }
14115  }
14116  }
14117  // int valid_mark = num_created_values - 64; // wait some time for new allocated values
14118  int head_mask = gc_candidate_values.head_mask;
14119  for(i = 0; i <= head_mask; i++){
14120  for(candidate = gc_candidate_values.heads[i], prev = NULL; candidate; candidate = next){
14121  OS_ASSERT(candidate->value_id);
14122  next = candidate->hash_next_free_candidate;
14123  if(candidate->ref_count | candidate->external_ref_count){
14124  OS_ASSERT(candidate->ref_count > 0 || candidate->external_ref_count > 0);
14125  if(prev){
14126  prev->hash_next_free_candidate = next;
14127  }else{
14128  gc_candidate_values.heads[i] = next;
14129  }
14130  OS_ASSERT(gc_candidate_values.count > 0);
14131  candidate->hash_next_free_candidate = NULL;
14132  gc_candidate_values.count--;
14133  // free(candidate);
14134  OS_ASSERT(!gc_candidate_values.get(candidate->value_id));
14135  continue;
14136  }
14137  // if(candidate->mark_created_values > valid_mark){
14138  if(candidate->gc_step_type == gc_step_type){ // local stack
14139  prev = candidate;
14140  continue;
14141  }
14142  OS_ASSERT(!candidate->ref_count);
14143  // triggerValueDestructor(candidate);
14144  if(prev){
14145  prev->hash_next_free_candidate = next;
14146  }else{
14147  gc_candidate_values.heads[i] = next;
14148  }
14149  OS_ASSERT(gc_candidate_values.count > 0);
14150  candidate->hash_next_free_candidate = NULL;
14151  gc_candidate_values.count--;
14152  // free(candidate);
14153  OS_ASSERT(!gc_candidate_values.get(candidate->value_id));
14154 
14155  clearValue(candidate);
14156  unregisterValue(candidate->value_id);
14157  // OS_ASSERT(!lib.findParent(candidate));
14158  deleteValue(candidate);
14159 
14160  if(head_mask != gc_candidate_values.head_mask){
14161  head_mask = gc_candidate_values.head_mask;
14162  // i = 0; // restart
14163  break;
14164  }
14165  }
14166  }
14167 
14168  int used_bytes = allocator->getUsedBytes();
14169  if(full || used_bytes >= gc_next_when_used_bytes){
14170  lib.gc_step_type = ++gc_step_type;
14171 
14172  lib.mark(global_vars);
14173  lib.mark(user_pool);
14174  lib.mark(retain_pool);
14175  lib.mark(check_get_recursion);
14176  lib.mark(check_set_recursion);
14177  lib.mark(check_valueof_recursion);
14178  for(i = 0; i < PROTOTYPE_COUNT; i++){
14179  lib.mark(prototypes[i]);
14180  }
14181  if(0){
14182  String * str = &strings->__construct;
14183  String * end = (String*)((OS_BYTE*)strings + sizeof(*strings));
14184  for(; str < end; str++){
14185  lib.mark(str->string);
14186  }
14187  }
14188  lib.mark(terminated_exception);
14189  for(i = 0; i < stack_values.count; i++){
14190  lib.mark(stack_values[i]);
14191  }
14192  for(i = 0; i < call_stack_funcs.count; i++){
14193  lib.mark(&call_stack_funcs[i]);
14194  }
14195 
14196 #if 1
14197  head_mask = gc_candidate_values.head_mask;
14198  for(i = 0; i <= head_mask; i++){
14199  for(candidate = gc_candidate_values.heads[i]; candidate; candidate = candidate->hash_next_free_candidate){
14200  OS_ASSERT(candidate->value_id);
14201  lib.mark(candidate);
14202  }
14203  }
14204 #endif
14205 
14206  gc_fix_in_progress = true;
14207  GCValue * destroy_list = NULL;
14208  int save_next_id = values.next_id;
14209  head_mask = values.head_mask;
14210  for(i = 0; i <= values.head_mask; i++){
14211  GCValue * value = values.heads[i], * prev = NULL, * next;
14212  for(; value; value = next){
14213  next = value->hash_next;
14214  if(value->gc_step_type == gc_step_type){
14215  prev = value;
14216  continue;
14217  }
14218  if(value->external_ref_count > 0){
14219  value->gc_step_type = gc_step_type;
14220  prev = value;
14221  continue;
14222  }
14223  // OS_ASSERT(!gc_candidate_values.get(value->value_id));
14224  // unregisterFreeCandidateValue(value->value_id);
14225  OS_ASSERT(value->ref_count >= 0);
14226  // OS_ASSERT(!lib.findParent(value));
14227  clearValue(value);
14228  if(prev){
14229  prev->hash_next = next;
14230  }else{
14231  values.heads[i] = next;
14232  }
14233  // value->hash_next = NULL;
14234  values.count--;
14235 
14236  // deleteValue(value);
14237  value->hash_next = destroy_list;
14238  destroy_list = value;
14239  }
14240  }
14241  OS_ASSERT(save_next_id == values.next_id);
14242 #if defined OS_DEBUG && 00
14243  head_mask = values.head_mask;
14244  for(i = 0; i <= values.head_mask; i++){
14245  GCValue * value = values.heads[i];
14246  for(; value; value = value->hash_next){
14247  if(value->table){
14248  Property * prop = value->table->first;
14249  for(; prop; prop = prop->next){
14250  OS_ASSERT(lib.checkValid(prop->index));
14251  OS_ASSERT(lib.checkValid(prop->value));
14252  }
14253  }
14254  switch(value->type){
14255  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_OBJECT:
14256  break;
14257  }
14258  }
14259  }
14260 #endif
14261  while(destroy_list){
14262  GCValue * value = destroy_list;
14263  destroy_list = value->hash_next;
14264  value->hash_next = NULL;
14265  // OS_ASSERT(!lib.findParent(value));
14266  unregisterFreeCandidateValue(value);
14267  deleteValue(value);
14268  }
14269 #if defined OS_DEBUG && 00
14270  head_mask = values.head_mask;
14271  for(i = 0; i <= values.head_mask; i++){
14272  GCValue * value = values.heads[i];
14273  for(; value; value = value->hash_next){
14274  if(value->table){
14275  Property * prop = value->table->first;
14276  for(; prop; prop = prop->next){
14277  OS_ASSERT(lib.checkValid(prop->index));
14278  OS_ASSERT(lib.checkValid(prop->value));
14279  }
14280  }
14281  switch(value->type){
14282  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_OBJECT:
14283  break;
14284  }
14285  }
14286  }
14287 #endif
14288  gc_fix_in_progress = false;
14289  // lib.destroyValues(false);
14290  used_bytes = allocator->getUsedBytes();
14291  if(used_bytes >= gc_next_when_used_bytes){
14292  gc_next_when_used_bytes *= 2;
14293  }else if(1){
14294  while(used_bytes < gc_next_when_used_bytes/2 && gc_next_when_used_bytes/2 >= gc_start_when_used_bytes){
14295  gc_next_when_used_bytes /= 2;
14296  }
14297  }
14298 #if 0
14299  if(0 && full){
14300  static bool in_progress = false;
14301  if(!in_progress){
14302  in_progress = true;
14303  static int i = 0;
14304  OS_CHAR str[128];
14305  OS_SNPRINTF(str, sizeof(str), "gc-%d.txt", ++i);
14306  dumpValuesToFile(str);
14307  OS_SNPRINTF(str, sizeof(str), "heap-%d.txt", i);
14308  ((OSHeapManager*)allocator->memory_manager)->dumpUsage(allocator, str);
14309  in_progress = false;
14310  }
14311  }
14312 #endif
14313  }
14314 }

14316 void OS::Core::dumpValues(Buffer& out)
14317 {
14318  struct Lib
14319  {
14320  Core * core;
14321  Buffer * out;
14322  int gc_step_type;
14323 
14324  void appendDepthSpaces(int depth)
14325  {
14326  for(int i = 0; i < depth; i++){
14327  out->append(OS_TEXT(" "));
14328  }
14329  }
14330  void appendString(const String& str)
14331  {
14332  out->append(str);
14333  }
14334  void appendString(const OS_CHAR * str)
14335  {
14336  out->append(str);
14337  }
14338  void appendNumber(OS_NUMBER val)
14339  {
14340  OS_CHAR str[128];
14341  Utils::numToStr(str, val);
14342  appendString(str);
14343  }
14344  void appendQuotedString(const String& str)
14345  {
14346  core->appendQuotedString(*out, str);
14347  }
14348 
14349  OS_CHAR str_buf[1024];
14350  const OS_CHAR * format(const OS_CHAR * fmt, ...)
14351  {
14352  va_list va;
14353  va_start(va, fmt);
14354  OS_VSNPRINTF(str_buf, sizeof(str_buf)-sizeof(str_buf[0]), fmt, va);
14355  va_end(va);
14356  return str_buf;
14357  }
14358 
14359  void dumpLocals(Locals * locals, int depth)
14360  {
14361  /*
14362  if(locals->gc_step_type == core->gc_step_type){
14363  // appendDepthSpaces(depth);
14364  appendString(format(OS_TEXT("<locals:in_stack=%d:count=%d> {{RECURSION}}\n"), (int)locals->is_stack_locals, locals->func_decl->num_locals));
14365  // appendString(OS_TEXT("{{RECURSION}}"));
14366  return;
14367  }
14368  locals->gc_step_type = core->gc_step_type;
14369  */
14370 
14371  int i;
14372  if(!locals->is_stack_locals && locals->values){
14373  appendString(format(OS_TEXT("<locals:in_stack=%d:count=%d> [\n"), (int)locals->is_stack_locals, locals->func_decl->num_locals));
14374  for(i = 0; i < locals->func_decl->num_locals; i++){
14375  appendDepthSpaces(depth + 1);
14376  appendString(format(OS_TEXT("%d: "), i));
14377  // appendDepthSpaces(depth + 1);
14378  dump(locals->values[i], depth + 1);
14379  appendString(OS_TEXT(",\n"));
14380  }
14381  appendDepthSpaces(depth);
14382  appendString(OS_TEXT("]\n"));
14383  }
14384  for(i = 0; i < locals->func_decl->func_depth; i++){
14385  appendDepthSpaces(depth + 1);
14386  appendString(OS_TEXT("parent: "));
14387  dumpLocals(locals->getParent(i), depth + 1);
14388  }
14389  }
14390 
14391  void dump(StackFunction * stack_func, int depth)
14392  {
14393  OS_ASSERT(stack_func->func);
14394  appendString(OS_TEXT("<stack_func> {\n"));
14395 
14396  appendDepthSpaces(depth + 1);
14397  appendString(OS_TEXT("func: "));
14398  dump(stack_func->func, depth + 1);
14399  appendString(OS_TEXT("\n"));
14400 
14401  if(stack_func->self_for_proto){
14402  appendDepthSpaces(depth + 1);
14403  appendString(OS_TEXT("self_for_proto: "));
14404  dump(stack_func->self_for_proto, depth + 1);
14405  appendString(OS_TEXT("\n"));
14406  }
14407  if(stack_func->arguments){
14408  appendDepthSpaces(depth + 1);
14409  appendString(OS_TEXT("arguments: "));
14410  dump(stack_func->arguments, depth + 1);
14411  appendString(OS_TEXT("\n"));
14412  }
14413  if(stack_func->rest_arguments){
14414  appendDepthSpaces(depth + 1);
14415  appendString(OS_TEXT("rest_arguments: "));
14416  dump(stack_func->rest_arguments, depth + 1);
14417  appendString(OS_TEXT("\n"));
14418  }
14419  appendDepthSpaces(depth + 1);
14420  dumpLocals(stack_func->locals, depth);
14421  appendString(OS_TEXT("\n"));
14422 
14423  appendDepthSpaces(depth);
14424  appendString(OS_TEXT("}"));
14425  }
14426 
14427  void dump(const Value& cur, int depth)
14428  {
14429  switch(OS_VALUE_TYPE(cur)){
14430  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_NULL:
14431  appendString(core->strings->syntax_null);
14432  break;
14433 
14434  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_BOOL:
14435  appendString(OS_VALUE_VARIANT(cur).boolean ? core->strings->syntax_true : core->strings->syntax_false);
14436  break;
14437 
14438  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_NUMBER:
14439  appendNumber(OS_VALUE_NUMBER(cur));
14440  break;
14441 
14442  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_STRING:
14443  OS_VALUE_VARIANT(cur).string->gc_step_type = core->gc_step_type;
14444  appendString(format(OS_TEXT("<string#%d> "), OS_VALUE_VARIANT(cur).string->value_id));
14445  appendQuotedString(String(core->allocator, OS_VALUE_VARIANT(cur).string));
14446  break;
14447 
14448  default:
14449  OS_ASSERT(cur.getGCValue());
14450  dump(cur.getGCValue(), depth);
14451  }
14452  }
14453 
14454  void dump(GCValue * value, int depth)
14455  {
14456  OS_ASSERT(gc_step_type == core->gc_step_type);
14457  if(value->gc_step_type == core->gc_step_type){
14458  switch(value->type){
14459  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_STRING:
14460  OS_ASSERT(dynamic_cast<GCStringValue*>(value));
14461  appendString(format(OS_TEXT("<string#%d> "), value->value_id));
14462  appendQuotedString(String(core->allocator, (GCStringValue*)value));
14463  return;
14464 
14465  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_ARRAY:
14466  appendString(format(OS_TEXT("<array#%d> {{RECURSION}}"), value->value_id));
14467  return;
14468 
14469  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_OBJECT:
14470  appendString(format(OS_TEXT("<object#%d:classname=%s> {{RECURSION}}"), value->value_id, core->getValueClassname(value).toChar()));
14471  return;
14472 
14473  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_USERDATA:
14474  appendString(format(OS_TEXT("<userdata#%d:classname=%s> {{RECURSION}}"), value->value_id, core->getValueClassname(value).toChar()));
14475  return;
14476 
14477  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_USERPTR:
14478  appendString(format(OS_TEXT("<userptr#%d:classname=%s> {{RECURSION}}"), value->value_id, core->getValueClassname(value).toChar()));
14479  return;
14480 
14481  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_FUNCTION:
14482  appendString(format(OS_TEXT("<function#%d> {{RECURSION}}"), value->value_id));
14483  return;
14484 
14485  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_CFUNCTION:
14486  appendString(format(OS_TEXT("<cfunction#%d> {{RECURSION}}"), value->value_id));
14487  return;
14488 
14489  default:
14490  OS_ASSERT(false);
14491  }
14492 
14493  appendString(OS_TEXT("{{RECURSION}}"));
14494  return;
14495  }
14496  value->gc_step_type = core->gc_step_type;
14497 
14498  switch(value->type){
14499  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_STRING:
14500  OS_ASSERT(dynamic_cast<GCStringValue*>(value));
14501  appendString(format(OS_TEXT("<string#%d> "), value->value_id));
14502  appendQuotedString(String(core->allocator, (GCStringValue*)value));
14503  return;
14504 
14505  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_ARRAY:
14506  {
14507  OS_ASSERT(dynamic_cast<Core::GCArrayValue*>(value));
14508  Core::GCArrayValue * arr = (Core::GCArrayValue*)value;
14509  // appendDepthSpaces(depth);
14510  appendString(format(OS_TEXT("<array#%d> [\n"), value->value_id));
14511  for(int i = 0; i < arr->values.count; i++){
14512  appendDepthSpaces(depth + 1);
14513  appendString(format(OS_TEXT("%d: "), i));
14514  dump(arr->values[i], depth + 1);
14515  appendString(OS_TEXT(",\n"));
14516  }
14517  if(!value->table){
14518  appendDepthSpaces(depth);
14519  appendString(OS_TEXT("]"));
14520  break;
14521  }else{
14522  appendDepthSpaces(depth);
14523  appendString(OS_TEXT("] + "));
14524  // goto dump_object;
14525  }
14526  }
14527 
14528  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_OBJECT:
14529  {
14530  appendString(format(OS_TEXT("<object#%d:classname=%s> {\n"), value->value_id, core->getValueClassname(value).toChar()));
14531 dump_object:
14532  if(!value->table){
14533  appendDepthSpaces(depth);
14534  appendString(OS_TEXT("}"));
14535  break;
14536  }
14537  Property * prop = value->table->first;
14538  for(; prop; prop = prop->next){
14539  appendDepthSpaces(depth + 1);
14540  dump(prop->index, depth + 1);
14541  appendString(OS_TEXT(": "));
14542  dump(prop->value, depth + 1);
14543  appendString(OS_TEXT(",\n"));
14544  }
14545  appendDepthSpaces(depth);
14546  appendString(OS_TEXT("}"));
14547  break;
14548  }
14549 
14550  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_USERDATA:
14551  appendString(format(OS_TEXT("<userdata#%d:classname=%s> {\n"), value->value_id, core->getValueClassname(value).toChar()));
14552  goto dump_object;
14553 
14554  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_USERPTR:
14555  appendString(format(OS_TEXT("<userptr#%d:classname=%s> {\n"), value->value_id, core->getValueClassname(value).toChar()));
14556  goto dump_object;
14557 
14558  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_FUNCTION:
14559  {
14560  OS_ASSERT(dynamic_cast<GCFunctionValue*>(value));
14561  GCFunctionValue * func_value = (GCFunctionValue*)value;
14562 
14563  appendString(format(OS_TEXT("<function#%d> {\n"), func_value->value_id));
14564 
14565  appendDepthSpaces(depth + 1);
14566  appendString(OS_TEXT("env: "));
14567  dump(func_value->env, depth + 1);
14568  appendString(OS_TEXT("\n"));
14569 
14570  appendString(OS_TEXT("this: "));
14571  dump(func_value->self, depth + 1);
14572  appendString(OS_TEXT("\n"));
14573 
14574  if(func_value->locals){
14575  appendDepthSpaces(depth + 1);
14576  dumpLocals(func_value->locals, depth + 1);
14577  }
14578 
14579  goto dump_object;
14580  }
14581 
14582  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_CFUNCTION:
14583  {
14584  OS_ASSERT(dynamic_cast<GCCFunctionValue*>(value));
14585  GCCFunctionValue * func_value = (GCCFunctionValue*)value;
14586 
14587  appendString(format(OS_TEXT("<cfunction#%d> {\n"), func_value->value_id));
14588 
14589  Value * closure_values = (Value*)(func_value + 1);
14590  for(int i = 0; i < func_value->num_closure_values; i++){
14591  appendDepthSpaces(depth + 1);
14592  appendString(format(OS_TEXT("closure_%d: "), i));
14593  dump(closure_values[i], depth + 1);
14594  appendString(OS_TEXT(",\n"));
14595  }
14596  goto dump_object;
14597  }
14598  }
14599  }
14600 
14601  } lib = {this, &out, ++gc_step_type};
14602 
14603  int i;
14604  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT("=== GLOBALS: "));
14605  lib.dump(global_vars, 0);
14606  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT("\n"));
14607 
14608  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT("=== USER_POOL: "));
14609  lib.dump(user_pool, 0);
14610  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT("\n"));
14611 
14612  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT("=== RETAIN_POOL: "));
14613  lib.dump(retain_pool, 0);
14614  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT("\n"));
14615 
14616  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT("=== CHECK_GET_RECURSION: "));
14617  lib.dump(check_get_recursion, 0);
14618  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT("\n"));
14619 
14620  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT("=== CHECK_SET_RECURSION: "));
14621  lib.dump(check_set_recursion, 0);
14622  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT("\n"));
14623 
14624  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT("=== CHECK_VALUEOF_RECURSION: "));
14625  lib.dump(check_valueof_recursion, 0);
14626  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT("\n"));
14627 
14628  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT("=== TERMINATED_EXCEPTION: "));
14629  lib.dump(terminated_exception, 0);
14630  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT("\n"));
14631 
14632  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT("=== PROTOTYPES ===\n"));
14633  for(i = 0; i < PROTOTYPE_COUNT; i++){
14634  lib.dump(prototypes[i], 0);
14635  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT(",\n"));
14636  }
14637 
14638  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT("=== STACK_VALUES ===\n"));
14639  for(i = 0; i < stack_values.count; i++){
14640  lib.appendString(lib.format(OS_TEXT("%d: "), i));
14641  lib.dump(stack_values[i], 0);
14642  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT(",\n"));
14643  }
14644 
14645  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT("=== CALL_STACK_FUNCS ===\n"));
14646  for(i = 0; i < call_stack_funcs.count; i++){
14647  lib.appendString(lib.format(OS_TEXT("%d: "), i));
14648  lib.dump(&call_stack_funcs[i], 0);
14649  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT(",\n"));
14650  }
14651 
14652  if(1){
14653  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT("=== EXTERNAL ===\n"));
14654  for(i = 0; i <= values.head_mask; i++){
14655  GCValue * value = values.heads[i];
14656  for(; value; value = value->hash_next){
14657  OS_ASSERT(gc_step_type == lib.core->gc_step_type);
14658  if(value->gc_step_type == gc_step_type){
14659  continue;
14660  }
14661  if(value->external_ref_count > 0){
14662  lib.dump(value, 0);
14663  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT("\n"));
14664  // value->gc_step_type = gc_step_type;
14665  }
14666  }
14667  }
14668 
14669  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT("=== LEAKS ===\n"));
14670  for(i = 0; i <= values.head_mask; i++){
14671  GCValue * value = values.heads[i];
14672  for(; value; value = value->hash_next){
14673  OS_ASSERT(gc_step_type == lib.core->gc_step_type);
14674  if(value->gc_step_type == gc_step_type){
14675  continue;
14676  }
14677  if(value->external_ref_count > 0){
14678  continue;
14679  }
14680  lib.dump(value, 0);
14681  lib.appendString(OS_TEXT("\n"));
14682  // value->gc_step_type = gc_step_type;
14683  }
14684  }
14685  }
14686 }

14688 void OS::Core::dumpValuesToFile(const OS_CHAR * filename)
14689 {
14690  Buffer out(allocator);
14691  dumpValues(out);
14692  FileStreamWriter(allocator, filename).writeBytes(out.buffer.buf, out.buffer.count);
14693 }

14702 
14703 void OS::Core::appendQuotedString(Buffer& buf, const String& string)
14704 {
14705  buf += OS_TEXT("\"");
14706  int len = string.getLen();
14707  const OS_CHAR * str = string.toChar();
14708  for(int i = 0; i < len; i++, str++){
14709  switch(*str){
14710  case OS_TEXT('\"'): buf += OS_TEXT("\\\""); continue;
14711  case OS_TEXT('\r'): buf += OS_TEXT("\\r"); continue;
14712  case OS_TEXT('\n'): buf += OS_TEXT("\\n"); continue;
14713  case OS_TEXT('\t'): buf += OS_TEXT("\\t"); continue;
14714  case OS_TEXT('\v'): buf += OS_TEXT("\\v"); continue;
14715  case OS_TEXT('\b'): buf += OS_TEXT("\\b"); continue;
14716  case OS_TEXT('\f'): buf += OS_TEXT("\\f"); continue;
14717  case OS_TEXT('\\'): buf += OS_TEXT("\\\\"); continue;
14718  }
14719  if(*str < OS_TEXT(' ')){
14720  buf += OS_TEXT("0x");
14721  buf.append(UPPER_DIGITS[((int)*str >> 4) & 0xF]);
14722  buf.append(UPPER_DIGITS[((int)*str >> 0) & 0xF]);
14723  continue;
14724  }
14725  buf.append(*str);
14726  }
14727  buf += OS_TEXT("\"");
14728 }
14729

14922 int OS::getFileSize(FileHandle * f)
14923 {
14924  if(f){
14925  int pos = seekFile(f, 0, SEEK_CUR);
14926  int size = seekFile(f, 0, SEEK_END);
14927  seekFile(f, pos, SEEK_SET);
14928  return size;
14929  }
14930  return 0;
14931 }

15022 #ifdef OS_DEBUG
15023 void OS::checkNativeStackUsage(const OS_CHAR * func_name)
15024 {
15025  if(native_stack_in_process){
15026  return;
15027  }
15028  int mark = 0;
15029  int cur_native_stack_usage = (int)&mark - native_stack_start_mark;
15030  if(cur_native_stack_usage < 0){
15031  cur_native_stack_usage = -cur_native_stack_usage;
15032  }
15033  if(native_stack_max_usage < cur_native_stack_usage){
15034  if(cur_native_stack_usage > 1024*100 && cur_native_stack_usage > native_stack_max_usage * 5 / 4){
15035  native_stack_in_process = true;
15036  printf(OS_TEXT("native stack usage: %.1f Kb (%s)\n"), (float)cur_native_stack_usage/1024.0f, func_name);
15037  native_stack_in_process = false;
15038  }
15039  native_stack_max_usage = cur_native_stack_usage;
15040  }
15041 }
15042 #endif

15141 
15142 void OS::Core::setExceptionValue(Value val)
15143 {
15144  if(!val.isNull()){
15145  allocator->getGlobal(OS_TEXT("Exception"));
15146  if(isValueInstanceOf(val, stack_values.lastElement())){
15147  stack_values.lastElement() = val;
15148  }else{
15149  allocator->pushGlobals();
15150  allocator->pushString(valueToString(val, true));
15151  callFT(1, 1); // _G.Exception(toString(val))
15152  }
15153  allocator->getProperty(-1, OS_TEXT("trace"), false);
15154  bool is_array = allocator->isArray();
15155  allocator->pop();
15156 
15157  if(!is_array){
15158  pushBackTrace(0);
15159  allocator->setProperty(-2, OS_TEXT("trace"));
15160  }
15161 
15162  setValue(terminated_exception, stack_values.buf[--stack_values.count]);
15163  if(!terminated_exception.isNull()){
15164  terminated = true;
15165  terminated_code = TERMINATED_EXCEPTION_CODE;
15166  return;
15167  }
15168  }
15169  OS_ASSERT(!call_stack_overflow);
15170  call_stack_overflow = false;
15171  terminated = false;
15172  terminated_code = 0;
15173  setValue(terminated_exception, Value());
15174 }
15175 
15176 void OS::setException()
15177 {
15178  core->setExceptionValue(core->getStackValue(-1));
15179  pop();
15180 }
15181

15183 {
15184  setException(Core::String(this, str));
15185 }

15187 void OS::setException(const Core::String& str)
15188 {
15189  pushString(str);
15190  setException();
15191 }
15192 
15193 void OS::handleException()
15194 {
15195  if(isExceptionSet()){
15196  getException();
15197  resetException();
15198  getGlobal(core->strings->func_unhandledException);
15199  pushGlobals();
15200  pushStackValue(-3); // exception
15201  callFT(1, 0, OS_CALLTYPE_FUNC);
15202  pop();
15203  resetException();
15204  }
15205 }

15212 
15213  // check_recursion = NULL;

15217 
15218  max_call_stack = OS_DEF_MAX_CALL_STACK_SIZE;
15219  stack_func = NULL;
15220  stack_func_locals = NULL;
15221  stack_func_env_index = 0;
15222  stack_func_prog_values = NULL;
15223 
15224  // gc_candidate_list = NULL;
15225 
15226  settings.create_compiled_file = true;
15227  settings.create_debug_info = true;
15228  settings.create_text_opcodes = true;
15229  settings.create_text_eval_opcodes = false;
