23951 
23952 void OS::initStringClass()
23953 {
23954  struct PackLib
23955  {
23956  static void packLong(long val, int size, int *map, char *output)
23957  {
23958  char *v = (char*)&val;
23959  for (int i = 0; i < size; i++) {
23960  *output++ = v[map[i]];
23961  }
23962  }
23963 
23964  /* pack() idea stolen from Perl (implemented formats behave the same as there)
23965  * Implemented formats are A, a, h, H, c, C, s, S, i, I, l, L, n, N, f, d, x, X, @.
23966  */
23967  static int pack(OS * os, int params, int, int, void*)
23968  {
23969  int offs = os->getAbsoluteOffs(-(++params));
23970 
23971  OS::String format_str = os->toString(offs);
23972  const OS_CHAR * format = format_str.toChar();
23973  int formatlen = format_str.getLen();
23974 
23975  /* We have a maximum of <formatlen> format codes to deal with */
23976  char * formatcodes = (char*)os->malloc(formatlen * sizeof(*formatcodes) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
23977  int * formatargs = (int*)os->malloc(formatlen * sizeof(*formatargs) OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
23978  int i, currentarg = 1;
23979 
23980  /* Preprocess format into formatcodes and formatargs */
23981  int formatcount = 0;
23982  for (i = 0; i < formatlen; formatcount++) {
23983  char code = format[i++];
23984  int arg = 1;
23985 
23986  /* Handle format arguments if any */
23987  if (i < formatlen) {
23988  char c = format[i];
23989  if (c == '*') {
23990  arg = -1;
23991  i++;
23992  }else if (c >= '0' && c <= '9') {
23993  // arg = atoi(&format[i]);
23994  arg = 0;
23995  while (format[i] >= '0' && format[i] <= '9' && i < formatlen) {
23996  arg = arg*10 + (format[i] - '0');
23997  i++;
23998  }
23999  }
24000  }
24001 
24002  /* Handle special arg '*' for all codes and check argv overflows */
24003  switch (code) {
24004  /* Never uses any args */
24005  case 'x':
24006  case 'X':
24007  case '@':
24008  if (arg < 0) {
24009  os->setException(OS::String::format(os, "type %c: '*' error", code));
24010  os->free(formatcodes);
24011  os->free(formatargs);
24012  return 0;
24013  // arg = 1;
24014  }
24015  break;
24016 
24017  /* Always uses one arg */
24018  case 'a':
24019  case 'A':
24020  case 'h':
24021  case 'H':
24022  if (currentarg >= params) {
24023  os->setException(OS::String::format(os, "type %c: not enough arguments", code));
24024  os->free(formatcodes);
24025  os->free(formatargs);
24026  return 0;
24027  }
24028 
24029  if (arg < 0) {
24030  OS::String str = os->toString(offs + currentarg);
24031  os->core->stack_values[offs + currentarg] = Core::Value(str);
24032  arg = str.getLen();
24033  }
24034 
24035  currentarg++;
24036  break;
24037 
24038  /* Use as many args as specified */
24039  case 'c':
24040  case 'C':
24041  case 's':
24042  case 'S':
24043  case 'i':
24044  case 'I':
24045  case 'l':
24046  case 'L':
24047  case 'n':
24048  case 'N':
24049  case 'v':
24050  case 'V':
24051  case 'f':
24052  case 'd':
24053  if (arg < 0) {
24054  arg = params - currentarg;
24055  }
24056 
24057  currentarg += arg;
24058 
24059  if (currentarg > params) {
24060  os->setException(OS::String::format(os, "type %c: too few arguments", code));
24061  os->free(formatcodes);
24062  os->free(formatargs);
24063  return 0;
24064  }
24065  break;
24066 
24067  default:
24068  os->setException(OS::String::format(os, "type %c: unknown format code", code));
24069  os->free(formatcodes);
24070  os->free(formatargs);
24071  return 0;
24072  }
24073 
24074  formatcodes[formatcount] = code;
24075  formatargs[formatcount] = arg;
24076  }
24077 
24078  if (currentarg < params) {
24079  os->setException(OS::String::format(os, "%d arguments unused", params - currentarg));
24080  os->free(formatcodes);
24081  os->free(formatargs);
24082  return 0;
24083  }
24084 
24085  /* Calculate output length and upper bound while processing*/
24086 #define OS_INC_OUTPUTPOS(a,b) \
24087  if ((a) < 0 || ((INT_MAX - outputpos)/((int)b)) < (a)) { \
24088  os->setException(OS::String::format(os, "Type %c: integer overflow in format string", code)); \
24089  os->free(formatcodes); \
24090  os->free(formatargs); \
24091  return 0; \
24092  } \
24093  outputpos += (a)*(b);
24094 
24095  int outputpos = 0, outputsize = 0;
24096  for (i = 0; i < formatcount; i++) {
24097  char code = formatcodes[i];
24098  int arg = formatargs[i];
24099 
24100  switch (code) {
24101  case 'h':
24102  case 'H':
24103  OS_INC_OUTPUTPOS((arg + (arg % 2)) / 2, 1) /* 4 bit per arg */
24104  break;
24105 
24106  case 'a':
24107  case 'A':
24108  case 'c':
24109  case 'C':
24110  case 'x':
24111  OS_INC_OUTPUTPOS(arg, 1) /* 8 bit per arg */
24112  break;
24113 
24114  case 's':
24115  case 'S':
24116  case 'n':
24117  case 'v':
24118  OS_INC_OUTPUTPOS(arg, 2) /* 16 bit per arg */
24119  break;
24120 
24121  case 'i':
24122  case 'I':
24123  OS_INC_OUTPUTPOS(arg, sizeof(int))
24124  break;
24125 
24126  case 'l':
24127  case 'L':
24128  case 'N':
24129  case 'V':
24130  OS_INC_OUTPUTPOS(arg, 4) /* 32 bit per arg */
24131  break;
24132 
24133  case 'f':
24134  OS_INC_OUTPUTPOS(arg, sizeof(float))
24135  break;
24136 
24137  case 'd':
24138  OS_INC_OUTPUTPOS(arg, sizeof(double))
24139  break;
24140 
24141  case 'X':
24142  outputpos -= arg;
24143 
24144  if (outputpos < 0) {
24145  os->setException(OS::String::format(os, "type %c: outside of string", code));
24146  os->free(formatcodes);
24147  os->free(formatargs);
24148  return 0;
24149  // outputpos = 0;
24150  }
24151  break;
24152 
24153  case '@':
24154  outputpos = arg;
24155  break;
24156  }
24157 
24158  if (outputsize < outputpos) {
24159  outputsize = outputpos;
24160  }
24161  }
24162 
24163  Core::Buffer buf(os);
24164  buf.reserveCapacity(outputsize + 1);
24165  char * output = (char*)buf.buffer.buf;
24166  outputpos = 0;
24167  currentarg = 1;
24168 
24169  /* Do actual packing */
24170  for (i = 0; i < formatcount; i++) {
24171  char code = formatcodes[i];
24172  int arg = formatargs[i];
24173  switch (code) {
24174  case 'a':
24175  case 'A': {
24176  memset(&output[outputpos], (code == 'a') ? '\0' : ' ', arg);
24177  OS::String val = os->toString(offs + currentarg++);
24178  const char * str = val.toChar();
24179  int len = val.getLen();
24180  memcpy(&output[outputpos], str, len < arg ? len : arg);
24181  outputpos += arg;
24182  break;
24183  }
24184 
24185  case 'h':
24186  case 'H': {
24187  int nibbleshift = (code == 'h') ? 0 : 4;
24188  int first = 1;
24189 
24190  OS::String val = os->toString(offs + currentarg++);
24191  const char * v = val.toChar();
24192  int len = val.getLen();
24193 
24194  outputpos--;
24195  if(arg > len) {
24196  os->setException(OS::String::format(os, "type %c: not enough characters in string", code));
24197  os->free(formatcodes);
24198  os->free(formatargs);
24199  return 0;
24200  // arg = len;
24201  }
24202 
24203  while (arg-- > 0) {
24204  char n = *v++;
24205 
24206  if (n >= '0' && n <= '9') {
24207  n -= '0';
24208  } else if (n >= 'A' && n <= 'F') {
24209  n -= ('A' - 10);
24210  } else if (n >= 'a' && n <= 'f') {
24211  n -= ('a' - 10);
24212  } else {
24213  os->setException(OS::String::format(os, "type %c: illegal hex digit %c", code, n));
24214  os->free(formatcodes);
24215  os->free(formatargs);
24216  return 0;
24217  // n = 0;
24218  }
24219 
24220  if (first--) {
24221  output[++outputpos] = 0;
24222  } else {
24223  first = 1;
24224  }
24225 
24226  output[outputpos] |= (n << nibbleshift);
24227  nibbleshift = (nibbleshift + 4) & 7;
24228  }
24229 
24230  outputpos++;
24231  break;
24232  }
24233 
24234  case 'c':
24235  case 'C':
24236  while (arg-- > 0) {
24237  packLong((long)os->toNumber(offs + currentarg++), 1, byte_map, &output[outputpos]);
24238  outputpos++;
24239  }
24240  break;
24241 
24242  case 's':
24243  case 'S':
24244  case 'n':
24245  case 'v': {
24246  int *map = machine_endian_short_map;
24247  if (code == 'n') {
24248  map = big_endian_short_map;
24249  } else if (code == 'v') {
24250  map = little_endian_short_map;
24251  }
24252  while (arg-- > 0) {
24253  packLong((long)os->toNumber(offs + currentarg++), 2, map, &output[outputpos]);
24254  outputpos += 2;
24255  }
24256  break;
24257  }
24258 
24259  case 'i':
24260  case 'I':
24261  while (arg-- > 0) {
24262  packLong((long)os->toNumber(offs + currentarg++), sizeof(int), int_map, &output[outputpos]);
24263  outputpos += sizeof(int);
24264  }
24265  break;
24266 
24267  case 'l':
24268  case 'L':
24269  case 'N':
24270  case 'V': {
24271  int *map = machine_endian_long_map;
24272  if (code == 'N') {
24273  map = big_endian_long_map;
24274  } else if (code == 'V') {
24275  map = little_endian_long_map;
24276  }
24277  while (arg-- > 0) {
24278  packLong((long)os->toNumber(offs + currentarg++), 4, map, &output[outputpos]);
24279  outputpos += 4;
24280  }
24281  break;
24282  }
24283 
24284  case 'f': {
24285  while (arg-- > 0) {
24286  float v = os->toFloat(offs + currentarg++);
24287  memcpy(&output[outputpos], &v, sizeof(v));
24288  outputpos += sizeof(v);
24289  }
24290  break;
24291  }
24292 
24293  case 'd': {
24294  while (arg-- > 0) {
24295  double v = os->toDouble(offs + currentarg++);
24296  memcpy(&output[outputpos], &v, sizeof(v));
24297  outputpos += sizeof(v);
24298  }
24299  break;
24300  }
24301 
24302  case 'x':
24303  memset(&output[outputpos], '\0', arg);
24304  outputpos += arg;
24305  break;
24306 
24307  case 'X':
24308  outputpos -= arg;
24309  if (outputpos < 0) {
24310  outputpos = 0;
24311  }
24312  break;
24313 
24314  case '@':
24315  if (arg > outputpos) {
24316  memset(&output[outputpos], '\0', arg - outputpos);
24317  }
24318  outputpos = arg;
24319  break;
24320  }
24321  }
24322  os->free(formatcodes);
24323  os->free(formatargs);
24324  output[outputpos] = '\0';
24325  buf.buffer.count = outputpos;
24326  os->pushString(buf);
24327  return 1;
24328  }
24329 
24330  static long unpackLong(const char *data, int size, int issigned, int *map)
24331  {
24332  long result = issigned ? -1 : 0;
24333  char *cresult = (char *) &result;
24334  for (int i = 0; i < size; i++) {
24335  cresult[map[i]] = *data++;
24336  }
24337  return result;
24338  }
24339 
24340  /* unpack() is based on Perl's unpack(), but is modified a bit from there.
24341  * Numeric pack types will return numbers, a and A will return strings,
24342  * f and d will return doubles.
24343  * Implemented formats are A, a, h, H, c, C, s, S, i, I, l, L, n, N, f, d, x, X, @.
24344  */
24345  static int unpack(OS * os, int params, int, int, void*)
24346  {
24347  if(params < 1){
24348  return 0;
24349  }
24350 
24351  OS::String format_str = os->toString(-params+0);
24352  const char * format = format_str.toChar();
24353  int formatlen = format_str.getLen();
24354 
24355  OS::String input_str = os->toString(-params-1);
24356  const char * input = input_str.toChar();
24357  int inputlen = input_str.getLen();
24358  int inputpos = 0, ret_values = 0;
24359 
24360  while (formatlen-- > 0) {
24361  char type = *(format++);
24362  char c;
24363  int arg = 1, argb;
24364  int size=0;
24365 
24366  /* Handle format arguments if any */
24367  if (formatlen > 0) {
24368  c = *format;
24369 
24370  if (c >= '0' && c <= '9') {
24371  arg = 0; // atoi(format);
24372  while (formatlen > 0 && *format >= '0' && *format <= '9') {
24373  arg = arg*10 + (*format - '0');
24374  format++;
24375  formatlen--;
24376  }
24377  } else if (c == '*') {
24378  arg = -1;
24379  format++;
24380  formatlen--;
24381  }
24382  }
24383 
24384  /* Get of new value in array */
24385  argb = arg;
24386  switch (type) {
24387  /* Never use any input */
24388  case 'X':
24389  size = -1;
24390  break;
24391 
24392  case '@':
24393  size = 0;
24394  break;
24395 
24396  case 'a':
24397  case 'A':
24398  size = arg;
24399  arg = 1;
24400  break;
24401 
24402  case 'h':
24403  case 'H':
24404  size = (arg > 0) ? (arg + (arg % 2)) / 2 : arg;
24405  arg = 1;
24406  break;
24407 
24408  /* Use 1 byte of input */
24409  case 'c':
24410  case 'C':
24411  case 'x':
24412  size = 1;
24413  break;
24414 
24415  /* Use 2 bytes of input */
24416  case 's':
24417  case 'S':
24418  case 'n':
24419  case 'v':
24420  size = 2;
24421  break;
24422 
24423  /* Use sizeof(int) bytes of input */
24424  case 'i':
24425  case 'I':
24426  size = sizeof(int);
24427  break;
24428 
24429  /* Use 4 bytes of input */
24430  case 'l':
24431  case 'L':
24432  case 'N':
24433  case 'V':
24434  size = 4;
24435  break;
24436 
24437  /* Use sizeof(float) bytes of input */
24438  case 'f':
24439  size = sizeof(float);
24440  break;
24441 
24442  /* Use sizeof(double) bytes of input */
24443  case 'd':
24444  size = sizeof(double);
24445  break;
24446 
24447  default:
24448  os->setException(OS::String::format(os, "invalid format type %c", type));
24449  return 0;
24450  }
24451 
24452  /* Do actual unpacking */
24453  for (int i = 0; i != arg; i++ ) {
24454  /* Space for name + number, safe as namelen is ensured <= 200 */
24455  /* char n[256];
24456  if (arg != 1 || namelen == 0) {
24457  // Need to add element number to name
24458  snprintf(n, sizeof(n), "%.*s%d", namelen, name, i + 1);
24459  } else {
24460  // Truncate name to next format code or end of string
24461  snprintf(n, sizeof(n), "%.*s", namelen, name);
24462  } */
24463 
24464  if (size != 0 && size != -1 && INT_MAX - size + 1 < inputpos) {
24465  os->setException(OS::String::format(os, "type %c: integer overflow", type));
24466  return 0;
24467  // inputpos = 0;
24468  }
24469 
24470  if ((inputpos + size) <= inputlen) {
24471  switch ((int) type) {
24472  case 'a':
24473  case 'A': {
24474  char pad = (type == 'a') ? '\0' : ' ';
24475  int len = inputlen - inputpos; /* Remaining string */
24476 
24477  /* If size was given take minimum of len and size */
24478  if ((size >= 0) && (len > size)) {
24479  len = size;
24480  }
24481 
24482  size = len;
24483 
24484  /* Remove padding chars from unpacked data */
24485  while (--len >= 0) {
24486  if (input[inputpos + len] != pad)
24487  break;
24488  }
24489  ret_values++;
24490  os->pushString(&input[inputpos], len + 1);
24491  // add_assoc_stringl(return_value, n, &input[inputpos], len + 1, 1);
24492  break;
24493  }
24494 
24495  case 'h':
24496  case 'H': {
24497  int len = (inputlen - inputpos) * 2; /* Remaining */
24498  int nibbleshift = (type == 'h') ? 0 : 4;
24499  int first = 1;
24500  char *buf;
24501  int ipos, opos;
24502 
24503  /* If size was given take minimum of len and size */
24504  if (size >= 0 && len > (size * 2)) {
24505  len = size * 2;
24506  }
24507 
24508  if (argb > 0) {
24509  len -= argb % 2;
24510  }
24511 
24512  buf = (char*)os->malloc(len + 1 OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
24513  for (ipos = opos = 0; opos < len; opos++) {
24514  char cc = (input[inputpos + ipos] >> nibbleshift) & 0xf;
24515 
24516  if (cc < 10) {
24517  cc += '0';
24518  } else {
24519  cc += 'a' - 10;
24520  }
24521 
24522  buf[opos] = cc;
24523  nibbleshift = (nibbleshift + 4) & 7;
24524 
24525  if (first-- == 0) {
24526  ipos++;
24527  first = 1;
24528  }
24529  }
24530 
24531  buf[len] = '\0';
24532  ret_values++;
24533  os->pushString(buf, len);
24534  // add_assoc_stringl(return_value, n, buf, len, 1);
24535  os->free(buf);
24536  break;
24537  }
24538 
24539  case 'c':
24540  case 'C': {
24541  int issigned = (type == 'c') ? (input[inputpos] & 0x80) : 0;
24542  long v = unpackLong(&input[inputpos], 1, issigned, byte_map);
24543  ret_values++;
24544  os->pushNumber(v);
24545  // add_assoc_long(return_value, n, v);
24546  break;
24547  }
24548 
24549  case 's':
24550  case 'S':
24551  case 'n':
24552  case 'v': {
24553  long v;
24554  int issigned = 0;
24555  int *map = machine_endian_short_map;
24556 
24557  if (type == 's') {
24558  issigned = input[inputpos + (machine_little_endian ? 1 : 0)] & 0x80;
24559  } else if (type == 'n') {
24560  map = big_endian_short_map;
24561  } else if (type == 'v') {
24562  map = little_endian_short_map;
24563  }
24564 
24565  v = unpackLong(&input[inputpos], 2, issigned, map);
24566  ret_values++;
24567  os->pushNumber(v);
24568  // add_assoc_long(return_value, n, v);
24569  break;
24570  }
24571 
24572  case 'i':
24573  case 'I': {
24574  long v;
24575  int issigned = 0;
24576 
24577  if (type == 'i') {
24578  issigned = input[inputpos + (machine_little_endian ? (sizeof(int) - 1) : 0)] & 0x80;
24579  }
24580 
24581  v = unpackLong(&input[inputpos], sizeof(int), issigned, int_map);
24582  ret_values++;
24583  os->pushNumber(v);
24584  // add_assoc_long(return_value, n, v);
24585  break;
24586  }
24587 
24588  case 'l':
24589  case 'L':
24590  case 'N':
24591  case 'V': {
24592  int issigned = 0;
24593  int *map = machine_endian_long_map;
24594  long v = 0;
24595 
24596  if (type == 'l' || type == 'L') {
24597  issigned = input[inputpos + (machine_little_endian ? 3 : 0)] & 0x80;
24598  } else if (type == 'N') {
24599  issigned = input[inputpos] & 0x80;
24600  map = big_endian_long_map;
24601  } else if (type == 'V') {
24602  issigned = input[inputpos + 3] & 0x80;
24603  map = little_endian_long_map;
24604  }
24605 
24606  if (sizeof(long) > 4 && issigned) {
24607  v = ~INT_MAX;
24608  }
24609 
24610  v |= unpackLong(&input[inputpos], 4, issigned, map);
24611  if (sizeof(long) > 4) {
24612  if (type == 'l') {
24613  v = (signed int) v;
24614  } else {
24615  v = (unsigned int) v;
24616  }
24617  }
24618  ret_values++;
24619  os->pushNumber(v);
24620  // add_assoc_long(return_value, n, v);
24621  break;
24622  }
24623 
24624  case 'f': {
24625  float v;
24626  memcpy(&v, &input[inputpos], sizeof(float));
24627  ret_values++;
24628  os->pushNumber(v);
24629  // add_assoc_double(return_value, n, (double)v);
24630  break;
24631  }
24632 
24633  case 'd': {
24634  double v;
24635  memcpy(&v, &input[inputpos], sizeof(double));
24636  ret_values++;
24637  os->pushNumber(v);
24638  // add_assoc_double(return_value, n, v);
24639  break;
24640  }
24641 
24642  case 'x':
24643  /* Do nothing with input, just skip it */
24644  break;
24645 
24646  case 'X':
24647  if (inputpos < size) {
24648  inputpos = -size;
24649  i = arg - 1; /* Break out of for loop */
24650 
24651  if (arg >= 0) {
24652  os->setException(OS::String::format(os, "type %c: outside of string", type));
24653  return 0;
24654  }
24655  }
24656  break;
24657 
24658  case '@':
24659  if (arg <= inputlen) {
24660  inputpos = arg;
24661  } else {
24662  os->setException(OS::String::format(os, "type %c: outside of string", type));
24663  return 0;
24664  }
24665 
24666  i = arg - 1; /* Done, break out of for loop */
24667  break;
24668  }
24669 
24670  inputpos += size;
24671  if (inputpos < 0) {
24672  if (size != -1) { /* only print warning if not working with * */
24673  os->setException(OS::String::format(os, "type %c: outside of string", type));
24674  return 0;
24675  }
24676  inputpos = 0;
24677  }
24678  } else if (arg < 0) {
24679  /* Reached end of input for '*' repeater */
24680  break;
24681  } else {
24682  os->setException(OS::String::format(os, "type %c: not enough input, need %d, have %d", type, size, inputlen - inputpos));
24683  return 0;
24684  }
24685  }
24686 
24687  // formatlen--; /* Skip '/' separator, does no harm if inputlen == 0 */
24688  // format++;
24689  }
24690  return ret_values;
24691  }
24692 
24693  static void init()
24694  {
24695  int machine_endian_check = 1;
24696  machine_little_endian = ((char *)&machine_endian_check)[0];
24697  if (machine_little_endian) {
24698  OS_ASSERT(IS_LITTLE_ENDIAN);
24699  /* Where to get lo to hi bytes from */
24700  byte_map[0] = 0;
24701  for (int i = 0; i < (int)sizeof(int); i++) {
24702  int_map[i] = i;
24703  }
24704 
24705  machine_endian_short_map[0] = 0;
24706  machine_endian_short_map[1] = 1;
24707  big_endian_short_map[0] = 1;
24708  big_endian_short_map[1] = 0;
24709  little_endian_short_map[0] = 0;
24710  little_endian_short_map[1] = 1;
24711 
24712  machine_endian_long_map[0] = 0;
24713  machine_endian_long_map[1] = 1;
24714  machine_endian_long_map[2] = 2;
24715  machine_endian_long_map[3] = 3;
24716  big_endian_long_map[0] = 3;
24717  big_endian_long_map[1] = 2;
24718  big_endian_long_map[2] = 1;
24719  big_endian_long_map[3] = 0;
24720  little_endian_long_map[0] = 0;
24721  little_endian_long_map[1] = 1;
24722  little_endian_long_map[2] = 2;
24723  little_endian_long_map[3] = 3;
24724  }else{
24725  OS_ASSERT(!IS_LITTLE_ENDIAN);
24726  // zval val;
24727  // int size = sizeof(Z_LVAL(val));
24728  // Z_LVAL(val)=0; /*silence a warning*/
24729  int size = sizeof(long);
24730 
24731  /* Where to get hi to lo bytes from */
24732  byte_map[0] = size - 1;
24733  for (int i = 0; i < (int)sizeof(int); i++) {
24734  int_map[i] = size - (sizeof(int) - i);
24735  }
24736 
24737  machine_endian_short_map[0] = size - 2;
24738  machine_endian_short_map[1] = size - 1;
24739  big_endian_short_map[0] = size - 2;
24740  big_endian_short_map[1] = size - 1;
24741  little_endian_short_map[0] = size - 1;
24742  little_endian_short_map[1] = size - 2;
24743 
24744  machine_endian_long_map[0] = size - 4;
24745  machine_endian_long_map[1] = size - 3;
24746  machine_endian_long_map[2] = size - 2;
24747  machine_endian_long_map[3] = size - 1;
24748  big_endian_long_map[0] = size - 4;
24749  big_endian_long_map[1] = size - 3;
24750  big_endian_long_map[2] = size - 2;
24751  big_endian_long_map[3] = size - 1;
24752  little_endian_long_map[0] = size - 1;
24753  little_endian_long_map[1] = size - 2;
24754  little_endian_long_map[2] = size - 3;
24755  little_endian_long_map[3] = size - 4;
24756  }
24757  }
24758  };
24759 
24760  struct String
24761  {
24762  static int length(OS * os, int params, int, int, void*)
24763  {
24764  os->pushNumber(os->toString(-params-1).getLen());
24765  return 1;
24766  }
24767 
24768  static int lengthUtf8(OS * os, int params, int, int, void*)
24769  {
24770  int len = 0;
24771  OS::String str = os->toString(-params-1);
24772  const OS_BYTE * string = (OS_BYTE*)str.toChar();
24773  const OS_BYTE * end = string + str.getDataSize();
24774  while(string < end){
24775  len++;
24776  UTF8_SKIP_MULTI_BYTE_SEQUENCE(string, end);
24777  }
24778  os->pushNumber(len);
24779  return 1;
24780  }
24781 
24782  static int sub(OS * os, int params, int, int, void*)
24783  {
24784  int start, len;
24785  OS::String str = os->toString(-params-1);
24786  int size = str.getLen();
24787  switch(params){
24788  case 0:
24789  os->pushStackValue(-params-1);
24790  return 1;
24791 
24792  case 1:
24793  start = os->toInt(-params);
24794  len = size;
24795  break;
24796 
24797  default:
24798  start = os->toInt(-params);
24799  len = os->toInt(-params+1);
24800  }
24801  if(start < 0){
24802  start = size + start;
24803  if(start < 0){
24804  start = 0;
24805  }
24806  }
24807  if(start >= size){
24808  os->pushString(OS_TEXT(""));
24809  return 1;
24810  }
24811  if(len < 0){
24812  len = size - start + len;
24813  }
24814  if(len <= 0){
24815  os->pushString(OS_TEXT(""));
24816  return 1;
24817  }
24818  if(start + len > size){
24819  len = size - start;
24820  }
24821  if(!start && len == size){
24822  os->pushStackValue(-params-1);
24823  return 1;
24824  }
24825  os->pushString(str.toChar() + start, len);
24826  return 1;
24827  }
24828 
24829  static int subUtf8(OS * os, int params, int, int, void*)
24830  {
24831  int start, len;
24832  OS::String str = os->toString(-params-1);
24833 
24834  int size = 0;
24835  const OS_BYTE * string = (OS_BYTE*)str.toChar();
24836  const OS_BYTE * end = string + str.getDataSize();
24837  while(string < end){
24838  size++;
24839  UTF8_SKIP_MULTI_BYTE_SEQUENCE(string, end);
24840  }
24841 
24842  switch(params){
24843  case 0:
24844  os->pushStackValue(-params-1);
24845  return 1;
24846 
24847  case 1:
24848  start = os->toInt(-params);
24849  len = size;
24850  break;
24851 
24852  default:
24853  start = os->toInt(-params);
24854  len = os->toInt(-params+1);
24855  }
24856  if(start < 0){
24857  start = size + start;
24858  if(start < 0){
24859  start = 0;
24860  }
24861  }
24862  if(start >= size){
24863  os->pushString(OS_TEXT(""));
24864  return 1;
24865  }
24866  if(len < 0){
24867  len = size - start + len;
24868  }
24869  if(len <= 0){
24870  os->pushString(OS_TEXT(""));
24871  return 1;
24872  }
24873  if(start + len > size){
24874  len = size - start;
24875  }
24876  if(!start && len == size){
24877  os->pushStackValue(-params-1);
24878  return 1;
24879  }
24880 
24881  string = (OS_BYTE*)str.toChar();
24882  for(; start > 0; start--){
24883  UTF8_SKIP_MULTI_BYTE_SEQUENCE(string, end);
24884  }
24885  const OS_BYTE * cur_end = string;
24886  for(; len > 0; len--){
24887  UTF8_SKIP_MULTI_BYTE_SEQUENCE(cur_end, end);
24888  }
24889 
24890  size = (int)(cur_end - string);
24891  os->pushString((void*)string, size);
24892  return 1;
24893  }
24894 
24895  static int replace(OS * os, int params, int, int, void*)
24896  {
24897  OS::String subject = os->toString(-params-1);
24898  int subject_len = subject.getLen();
24899  if(params >= 1){
24900  if(!os->isString(-params)){
24901  int offs = os->getAbsoluteOffs(-params);
24902  os->getGlobal(OS_TEXT("Regexp"), false);
24903  bool is_reg_exp = os->is(offs, -1);
24904  os->pop(1);
24905  if(is_reg_exp){
24906  os->pushStackValue(offs);
24907  os->getProperty(OS_TEXT("replace"));
24908  OS_ASSERT(os->isFunction());
24909  os->pushStackValue(offs); // this for function
24910  os->pushString(subject);
24911  if(params >= 2) os->pushStackValue(offs+1);
24912  if(params >= 3) os->pushStackValue(offs+2);
24913  os->callFT(params >= 3 ? 3 : params, 1, OS_CALLTYPE_FUNC);
24914  return 1;
24915  }
24916  if(os->isObject(-params)){
24917  os->pushStackValue(-params);
24918  while(os->nextIteratorStep()){
24919  os->pushCFunction(replace);
24920  os->pushString(subject);
24921  os->pushStackValue(-4);
24922  os->pushStackValue(-4);
24923  os->callFT(2, 1, OS_CALLTYPE_FUNC);
24924  subject = os->toString();
24925  os->pop(3);
24926  }
24927  os->pushString(subject);
24928  return 1;
24929  }
24930  }
24931  OS::String search = os->toString(-params);
24932  int search_len = search.getLen();
24933  if(search_len > 0 && search_len <= subject_len){
24934  OS::String replace = params >= 2 ? os->toString(-params+1) : OS::String(os);
24935  int replace_len = replace.getLen();
24936 
24937  const OS_CHAR * subject_str = subject.toChar();
24938  const OS_CHAR * search_str = search.toChar();
24939 
24940  OS::Core::Buffer buf(os);
24941  bool found = false;
24942  int start = 0;
24943  for(int i = 0; i < subject_len-search_len+1;){
24944  if(OS_MEMCMP(subject_str + i, search_str, sizeof(OS_CHAR)*search_len) == 0){
24945  buf.append(subject_str + start, i - start);
24946  buf.append(replace, replace_len);
24947  i += search_len;
24948  start = i;
24949  found = true;
24950  }else{
24951  i++;
24952  }
24953  }
24954  if(found){
24955  buf.append(subject_str + start, subject_len - start);
24956  os->pushString(buf);
24957  return 1;
24958  }
24959  }
24960  }
24961  os->pushString(subject);
24962  return 1;
24963  }
24964 
24965  static int find(OS * os, int params, int, int, void*)
24966  {
24967  if(params >= 1){
24968  OS::String subject = os->toString(-params-1);
24969  int subject_len = subject.getLen();
24970  OS::String search = os->toString(-params);
24971  int search_len = search.getLen();
24972  int i = params >= 2 ? os->toInt(-params+1) : 0;
24973  if(search_len > 0 && search_len <= subject_len && i >= 0){
24974  const OS_CHAR * subject_str = subject.toChar();
24975  const OS_CHAR * search_str = search.toChar();
24976  int end = subject_len - search_len;
24977  for(; i <= end; i++){
24978  if(OS_MEMCMP(subject_str + i, search_str, sizeof(OS_CHAR)*search_len) == 0){
24979  os->pushNumber(i);
24980  return 1;
24981  }
24982  }
24983  }
24984  }
24985  return 0;
24986  }
24987 
24988  static int findUtf8(OS * os, int params, int closure_values, int need_ret_values, void * user_param)
24989  {
24990  int offs = os->getAbsoluteOffs(-params-1);
24991  OS::String subject = os->toString(offs);
24992  if(os->getType(offs) != OS_VALUE_TYPE_STRING){
24993  os->core->stack_values[offs] = Core::Value(subject);
24994  }
24995  int ret = find(os, params, closure_values, need_ret_values, user_param);
24996  if(ret > 0){
24997  int pos = os->toInt(-ret);
24998  int subject_len = subject.getLen();
24999  OS_ASSERT(pos < subject_len);
25000  const OS_CHAR * start = subject.toChar();
25001  const OS_CHAR * end = start + pos;
25002  int new_pos = 0;
25003  for(; start < end; new_pos++){
25004  UTF8_SKIP_MULTI_BYTE_SEQUENCE(start, end);
25005  }
25006  if(start != end){
25007  os->setException(OS_TEXT("find utf-8 error: illegal seq"));
25008  return 0;
25009  }
25010  os->pushNumber(new_pos);
25011  return 1;
25012  }
25013  return 0;
25014  }

25016  static int compare(OS * os, int left_offs, int right_offs)
25017  {
25018 #if 1
25019  OS::String left(os);
25020  if(!os->isString(left_offs, &left)){
25021  os->setException(OS::String::format(os, OS_TEXT("unsupported type %s for string comparizon"), os->getTypeStr(left_offs).toChar()));
25022  return 0;
25023  }
25024  OS::String right(os);
25025  if(!os->isString(right_offs, &right)){
25026  os->setException(OS::String::format(os, OS_TEXT("unsupported type %s for string comparizon"), os->getTypeStr(right_offs).toChar()));
25027  return 0;
25028  }
25029 #else
25030  OS::String left = os->toString(-params - 1);
25031  OS::String right = os->toString(-params + 0);
25032 #endif
25033  os->pushNumber(left.cmp(right));
25034  return 1;
25035  }

25040  return compare(os, -params - 1, -params + 0);
25041  }
25042  return 0;
25043  }

25046  {

25048  return compare(os, -params + 0, -params - 1);
25049  }
25050  return 0;
25051  }

25053  static int trim(OS * os, int params, int, int, void*)
25054  {

25056  bool trim_left = params >= 1 ? os->toBool(-params + 0) : true;
25057  bool trim_right = params >= 2 ? os->toBool(-params + 1) : true;
25058  os->pushString(str.trim(trim_left, trim_right));
25059  return 1;
25060  }

25062  static int upper(OS * os, int params, int, int, void*)
25063  {
25064  OS::String self = os->toString(-params - 1); // this
25065  const OS_CHAR * str = self.toChar();
25066  int len = self.getLen();
25067  for(int i = 0; i < len; i++){
25068  OS_CHAR c = OS_CHAR_UPPER(str[i]);
25069  if(c != str[i]){
25070  OS::Core::Buffer buf(os);
25071  buf.append(str, i);
25072  buf.append(c);
25073  for(i++; i < len; i++){
25074  buf.append(OS_CHAR_UPPER(str[i]));
25075  }
25076  os->pushString(buf);
25077  return 1;
25078  }
25079  }
25080  os->pushString(self);
25081  return 1;
25082  }

25106  static int split(OS * os, int params, int, int, void*)
25107  {
25108  int offs = os->getAbsoluteOffs(-params-1);
25109 
25110  os->newArray();
25111  int count = 0;
25112 
25113  OS::String subject = os->toString(offs);
25114  int subject_len = subject.getLen();
25115  if(params >= 1){
25116  if(!os->isString(offs+1)){
25117  os->getGlobal(OS_TEXT("Regexp"), false);
25118  bool is_reg_exp = os->is(offs+1, -1);
25119  os->pop(1);
25120  if(is_reg_exp){
25121  os->pushStackValue(offs+1);
25122  os->getProperty(OS_TEXT("split"));
25123  OS_ASSERT(os->isFunction());
25124  os->pushStackValue(offs+1); // this for function
25125  os->pushString(subject);
25126  if(params >= 2) os->pushStackValue(offs+2); // limit
25127  if(params >= 3) os->pushStackValue(offs+3); // flags
25128  os->callFT(params >= 3 ? 3 : params, 1, OS_CALLTYPE_FUNC);
25129  return 1;
25130  }
25131  }
25132  OS::String search = os->toString(offs+1);
25133  int search_len = search.getLen();
25134  if(search_len > 0 && search_len <= subject_len){
25135  const OS_CHAR * subject_str = subject.toChar();
25136  const OS_CHAR * search_str = search.toChar();
25137 
25138  int max_count = params >= 2 ? os->toInt(offs+2) : INT_MAX;
25139  if(max_count > 1){
25140  bool found = false;
25141  int start = 0;
25142  for(int i = 0; i < subject_len-search_len+1;){
25143  if(OS_MEMCMP(subject_str + i, search_str, sizeof(OS_CHAR)*search_len) == 0){
25144  os->pushStackValue();
25145  os->pushNumber(count++);
25146  os->pushString(subject_str + start, i - start);
25147  os->setProperty();
25148  i += search_len;
25149  start = i;
25150  found = true;
25151  if(count+1 >= max_count){
25152  break;
25153  }
25154  }else{
25155  i++;
25156  }
25157  }
25158  if(found){
25159  os->pushStackValue();
25160  os->pushNumber(count++);
25161  os->pushString(subject_str + start, subject_len - start);
25162  os->setProperty();
25163  return 1;
25164  }
25165  }
25166  }
25167  }
25168  os->pushStackValue();
25169  os->pushNumber(0);
25170  os->pushString(subject);
25171  os->setProperty();
25172  return 1;
25173  }

25474 void OS::initFunctionClass()

25476  struct Function
25477  {
25478  /* static int construct(OS * os, int params, int, int, void*)
25479  {
25480  // TODO: correct?

25484  static int applyEnv(OS * os, int params, int, int need_ret_values, void *)
25485  {
25486  Core::Value save_env;

25488  if(OS_VALUE_TYPE(func) == OS_VALUE_TYPE_FUNCTION){
25489  save_env = OS_VALUE_VARIANT(func).func->env;
25490  OS_VALUE_VARIANT(func).func->env = os->core->getStackValue(-params).getGCValue();
25491  }
25492  os->remove(-params);
25493  int r = Core::prototypeFunctionApply(os, params-1, 0, need_ret_values, NULL);
25494  if(OS_VALUE_TYPE(func) == OS_VALUE_TYPE_FUNCTION){
25495  OS_VALUE_VARIANT(func).func->env = save_env;
25496  }
25497  return r;
25498  }
25499 
25500  static int callEnv(OS * os, int params, int, int need_ret_values, void *)
25501  {
25502  Core::Value save_env;
25503  Core::Value func = os->core->getStackValue(-params-1);
25504  if(OS_VALUE_TYPE(func) == OS_VALUE_TYPE_FUNCTION){
25505  save_env = OS_VALUE_VARIANT(func).func->env;
25506  OS_VALUE_VARIANT(func).func->env = os->core->getStackValue(-params).getGCValue();
25507  }
25508  os->remove(-params);
25509  int r = Core::prototypeFunctionCall(os, params-1, 0, need_ret_values, NULL);
25510  if(OS_VALUE_TYPE(func) == OS_VALUE_TYPE_FUNCTION){
25511  OS_VALUE_VARIANT(func).func->env = save_env;
25512  }
25513  return r;
25514  }
25515  };
25516  FuncDef list[] = {
25517  // {core->strings->__construct, Function::construct},
25518  {OS_TEXT("applyEnv"), Function::applyEnv},
25519  {OS_TEXT("callEnv"), Function::callEnv},
25520  {}
25521  };
25522  core->pushValue(core->prototypes[Core::PROTOTYPE_FUNCTION]);
25523  setFuncs(list);
25524  pop();
25525 }
25526 
25527 /*
25528 The following functions are based on a C++ class MTRand by
25529 Richard J. Wagner. For more information see the web page at
25530 http://www-personal.engin.umich.edu/~wagnerr/MersenneTwister.html
25531 
25532 It's port from PHP framework.
25533 */
25534 
25535 #define OS_RAND_N RAND_STATE_SIZE /* length of state vector */
25536 #define OS_RAND_M (397) /* a period parameter */
25537 #define OS_RAND_hiBit(u) ((u) & 0x80000000U) /* mask all but highest bit of u */
25538 #define OS_RAND_loBit(u) ((u) & 0x00000001U) /* mask all but lowest bit of u */
25539 #define OS_RAND_loBits(u) ((u) & 0x7FFFFFFFU) /* mask the highest bit of u */
25540 #define OS_RAND_mixBits(u, v) (OS_RAND_hiBit(u)|OS_RAND_loBits(v)) /* move hi bit of u to hi bit of v */
25541 
25542 #define OS_RAND_twist(m,u,v) (m ^ (OS_RAND_mixBits(u,v)>>1) ^ ((OS_U32)(-(OS_INT32)(OS_RAND_loBit(u))) & 0x9908b0dfU))
25543 #define OS_RAND_MAX 0x7FFFFFFF /* (1<<31) - 1 */
25544 
25545 #define OS_RAND_RANGE(__n, __min, __max, __tmax) \
25546  (__n) = (__min) + (long) ((double) ( (double) (__max) - (__min) + 1.0) * ((__n) / ((__tmax) + 1.0)))
25547 
25548 #if defined _MSC_VER && !defined IW_SDK
25549 #include <windows.h>
25550 #define OS_RAND_GENERATE_SEED() (((long) (time(0) * GetCurrentProcessId())) ^ ((long) (1000000.0)))
25551 // #elif !defined IW_SDK
25552 // #define OS_RAND_GENERATE_SEED() (((long) (time(0) * getpid())) ^ ((long) (1000000.0)))
25553 #else
25554 #define OS_RAND_GENERATE_SEED() (((long) (time(0))) ^ ((long) (1000000.0)))
25555 #endif
25556 
25557 int OS::Core::getRandSeed()
25558 {
25559  return rand_seed;
25560 }
25561 
25562 void OS::Core::setRandSeed(int seed)
25563 {
25564  rand_seed = (OS_U32)seed;
25565 
25566  OS_U32 * s = rand_state;
25567  OS_U32 * r = s;
25568 
25569  *s++ = seed & 0xffffffffU;
25570  for(int i = 1; i < OS_RAND_N; ++i ) {
25571  *s++ = ( 1812433253U * ( *r ^ (*r >> 30) ) + i ) & 0xffffffffU;
25572  r++;
25573  }
25574 
25575  randReload();
25576 }
25577 
25578 void OS::Core::randReload()
25579 {
25580  /* Generate N new values in state
25581  Made clearer and faster by Matthew Bellew (matthew.bellew@home.com) */
25582 
25583  OS_U32 * state = rand_state;
25584  OS_U32 * p = state;
25585  int i;
25586 
25587  for(i = OS_RAND_N - OS_RAND_M; i--; ++p){
25588  *p = OS_RAND_twist(p[OS_RAND_M], p[0], p[1]);
25589  }
25590  for(i = OS_RAND_M; --i; ++p){
25591  *p = OS_RAND_twist(p[OS_RAND_M-OS_RAND_N], p[0], p[1]);
25592  }
25593  *p = OS_RAND_twist(p[OS_RAND_M-OS_RAND_N], p[0], state[0]);
25594  rand_left = OS_RAND_N;
25595  rand_next = state;
25596 }
25597 
25598 double OS::Core::getRand()
25599 {
25600  /* Pull a 32-bit integer from the generator state
25601  Every other access function simply transforms the numbers extracted here */
25602 
25603  if(!rand_left){
25604  if(!rand_next){
25605  setRandSeed(OS_RAND_GENERATE_SEED());
25606  }else{
25607  randReload();
25608  }
25609  }
25610  --rand_left;
25611 
25612  OS_U32 s1 = *rand_next++;
25613  s1 ^= (s1 >> 11);
25614  s1 ^= (s1 << 7) & 0x9d2c5680U;
25615  s1 ^= (s1 << 15) & 0xefc60000U;
25616  return (double)((s1 ^ (s1 >> 18))>>1) / (double)OS_RAND_MAX;
25617 }
25618 
25619 double OS::Core::getRand(double up)
25620 {
25621  return ::floor(getRand()*(up-1) + 0.5);
25622 }
25623 
25624 double OS::Core::getRand(double min, double max)
25625 {
25626  return getRand() * (max - min) + min;
25627 }

25682 void OS::initMathModule()
25683 {
25684  struct Math
25685  {
25686  static int minmax(OS * os, int params, OS_EOpcode opcode)
25687  {
25688  OS_ASSERT(params >= 0);
25689  if(params <= 1){
25690  return params;
25691  }
25692  int params_offs = os->getAbsoluteOffs(-params);
25693  os->pushStackValue(params_offs); // save temp result
25694  for(int i = 1; i < params; i++){
25695  os->pushStackValue(-1); // copy temp result
25696  os->pushStackValue(params_offs + i);
25697  os->runOp(opcode); // remove params & push op result
25698  if(!os->toBool()){
25699  os->pop(2); // remove op result and temp result
25700  os->pushStackValue(params_offs + i); // save temp result
25701  continue;
25702  }
25703  os->pop();
25704  }
25705  return 1;
25706  }
25707

25709  {
25710  return minmax(os, params, OP_LOGIC_LE);
25711  }
25712 
25713  static int max_func(OS * os, int params, int, int, void*)
25714  {
25715  return minmax(os, params, OP_LOGIC_GE);
25716  }

25984 void OS::initJsonModule()
25985 {
25986  struct Lib
25987  {
25988  static int encode(OS * os, int params, int, int, void*)
25989  {
25990  if(params > 0){
25991  int offs = os->getAbsoluteOffs(-params+0);
25992  os->getGlobal(OS_TEXT("Object"));
25993  os->getProperty(OS_TEXT("toJson"));
25994  os->pushNull();
25995  os->pushStackValue(offs);
25996  os->callFT(1, 1, OS_CALLTYPE_FUNC);
25997  return 1;
25998  }
25999  return 0;
26000  }
26001 
26002  static int decode(OS * os, int params, int, int, void*)
26003  {
26004  if(params > 0){
26005  int ret = 0;
26006  OS * new_os = OS::create(os->memory_manager);
26007  {
26008  OS::Core::Buffer buf(new_os);
26009  buf += OS_TEXT("return (");
26010  OS::String str = os->toString(-params+0);
26011  if(str.getLen() >= 3 && OS_STRNCMP(str.toChar(), OS_TEXT("\xef\xbb\xbf"), 3) == 0){
26012  buf.append(str.toChar()+3, str.getLen()-3); // skip utf8 BOM
26013  }else{
26014  buf += str;
26015  }
26016  buf += OS_TEXT(")");
26017 
26018  new_os->compile(buf.toStringOS(), OS_SOURCECODE_PLAIN, false);
26019  /* new_os->getGlobal(OS_TEXT("compileText"));
26020  new_os->pushGlobals();
26021  new_os->pushString(buf);
26022  new_os->pushNumber(OS_SOURCECODE_PLAIN);
26023  new_os->pushBool(false);
26024  new_os->call(3, 1); */
26025  }
26026  if(new_os->isFunction()){
26027  new_os->pushNull();
26028  new_os->callFT(0, 1, OS_CALLTYPE_FUNC);
26029  os->core->pushCloneValueFrom(new_os, new_os->core->getStackValue(-1));
26030  ret = 1;
26031  }
26032  new_os->pop();
26033  new_os->release();
26034  return ret;
26035  }
26036  return 0;
26037  }
26038  };
26039 
26040  OS::FuncDef funcs[] = {
26041  {OS_TEXT("encode"), &Lib::encode},
26042  {OS_TEXT("decode"), &Lib::decode},
26043  {}
26044  };
26045 
26046  getModule(OS_TEXT("json"));
26047  setFuncs(funcs);
26048  pop();
26049 }

26143 void OS::initLangTokenizerModule()

26153 
26154  static int getTokenType(Core::TokenType type)
26155  {
26156  switch(type){
26157  case Core::Tokenizer::NAME:
26158  return TOKEN_TYPE_NAME;
26159 
26160  case Core::Tokenizer::STRING:
26161  return TOKEN_TYPE_STRING;
26162 
26163  case Core::Tokenizer::NUMBER:
26164  return TOKEN_TYPE_NUMBER;
26165  }
26166  return TOKEN_TYPE_OPERATOR;
26167  }
26168 
26169  static void pushTokensAsObject(OS * os, Core::Tokenizer& tokenizer)
26170  {
26171  os->newArray();
26172  int count = tokenizer.getNumTokens();
26173  for(int i = 0; i < count; i++){
26174  os->pushStackValue(-1);
26175  os->newObject();
26176  {
26177  Core::TokenData * token = tokenizer.getToken(i);
26178 
26179  os->pushStackValue(-1);
26180  os->pushString(OS_TEXT("str"));
26181  os->pushString(token->str);
26182  os->setProperty();
26183 #if 0
26184  os->pushStackValue(-1);
26185  os->pushString(OS_TEXT("line"));
26186  os->pushNumber(token->line+1);
26187  os->setProperty();
26188 
26189  os->pushStackValue(-1);
26190  os->pushString(OS_TEXT("pos"));
26191  os->pushNumber(token->pos+1);
26192  os->setProperty();
26193 #endif
26194  os->pushStackValue(-1);
26195  os->pushString(OS_TEXT("type"));
26196  int type = getTokenType(token->type);
26197  // os->printf("pushTokensAsObject: %d, %s\n", type, token->str.toChar());
26198  os->pushNumber(type);
26199  os->setProperty();
26200  }
26201  os->addProperty();
26202  }
26203  }
26204 
26205  static int parseText(OS * os, int params, int, int, void*)
26206  {
26207  if(params < 1){
26208  return 0;
26209  }
26210  String str = os->toString(-params);
26211  if(str.getDataSize() == 0){
26212  return 0;
26213  }
26214  Core::Tokenizer tokenizer(os);
26215  tokenizer.parseText(str.toChar(), str.getLen(), String(os), false,
26216  params >= 2 ? (OS_ESourceCodeType)os->toInt(-params+1) : OS_SOURCECODE_AUTO,
26217  params >= 3 ? os->toBool(-params+2) : true);
26218  pushTokensAsObject(os, tokenizer);
26219  return 1;
26220  }
26221 
26222  static int parseFile(OS * os, int params, int, int, void*)
26223  {
26224  if(params < 1){
26225  return 0;
26226  }
26227  String filename = os->resolvePath(os->toString(-params));
26228  if(filename.getDataSize() == 0){
26229  return 0;
26230  }
26231  Core::FileStreamReader file(os, filename);
26232  if(!file.f){
26233  return 0;
26234  }
26235  Core::MemStreamWriter file_data(os);
26236  file_data.writeFromStream(&file);
26237 
26238  Core::Tokenizer tokenizer(os);
26239  tokenizer.parseText((OS_CHAR*)file_data.buffer.buf, file_data.buffer.count, filename, true,
26240  params >= 2 ? (OS_ESourceCodeType)os->toInt(-params+1) : OS_SOURCECODE_AUTO,
26241  params >= 3 ? os->toBool(-params+2) : true);
26242 
26243  pushTokensAsObject(os, tokenizer);
26244  return 1;
26245  }
26246  };
26247 
26248  FuncDef list[] = {
26249  {OS_TEXT("parseText"), LangTokenizer::parseText},
26250  {OS_TEXT("parseFile"), LangTokenizer::parseFile},
26251  {}
26252  };
26253 
26254  NumberDef numbers[] = {
26255  {OS_TEXT("TOKEN_TYPE_STRING"), LangTokenizer::TOKEN_TYPE_STRING},
26256  {OS_TEXT("TOKEN_TYPE_NUMBER"), LangTokenizer::TOKEN_TYPE_NUMBER},
26257  {OS_TEXT("TOKEN_TYPE_NAME"), LangTokenizer::TOKEN_TYPE_NAME},
26258  {OS_TEXT("TOKEN_TYPE_OPERATOR"), LangTokenizer::TOKEN_TYPE_OPERATOR},
26259  {}
26260  };
26261 
26262  getModule(OS_TEXT("LangTokenizer"));
26263  setFuncs(list);
26264  setNumbers(numbers);
26265  pop();
26266 }

26305  function unhandledException(e){

26313  printf("#${i} ${t.file}%s: %s, args: ${t.arguments}\n",
26314  t.line > 0 ? "(${t.line},${t.pos})" : "",
26315  t.object && t.object !== _G ? "<${typeOf(t.object)}#${t.object.__id}:classname=${t.object.classname}>.${t.func.__name}" : t.func.__name)
26316  }
26317  }

26413 OS::Core::GCValue * OS::Core::initNewInstance(GCValue * object)
26414 {
26415  struct InitNewInstance
26416  {
26417  Core * core;
26418  GCValue * object;
26419  Value value;
26420 
26421  InitNewInstance(Core * p_core, GCValue * p_object)
26422  {
26423  core = p_core;
26424  object = p_object;
26425  if(object){
26426  if(!object->table || !object->table->count){
26427  setProperties_r(object->prototype);
26428  cloneProperties();
26429  }else{
26430  setAndCloneProperties_r(object->prototype);
26431  }
26432  }
26433  }
26434 
26435  void setProperties_r(GCValue * prototype)
26436  {
26437  if(prototype){
26438  setProperties_r(prototype->prototype);
26439  if(core->getPropertyValue(value, prototype, core->strings->__object, false)){
26440  GCValue * object_props = value.getGCValue();
26441  if(object_props && object_props->table){
26442  Property * prop = object_props->table->first;
26443  for(; prop; prop = prop->next){
26444  core->setPropertyValue(object, prop->index, prop->value, false);
26445  }
26446  }
26447  }
26448  }
26449  }
26450 
26451  void setAndCloneProperties_r(GCValue * prototype)
26452  {
26453  if(prototype){
26454  setProperties_r(prototype->prototype);
26455  if(core->getPropertyValue(value, prototype, core->strings->__object, false)){
26456  GCValue * object_props = value.getGCValue();
26457  if(object_props && object_props->table){
26458  Property * prop = object_props->table->first;
26459  for(; prop; prop = prop->next){
26460  core->pushCloneValue(prop->value);
26461  core->setPropertyValue(object, prop->index, core->stack_values.lastElement(), false);
26462  core->pop();
26463  }
26464  }
26465  }
26466  }
26467  }
26468 
26469  void cloneProperties()
26470  {
26471  if(object->table){
26472  Property * prop = object->table->first;
26473  for(; prop; prop = prop->next){
26474  core->pushCloneValue(prop->value);
26475  core->setValue(prop->value, core->stack_values.lastElement());
26476  core->pop();
26477  }
26478  }
26479  }
26480  };
26481  InitNewInstance(this, object);
26482  return object;
26483 }
26484 
26485 void OS::Core::pushArguments(StackFunction * stack_func)
26486 {
26487  if(!stack_func->arguments){
26488  int num_params = stack_func->num_params;
26489  if(stack_func->rest_arguments && num_params == PRE_VARS){
26490  retainValue(stack_func->arguments = stack_func->rest_arguments);
26491  pushValue(stack_func->arguments);
26492  return;
26493  }
26494  int i;
26495  GCArrayValue * args = pushArrayValue(num_params - PRE_VARS + (stack_func->rest_arguments ? stack_func->rest_arguments->values.count : 0));
26496  Locals * func_locals = stack_func->locals;
26497  for(i = PRE_VARS; i < num_params; i++){
26498  retainValue(func_locals->values[i]);
26499  allocator->vectorAddItem(args->values, func_locals->values[i] OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
26500  }
26501  if(stack_func->rest_arguments){
26502  GCArrayValue * arr = stack_func->rest_arguments;
26503  for(i = 0; i < arr->values.count; i++){
26504  setPropertyValue(args, Value(args->values.count), arr->values[i], false);
26505  }
26506  }
26507  retainValue(args);
26508  stack_func->arguments = args;
26509  }else{
26510  pushValue(stack_func->arguments);
26511  }
26512 }
26513 
26514 void OS::Core::pushArgumentsWithNames(StackFunction * stack_func)
26515 {
26516  int i;
26517  GCObjectValue * args = pushObjectValue();
26518  Locals * func_locals = stack_func->locals;
26519  FunctionDecl * func_decl = stack_func->func->func_decl;
26520  int num_params = stack_func->num_params;
26521  for(i = PRE_VARS; i < num_params; i++){ // skip func & this
26522  setPropertyValue(args, func_decl->locals[i].name.string, func_locals->values[i], false);
26523  }
26524  if(num_params < func_decl->num_params){
26525  for(; i < func_decl->num_params; i++){
26526  setPropertyValue(args, func_decl->locals[i].name.string, Value(), false);
26527  }
26528  }else if(stack_func->rest_arguments){
26529  GCArrayValue * arr = stack_func->rest_arguments;
26530  for(i = 0; i < arr->values.count; i++){
26531  setPropertyValue(args, Value(args->table ? args->table->next_index : 0), arr->values[i], false);
26532  }
26533  }
26534 }
26535 
26536 void OS::Core::pushRestArguments(StackFunction * stack_func)
26537 {
26538  if(!stack_func->rest_arguments){
26539  stack_func->rest_arguments = pushArrayValue();
26540  retainValue(stack_func->rest_arguments);
26541  }else{
26542  pushValue(stack_func->rest_arguments);
26543  }
26544 }

26546 void OS::Core::pushBackTrace(int skip_funcs, int max_trace_funcs)
26547 {
26548  GCArrayValue * arr = pushArrayValue();
26549 
26550  String function_str(allocator, OS_TEXT("func"));
26551  String name_str(allocator, OS_TEXT("name"));
26552  String file_str(allocator, OS_TEXT("file"));
26553  String line_str(allocator, OS_TEXT("line"));
26554  String pos_str(allocator, OS_TEXT("pos"));
26555  String object_str(allocator, OS_TEXT("object"));
26556  String arguments_str(allocator, OS_TEXT("arguments"));
26557  String core_str(allocator, OS_TEXT("{{CORE}}"));
26558  String lambda_str(allocator, OS_TEXT("{{lambda}}"));
26559 
26560  if(skip_funcs < 0){
26561  skip_funcs = 0;
26562  }
26563  for(int i = call_stack_funcs.count-1-skip_funcs; i >= 0 && arr->values.count < max_trace_funcs; i--){
26564  StackFunction * stack_func = call_stack_funcs.buf + i;
26565 
26566  Program * prog = stack_func->func->prog;
26567  if((!stack_func->func->name || core_str == stack_func->func->name) && !prog->filename.getDataSize()){
26568  continue;
26569  }
26570 
26571  GCObjectValue * obj = pushObjectValue();
26572  setPropertyValue(obj, name_str, stack_func->func->name ? stack_func->func->name : lambda_str.string, false);
26573  setPropertyValue(obj, function_str, stack_func->func, false);
26574 
26575  const String& filename = prog->filename.getDataSize() ? prog->filename : core_str;
26576  setPropertyValue(obj, file_str, filename.string, false);
26577 
26578  Program::DebugInfoItem * debug_info = NULL;
26579  if(prog->filename.getDataSize() && prog->debug_info.count > 0){
26580  int opcode_pos = (int)(stack_func->opcodes - prog->opcodes.buf); // .getPos() + stack_func->func->func_decl->opcodes_pos;
26581  debug_info = prog->getDebugInfo(opcode_pos);
26582  }
26583  setPropertyValue(obj, line_str, debug_info ? (int)debug_info->line : Value(), false);
26584  setPropertyValue(obj, pos_str, debug_info ? (int)debug_info->pos : Value(), false);
26585 
26586  OS_ASSERT(stack_func->locals->values);
26587  setPropertyValue(obj, object_str, stack_func->locals->values[PRE_VAR_THIS], false);
26588 
26589  pushArgumentsWithNames(stack_func);
26590  setPropertyValue(obj, arguments_str, stack_values.lastElement(), false);
26591  pop(); // remove args
26592 
26593  setPropertyValue(arr, Value(arr->values.count), obj, false);
26594  pop(); // remove obj
26595  }
26596 }
26597 
26598 void OS::Core::callFT(int start_pos, int call_params, int ret_values, GCValue * self_for_proto, OS_ECallEnter call_enter, OS_ECallType call_type, OS_ECallThisUsage call_this_usage)
26599 {
26600  OS_ASSERT(start_pos >= OS_TOP_STACK_NULL_VALUES && call_params >= 2 && start_pos + call_params <= stack_values.count);
26601  if(!terminated){
26602  Value& func = stack_values[start_pos + PRE_VAR_FUNC];
26603  switch(OS_VALUE_TYPE(func)){
26604  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_FUNCTION:
26605  {
26606  OS_ASSERT(dynamic_cast<GCFunctionValue*>(OS_VALUE_VARIANT(func).func));
26607  GCFunctionValue * func_value = OS_VALUE_VARIANT(func).func;
26608  FunctionDecl * func_decl = func_value->func_decl;
26609 
26610  reserveStackValues(start_pos + (func_decl->stack_size > ret_values ? func_decl->stack_size : ret_values));
26611 
26612  if(call_stack_funcs.count >= max_call_stack && !call_stack_overflow){
26613  call_stack_overflow = true;
26614  allocator->setException("call stack overflow");
26615  break;
26616  }
26617  if(call_stack_funcs.capacity < call_stack_funcs.count+1){
26618  call_stack_funcs.capacity = call_stack_funcs.capacity > 0 ? call_stack_funcs.capacity*2 : 8;
26619  OS_ASSERT(call_stack_funcs.capacity >= call_stack_funcs.count+1);
26620 
26621  StackFunction * new_buf = (StackFunction*)malloc(sizeof(StackFunction)*call_stack_funcs.capacity OS_DBG_FILEPOS);
26622  OS_MEMCPY(new_buf, call_stack_funcs.buf, sizeof(StackFunction) * call_stack_funcs.count);
26623  free(call_stack_funcs.buf);
26624  call_stack_funcs.buf = new_buf;
26625  }
26626 
26627  // it should be here before call_stack_funcs.count++ !!! don't move it
26628  GCArrayValue * rest_arguments;
26629  if(call_params > func_decl->num_params){
26630  int num_extra_params = call_params - func_decl->num_params;
26631  retainValue(rest_arguments = pushArrayValue(num_extra_params)); pop();
26632  OS_MEMCPY(rest_arguments->values.buf, stack_values.buf + start_pos + func_decl->num_params, sizeof(Value) * num_extra_params);
26633  retainValues(rest_arguments->values.buf, num_extra_params);
26634  rest_arguments->values.count = num_extra_params;
26635  call_params = func_decl->num_params;
26636  }else{
26637  rest_arguments = NULL;
26638  }
26639 
26640  StackFunction * stack_func = call_stack_funcs.buf + call_stack_funcs.count++;
26641  stack_func->func = func_value;
26642 
26643  stack_func->rest_arguments = rest_arguments;
26644  stack_func->arguments = NULL;
26645 
26646  stack_func->locals_stack_pos = start_pos;
26647  stack_func->num_params = call_params;
26648 
26649  Locals * func_locals = (Locals*)(malloc(sizeof(Locals) + sizeof(Locals*) * func_decl->func_depth OS_DBG_FILEPOS));
26650  func_locals->prog = func_value->prog->retain();
26651  func_locals->func_decl = func_decl;
26652  func_locals->values = stack_values.buf + stack_func->locals_stack_pos;
26653  func_locals->is_stack_locals = true;
26654  // func_locals->num_parents = func_decl->func_depth;
26655  func_locals->ref_count = 1;
26656  func_locals->gc_step_type = 0;
26657  if(func_decl->func_depth > 0){
26658  OS_ASSERT(func_value->locals && func_value->locals->func_decl->func_depth == func_decl->func_depth-1);
26659  Locals ** parents = func_locals->getParents();
26660  parents[0] = func_value->locals->retain();
26661  if(func_decl->func_depth > 1){
26662  OS_MEMCPY(parents+1, func_value->locals->getParents(), sizeof(Locals*) * (func_decl->func_depth-1));
26663  }
26664  }
26665  stack_func->locals = func_locals;
26666 
26667  int clear_values = func_decl->stack_size - call_params;
26668  if(clear_values > 0){
26669  OS_SET_NULL_VALUES(func_locals->values + call_params, clear_values);
26670  }
26671 
26672  stack_func->need_ret_values = ret_values;
26673  stack_func->opcodes = func_value->prog->opcodes.buf + func_decl->opcodes_pos;
26674 
26675  if(self_for_proto){
26676  retainValue(stack_func->self_for_proto = self_for_proto);
26677  }else if(!(stack_func->self_for_proto = func_locals->values[PRE_VAR_THIS].getGCValue())){
26678  switch(OS_VALUE_TYPE(func_locals->values[PRE_VAR_THIS])){
26679  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_BOOL:
26680  retainValue(stack_func->self_for_proto = prototypes[PROTOTYPE_BOOL]);
26681  break;
26682 
26683  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_NUMBER:
26684  retainValue(stack_func->self_for_proto = prototypes[PROTOTYPE_NUMBER]);
26685  break;
26686 
26687  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_STRING:
26688  retainValue(stack_func->self_for_proto = prototypes[PROTOTYPE_STRING]);
26689  break;
26690  }
26691  }else{
26692  retainValue(stack_func->self_for_proto);
26693  }
26694 
26695  stack_func->caller_stack_size = stack_values.count;
26696 
26697  OS_ASSERT(stack_func->locals_stack_pos + func_decl->stack_size <= stack_values.capacity);
26698  stack_values.count = stack_func->locals_stack_pos + func_decl->stack_size;
26699 
26700  if(call_this_usage == OS_CALLTHIS_FUNCTION_OVERWRITE){
26701  func_locals->values[PRE_VAR_THIS] = func_value->self;
26702  }
26703 
26704  func_locals->values[func_decl->num_params + POST_VAR_ENV] = func_value->env;
26705  func_locals->values[func_decl->num_params + POST_VAR_GLOBALS] = global_vars;
26706 
26707  reloadStackFunctionCache();
26708 
26709  if(call_enter == OS_CALLENTER_ALLOW_ONLY_ENTER){
26710  return;
26711  }
26712  return execute();
26713  }
26714 
26715  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_CFUNCTION:
26716  {
26717  OS_ASSERT(dynamic_cast<GCCFunctionValue*>(OS_VALUE_VARIANT(func).cfunc));
26718  OS_ASSERT(start_pos + call_params <= stack_values.count);
26719  int save_stack_size = stack_values.count;
26720  GCCFunctionValue * cfunc_value = OS_VALUE_VARIANT(func).cfunc;
26721  if(cfunc_value->num_closure_values > 0){
26722  reserveStackValues(start_pos + call_params + cfunc_value->num_closure_values);
26723  Value * closure_values = (Value*)(cfunc_value + 1);
26724  OS_MEMCPY(stack_values.buf + start_pos + call_params, closure_values, sizeof(Value)*cfunc_value->num_closure_values);
26725  }
26726  stack_values.count = start_pos + call_params + cfunc_value->num_closure_values;
26727  int cur_ret_values;
26728  try{
26729  cur_ret_values = cfunc_value->func(allocator, call_params - 2, cfunc_value->num_closure_values, ret_values, cfunc_value->user_param);
26730  }catch(...){
26731  cur_ret_values = 0;
26732  allocator->setException(OS_TEXT("internal error"));
26733  }
26734  #if 0 // do save closure values?
26735  if(cfunc_value->num_closure_values > 0){
26736  Value * closure_values = (Value*)(cfunc_value + 1);
26737  OS_MEMCPY(closure_values, stack_values.buf + start_pos + call_params, sizeof(Value)*cfunc_value->num_closure_values);
26738  }
26739  #endif
26740  if(ret_values == 1){
26741  if(cur_ret_values > 0){
26742  stack_values.buf[start_pos] = stack_values.buf[stack_values.count - cur_ret_values];
26743  }else{
26744  OS_SET_VALUE_NULL(stack_values.buf[start_pos]);
26745  }
26746  }else if(ret_values > 0){
26747  Value * stack_func_locals = stack_values.buf + stack_values.count - cur_ret_values;
26748  if(ret_values <= cur_ret_values){
26749  OS_MEMMOVE(stack_values.buf + start_pos, stack_func_locals, sizeof(Value) * ret_values);
26750  }else{
26751  if(cur_ret_values > 0){
26752  OS_MEMMOVE(stack_values.buf + start_pos, stack_func_locals, sizeof(Value) * cur_ret_values);
26753  }
26754  OS_SET_NULL_VALUES(stack_values.buf + start_pos + cur_ret_values, ret_values - cur_ret_values);
26755  }
26756  }
26757  if(save_stack_size > stack_values.count){
26758  OS_ASSERT(save_stack_size <= stack_values.capacity);
26759  OS_SET_NULL_VALUES(stack_values.buf + stack_values.count, save_stack_size - stack_values.count);
26760  }
26761  stack_values.count = save_stack_size;
26762  return;
26763  }
26764 
26765  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_OBJECT:
26766  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_USERDATA:
26767  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_USERPTR:
26768  if(call_type == OS_CALLTYPE_FUNC){
26769  allocator->setException(String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("attempt to call not function: %s"), getTypeStr(func).toChar()));
26770  }else{
26771  Value value;
26772  Value class_value = func; // we should create stack value here because of stack_values could be resized
26773  bool prototype_enabled = false;
26774  if(getPropertyValue(value, class_value, strings->__instantiable, prototype_enabled) && valueToBool(value)){
26775  prototype_enabled = true;
26776  if(getPropertyValue(value, class_value, strings->__newinstance, prototype_enabled)){
26777  stack_values.buf[start_pos + 0] = value;
26778  stack_values.buf[start_pos + 1] = class_value;
26779  callFT(start_pos, call_params, ret_values, NULL, OS_CALLENTER_EXECUTE_AND_RETURN, OS_CALLTYPE_FUNC, OS_CALLTHIS_KEEP_STACK_VALUE);
26780  return;
26781  }else{
26782  allocator->setException(String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("method %s is not implemented in %s"),
26783  strings->__newinstance.toChar(), getValueNameOrClassname(class_value).toChar()));
26784  }
26785  }else{
26786  if(value.isNull()){
26787  prototype_enabled = true;
26788  if(getPropertyValue(value, class_value, strings->__callinstance, prototype_enabled)){
26789  stack_values.buf[start_pos + 0] = value;
26790  stack_values.buf[start_pos + 1] = class_value;
26791  callFT(start_pos, call_params, ret_values, NULL, OS_CALLENTER_EXECUTE_AND_RETURN, OS_CALLTYPE_FUNC, OS_CALLTHIS_KEEP_STACK_VALUE);
26792  return;
26793  }else{
26794  allocator->setException(String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("attempt to call instance of %s"), getValueNameOrClassname(class_value).toChar()));
26795  }
26796  }else{
26797  allocator->setException(String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("%s is not instantiable"), getValueNameOrClassname(class_value).toChar()));
26798  }
26799  }
26800  break;
26801  }
26802 
26803  case OS_VALUE_TYPE_NULL:
26804  break;
26805 
26806  default:
26807  allocator->setException(String::format(allocator, OS_TEXT("attempt to call not function: %s"), getTypeStr(func).toChar()));
26808  break;
26809  }
26810  }else{
26811  // terminated
26812  int i = 0;
26813  }
26814  reserveStackValues(start_pos + ret_values);
26815  OS_SET_NULL_VALUES(stack_values.buf + start_pos, ret_values);
26816 }
26817 
26818 void OS::Core::callFT(int params, int ret_values, GCValue * self_for_proto, OS_ECallEnter call_enter, OS_ECallType call_type, OS_ECallThisUsage call_this_usage)
26819 {
26820  params += 2;
26821  int start_pos = stack_values.count - params;
26822  callFT(start_pos, params, ret_values, self_for_proto, call_enter, call_type, call_this_usage);
26823  stack_values.count = start_pos + ret_values;
26824 }

26830  GCValue * self_for_proto = NULL;
26831  callFT(start_pos, params, ret_values, self_for_proto, OS_CALLENTER_EXECUTE_AND_RETURN, call_type, call_this_usage);
26832  stack_values.count = start_pos + ret_values;
26833 }

26840  exchangeStackValues(start_pos);
26841  callFT(start_pos, params, ret_values, self_for_proto, OS_CALLENTER_EXECUTE_AND_RETURN, call_type, call_this_usage);
26842  stack_values.count = start_pos + ret_values;
26843 }

26845 void OS::Core::callF(int params, int ret_values, OS_ECallType call_type)
26846 {
26847  // insert null as 'this' value to get stack values properly
26848  if(params > 0){
26849 #if 1
26850  int offs = stack_values.count - params;
26851 
26852  // reserveStackValues(stack_values.count+1);
26853  int new_count = stack_values.count + 1;
26854  if(stack_values.capacity < new_count){
26855  growStackValues(new_count);
26856  }
26857  stack_values.count = new_count;
26858  /* if(offs < 0){
26859  OS_ASSERT(false);
26860  return;
26861  } */
26862  int count = stack_values.count - offs - 1;
26863  OS_ASSERT(count > 0);
26864  if(count == 1){
26865  stack_values[offs+1] = stack_values[offs];
26866  }else{
26867  OS_MEMMOVE(stack_values.buf + offs+1, stack_values.buf + offs, sizeof(Value) * count);
26868  }
26869  OS_SET_VALUE_NULL(stack_values[offs]);
26870 #else
26871  insertValue(Value(), -params);
26872 #endif
26873  }else{
26874  pushNull();
26875  }
26876  params += 2;
26877  int start_pos = stack_values.count - params;
26878  GCValue * self_for_proto = NULL;
26879  callFT(start_pos, params, ret_values, self_for_proto, OS_CALLENTER_EXECUTE_AND_RETURN, call_type, OS_CALLTHIS_FUNCTION_OVERWRITE);
26880  stack_values.count = start_pos + ret_values;
26881 }

26892 bool OS::compileFile(const String& p_filename, bool required, OS_ESourceCodeType source_code_type, bool check_utf8_bom)
26893 {
26894  String filename = resolvePath(p_filename);
26895  bool is_compiled = getFilenameExt(filename) == OS_EXT_COMPILED;
26896  String compiled_filename = is_compiled ? filename : getCompiledFilename(filename);
26897  bool sourcecode_file_exist = is_compiled ? false : isFileExist(filename);
26898  bool compiled_file_exist = isFileExist(compiled_filename);
26899  bool recompile_enabled = false;
26900  if(core->settings.sourcecode_must_exist && !sourcecode_file_exist){
26901  compiled_file_exist = false;
26902  }
26903  if(compiled_file_exist && sourcecode_file_exist){
26904  if(core->settings.primary_compiled_file || checkFileUsage(filename, compiled_filename) == LOAD_COMPILED_FILE){
26905  sourcecode_file_exist = false;
26906  recompile_enabled = true;
26907  }else{
26908  compiled_file_exist = false;
26909  }
26910  }
26911  if(!sourcecode_file_exist && !compiled_file_exist){
26912  if(required){
26913  setException(String::format(this, OS_TEXT("required filename %s is not exist"), p_filename.toChar()));
26914  pushNull();
26915  return false;
26916  }
26917  pushNull();
26918  return false;
26919  }
26920  if(!sourcecode_file_exist){
26921  OS_ASSERT(compiled_file_exist);
26922  Core::Program * prog = new (malloc(sizeof(Core::Program) OS_DBG_FILEPOS)) Core::Program(this);
26923  // prog->filename = compiled_filename;
26924 
26925  Core::FileStreamReader prog_file_reader(this, compiled_filename);
26926  Core::MemStreamWriter prog_file_data(this);
26927  prog_file_data.writeFromStream(&prog_file_reader);
26928  Core::MemStreamReader prog_reader(NULL, prog_file_data.buffer.buf, prog_file_data.getSize());
26929 
26930  if(prog->loadFromStream(&prog_reader)){
26931  prog->pushStartFunction();
26932  prog->release();
26933  return true;
26934  }
26935  prog->release();
26936  if(!recompile_enabled){
26937  pushNull();
26938  return false;
26939  }
26940  }
26941 
26942  Core::FileStreamReader file(this, filename);
26943  if(!file.f){
26944  setException(String::format(this, OS_TEXT("error open filename %s"), p_filename.toChar()));
26945  pushNull();
26946  return false;
26947  }
26948 
26949  Core::MemStreamWriter file_data(this);
26950  file_data.writeFromStream(&file);
26951 
26952  if(source_code_type == OS_SOURCECODE_AUTO){
26953  source_code_type = getSourceCodeType(filename);
26954  }
26955 
26956  Core::Tokenizer tokenizer(this);
26957  tokenizer.parseText((OS_CHAR*)file_data.buffer.buf, file_data.buffer.count, filename, true, source_code_type, check_utf8_bom);
26958 
26959  Core::Compiler compiler(&tokenizer);
26960  return compiler.compile();
26961 }

27119 int OS::setSetting(OS_ESettings setting, int value)
27120 {
27121  struct Lib {
27122  static int ret(bool& cur_value, int new_value)
27123  {
27124  int old = cur_value;
27125  cur_value = new_value ? true : false;
27126  return old;
27127  }
27128  };
27129 
27130  switch(setting){
27131  case OS_SETTING_CREATE_DEBUG_INFO:
27132  return Lib::ret(core->settings.create_debug_info, value);
27133 
27134  case OS_SETTING_CREATE_TEXT_OPCODES:
27135  return Lib::ret(core->settings.create_text_opcodes, value);
27136 
27137  case OS_SETTING_CREATE_TEXT_EVAL_OPCODES:
27138  return Lib::ret(core->settings.create_text_eval_opcodes, value);
27139 
27140  case OS_SETTING_CREATE_COMPILED_FILE:
27141  return Lib::ret(core->settings.create_compiled_file, value);
27142 
27143  case OS_SETTING_PRIMARY_COMPILED_FILE:
27144  return Lib::ret(core->settings.primary_compiled_file, value);
27145 
27146  case OS_SETTING_SOURCECODE_MUST_EXIST:
27147  return Lib::ret(core->settings.sourcecode_must_exist, value);
27148 
27149  default:
27150  OS_ASSERT(false);
27151  }
27152  return -1;
27153 }

27174 
27175 #define OS_QSORT_CUTOFF 8
27176 
27177 static void qsortSwap(char *a, char *b, unsigned width)
27178 {
27179  if(a != b) {
27180  if(width == sizeof(void*)){
27181  void * tmp = *(void**)a;
27182  *(void**)a = *(void**)b;
27183  *(void**)b = tmp;
27184  return;
27185  }
27186  if(width >= 16 && width <= 256){
27187  void * tmp = alloca(width);
27188  OS_MEMCPY(tmp, a, width);
27189  OS_MEMCPY(a, b, width);
27190  OS_MEMCPY(b, tmp, width);
27191  return;
27192  }
27193  while(width--){
27194  char tmp = *a;
27195  *a++ = *b;
27196  *b++ = tmp;
27197  }
27198  }
27199 }
27200 
27201 static void qsortShortsort(OS * os, char *lo, char *hi, unsigned width, int (*comp)(OS*, const void *, const void *, void*), void * user_params)
27202 {
27203  char *p, *max;
27204 
27205  while (hi > lo) {
27206  max = lo;
27207  for (p = lo + width; p <= hi; p += width) if (comp(os, p, max, user_params) > 0) max = p;
27208  qsortSwap(max, hi, width);
27209  hi -= width;
27210  }
27211 }
27212 
27213 void OS::qsort(void *base, unsigned num, unsigned width, int (*comp)(OS*, const void *, const void *, void*), void * user_params)
27214 {
27215  char *lo, *hi;
27216  char *mid;
27217  char *l, *h;
27218  unsigned size;
27219  char *lostk[30], *histk[30];
27220  int stkptr;
27221 
27222  if (num < 2 || width == 0) return;
27223  stkptr = 0;
27224 
27225  lo = (char*)base;
27226  hi = (char*)base + width * (num - 1);
27227 
27228 recurse:
27229  size = (unsigned)((hi - lo) / width + 1);
27230 
27231  if (size <= OS_QSORT_CUTOFF) {
27232  qsortShortsort(this, lo, hi, width, comp, user_params);
27233  } else {
27234  mid = lo + (size / 2) * width;
27235  qsortSwap(mid, lo, width);
27236 
27237  l = lo;
27238  h = hi + width;
27239 
27240  for (;;) {
27241  do { l += width; } while (l <= hi && comp(this, l, lo, user_params) <= 0);
27242  do { h -= width; } while (h > lo && comp(this, h, lo, user_params) >= 0);
27243  if (h < l) break;
27244  qsortSwap(l, h, width);
27245  }
27246 
27247  qsortSwap(lo, h, width);
27248 
27249  if (h - 1 - lo >= hi - l) {
27250  if (lo + width < h) {
27251  lostk[stkptr] = lo;
27252  histk[stkptr] = h - width;
27253  ++stkptr;
27254  }
27255 
27256  if (l < hi) {
27257  lo = l;
27258  goto recurse;
27259  }
27260  } else {
27261  if (l < hi) {
27262  lostk[stkptr] = l;
27263  histk[stkptr] = hi;
27264  ++stkptr;
27265  }
27266 
27267  if (lo + width < h) {
27268  hi = h - width;
27269  goto recurse;
27270  }
27271  }
27272  }
27273 
27274  --stkptr;
27275  if (stkptr >= 0) {
27276  lo = lostk[stkptr];
27277  hi = histk[stkptr];
27278  goto recurse;
27279  }
27280 }

27293  // data_hash = 0;

27300 FunctionDataChain * FunctionDataChain::find()
27301 {
27302  FunctionDataChain * cur = function_data_first;
27303  for(; cur; cur = cur->next){
27304  if(cur->data_size == data_size && OS_MEMCMP(cur->ptr, ptr, data_size) == 0){
27305  return cur;
27306  }
27307  }
27308  return NULL;
27309 }

27312 {

27314  function_data_first = this;
27315 }

27317 void ObjectScript::finalizeAllBinds()
27318 {
27319  while(function_data_first){
27320  FunctionDataChain * cur = function_data_first;
27321  function_data_first = cur->next;
27322  delete cur;
27323  }
27324 }
